7, 'I didn''t want to escape my life and become a big actress and live my dreams. That was never the way it was it was just these amazing opportunities that happened. ', 21196, 0), (430038, 'When I first set out to do it, I wanted to be a working actor, and now it seems like it''s superseded even my dreams.', 68251, 0), (430039, 'I tell kids to pursue their basketball dreams, but I tell them to not let that be their only dream.', 19298, 0), (430040, 'It is exactly because we are a city that embraces freedom, that welcomes everyone and encourages their dreams, that New York remains on the front lines in the war on terror.', 67699, 0), (430041, 'Ironically, it is exactly because we are a city that embraces freedom, that welcomes everyone and encourages their dreams, that New York remains on the front lines in the war on terror.', 67699, 0), (430042, 'To be able to help a 13-year-old kid from the Bronx follow her dreams just by letting her know she''s not forgotten in this crazy world - that''s why I got involved with Frum Tha Ground Up.', 558, 0), (430043, 'My office is at Yankee stadium. Yes, dreams do come true.', 66702, 0), (430044, 'My dreams do not end with playing Major League Baseball.', 66702, 0), (430045, 'In a couple, sometimes, one or both people have to give up their personal life, dreams and ambitions for the good of the family.', 47394, 0), (430046, 'That always has been one of my dreams, to be able to appeal to a bunch of people.', 68252, 0), (430047, 'Tamerlan Tsarnaev, one of the two brothers who carried out the marathon bombing, was a non-practicing Muslim who only became an Islamist militant once his dreams of becoming an Olympic boxer faded. At the time of the attack, he was unemployed.', 68253, 0), (430048, 'I must refine my training every day to give myself the best opportunity to achieve my dreams during the Olympic Games in Rio.', 68254, 0), (430049, 'In our marriage, the success of our athletic dreams comes before everything. ''Hey do you want