t out of the way so they can take care of their families and pursue their dreams.', 68318, 0), (430241, 'Our theme for this year''s festivities, Dreams and Challenges of Asian Pacific Americans, speaks to the many generations of Asian Pacific Americans who worked hard to overcome economic hardship, racism and other barriers in their pursuit of the American dream.', 66776, 0), (430242, 'Dreams look real, but they''re in your mind, so you realize that the physical world is also a construction, which shows that the mind can affect reality in more ways than you can imagine.', 44406, 0), (430243, 'When you''re a young English person who wants to be an actress and you have dreams, you dream of being Vanessa Redgrave or Judi Dench.', 68319, 0), (430244, 'Although the events we appear to perceive in dreams are illusory, our feelings in response to dream content are real. Indeed, most of the events we experience in dreams are real; when we experience feelings, say, anxiety or ecstasy, in dreams, we really do feel anxious or ecstatic at the time.', 44406, 0), (430245, 'The whole idea of a dream, to me, is a mystery plane. Things are operating there that tell us the real truth. The stuff going on inside us that we don''t express or even know about pours out in our dreams.', 68320, 0), (430246, 'Dream and give yourself permission to envision a You that you choose to be.', 68321, 0), (430247, 'Looking back 25 years later, what I may say is that the facts have been far better than the dreams. In the long course of cell life on this earth it remained, for our age for our generation, to receive the full ownership of our inheritance.', 67415, 0), (430248, 'Worse than not realizing the dreams of your youth, would be to have been young and never dreamed at all.', 10044, 0), (430249, 'And our dreams are who we are.', 30125, 0), (430250, 'I have always been amazed at the way an ordinary observer lends so much more credence and attaches so much more importance to waking events than to those occurring in dreams... Man... is above all the plaything of his memory.', 168, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (430251, 'My life has been a continuous fulfillment of dreams. It appears that everything I saw and did has a new, and perhaps, more significant meaning, every time I see it. The earth is good. It is a privilege to live thereon.', 67479, 0), (430252, 'I was a great dreamer of day dreams.', 68322, 0), (430253, 'To see your friend''s dreams come true, there''s really nothing that can make you happier.', 68323, 0), (430254, 'I just want that sensation you have in dreams when you fly to be real.', 68324, 0), (430255, 'The idea of being able to serve as an example, based upon how to process, how to think, how to realize our own dreams, we can pass that down to our children.', 68325, 0), (430256, 'I think everyone has dreams, and it''s just how you go about pursuing that. And I think anybody can do anything that they set their mind to. So if you set your mind to do something, and you exhaust every opportunity, I think you''re going to get there.', 68326, 0), (430257, 'I never remember my dreams.', 68327, 0), (430258, 'Right before ''American Dreams,'' I started to pursue these avenues, like short films and getting into a couple night courses to really study photography and cinematography, and the language of visual storytelling.', 68328, 0), (430259, 'Take everything easy and quit dreaming and brooding and you will be well guarded from a thousand evils.', 8660, 0), (430260, 'Married or unmarried, young or old, poet or worker, you are still a dreamer, and will one time know, and feel, that your life is but a dream.', 62297, 0), (430261, 'I put a lot of faith in dreams. I know that big movie roles and opportunities are going to happen.', 68329, 0), (430262, 'I spend a lot of time practicing active imagination before I go to sleep. What I''m feeling will manifest as images through active imagination. And then I go to sleep, and those play out even more in my dreams.', 68330, 0), (430263, 'The Oval Office symbolizes...