ou fly an hour and a half and you''re in the mountains in three feet of powder. I also think it''s a much better city if you''re working as an actor. If you''re not working and you don''t see your dreams coming true, there can be a lot of heartache.', 68336, 0), (430275, 'At the end of the day, life''s about realising one''s human potential. I don''t know if I''ve realised mine, but I''ve certainly gone a long way towards realising some goals and some dreams.', 68337, 0), (430276, 'You have to dream dreams to live dreams.', 68338, 0), (430277, 'For over two centuries, Americans have grown up in a society that rewards hard work, protects innovation, and allows its citizens to constantly break new barriers. The key element to this success rests on freedom and the ability of individuals to strive toward achieving their dreams and making their children''s futures better than their own.', 68339, 0), (430278, 'If dreams are like movies, then memories are films about ghosts.', 68340, 0), (430279, 'Big dreams create the magic that stir men''s souls to greatness.', 68341, 0), (430280, 'Within months after reading the novel ''The Hunger Games,'' I went from telling my mom that I could see myself as this character to actually getting the role. My mother reminds me that if I could manifest such an important role just because I wanted it so much, all of my dreams are possible.', 28407, 0), (430281, 'We should never discourage young people from dreaming dreams.', 68342, 0), (430282, 'Sometimes, I get ideas from dreams. Often, my stories are based on adventures that I, or my friends, have actually lived.', 3972, 0), (430283, 'In my dreams I am not crippled. In my dreams, I dance.', 52541, 0), (430284, 'If you choose not to pursue your dreams, you''ll still be a part of a dream - only it will be someone else''s.', 68343, 0), (430285, 'If there is one place on the face of earth where all the dreams of living men have found a home from the very earliest days when man began the dream 