s solemn secrets of ourselves.', 68349, 0), (430297, 'Being as it was one of my dreams to sing with one of the world''s greatest groups, for me to join ''The Temptations'' was a great blessing.', 68350, 0), (430298, 'The most important thing in the world is family and love.', 1721, 0), (430299, 'One of the greatest titles in the world is parent, and one of the biggest blessings in the world is to have parents to call mom and dad.', 68351, 0), (430300, 'Anyone can be a father, but it takes someone special to be a dad, and that''s why I call you dad, because you are so special to me. You taught me the game and you taught me how to play it right.', 5512, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (430301, 'A real man loves his wife, and places his family as the most important thing in life. Nothing has brought me more peace and content in life than simply being a good husband and father.', 68352, 0), (430302, 'To a father growing old nothing is dearer than a daughter.', 542, 0), (430303, 'My dad is my best friend, my father, and my boss. When I do something that is exciting and he likes it, it feels three times as good as you can imagine.', 68353, 0), (430304, 'Being a father has been, without a doubt, my greatest source of achievement, pride and inspiration. Fatherhood has taught me about unconditional love, reinforced the importance of giving back and taught me how to be a better person.', 66796, 0), (430305, 'Until you have a son of your own... you will never know the joy, the love beyond feeling that resonates in the heart of a father as he looks upon his son.', 5155, 0), (430306, 'One father is more than a hundred schoolmasters.', 3428, 0), (430307, 'Dad, wherever you are, you are gone but you will never be forgotten.', 68354, 0), (430308, 'My dad was my best friend and greatest role model. He was an amazing dad, coach, mentor, soldier, husband and friend.', 11163, 0), (430309, 'I pray to be a good servant to God, a father, a husband, a son, a friend, a brother, an uncle, a good neighbor, a good leader to those who look up to me, a good follower to those who are serving God and doing the right thing.', 13187, 0), (430310, 'My dad''s my best mate, and he always will be.', 26070, 0), (430311, 'My father used to say that it''s never too late to do anything you wanted to do. And he said, ''You never know what you can accomplish until you try.''', 1813, 0), (430312, 'I think my mom put it best. She said, ''Little girls soften their daddy''s hearts.''', 55738, 0), (430313, 'It is a wise father that knows his own child.', 13, 0), (430314, 'You don''t have to deserve your mother''s love. You have to deserve your father''s.', 35, 0), (430315, 'Without my dad, I wouldn''t be here.', 68355, 0), (430316, 'Becoming a dad means you have to be a role model for your son and be someone he can look up to.', 68356, 0), (430317, 'I was raised in the greatest of homes... just a really great dad, and I miss him so much... he was a good man, a real simple man... Very faithful, always loved my mom, always provided for the kids, and just a lot of fun.', 86, 0), (430318, 'I would want my legacy to be that I was a great son, father and friend.', 68357, 0), (430319, 'Son, brother, father, lover, friend. There is room in the heart for all the affections, as there is room in heaven for all the stars.', 98, 0), (430320, 'Mothers play an important role as the heart of the home, but this in no way lessens the equally important role fathers should play, as head of the home, in nurturing, training, and loving their children.', 1826, 0), (430321, 'I''m a strong person, I''m a strong family man, I''m a strong husband and a strong father.', 67777, 0), (430322, 'Dad taught me everything I know. Unfortunately, he didn''t teach me everything he knows.', 68358, 0), (430323, 'I would say my greatest achievement in life right now - my greatest achievement period is - and I''m still trying to achieve it - is to be a wonderful father to my kids.', 58659, 0), (430324, 'I admire my father greatly.', 68359, 0), (430325, 'I have a Father''s Day every day.', 67949, 0), (430326, 'It''s an ongoing joy being a dad.', 67563, 0), (430327, 'It doesn''t matter who my father was it matters who I remember he was. ', 164, 0), (430328, 'A good father believes that he does wisely to encourage enterprise, productive skill, prudent self-denial, and judicious expenditure on the part of his son.', 48695, 0), (430329, 'I am not ashamed to say that no man I ever met was my father''s equal, and I never loved any other man as much.', 12987, 0), (430330, 'Man becomes man only by his intelligence, but he is man only by his heart.', 4754, 0), (430331, 'One of the greatest gifts my father gave me - unintentionally - was witnessing the courage with which he bore adversity. We had a bit of a rollercoaster life with some really challenging financial periods. He was always unshaken, completely tranquil, the same ebullient, laughing, jovial man.', 1028, 0), (430332, 'My role model is my dad.', 68360, 0), (430333, 'I decided in my life that I would do nothing that did not reflect positively on my father''s life.', 11458, 0), (430334, 'I mean, I look at my dad. He was twenty when he started having a family, and he was always the coolest dad. He did everything for his kids, and he never made us feel like he was pressured. I know that it must be a great feeling to be a guy like that.', 68361, 0), (430335, 'My Dad is my hero.', 68271, 0), (430336, 'Being a father helps me be more responsible... you see more things than you''ve ever seen.', 67013, 0), (430337, 'I''m a father that''s what matters most. Nothing matters more. ', 68362, 0), (430338, 'To me, having kids is the ultimate job in life. I want to be most successful at being a good father.', 68363, 0), (430339, 'I want to congratulate all the men out there who are working diligently to be good fathers whether they are stepfathers, or biological fathers or just spiritual fathers.', 225, 0), (430340, 'I was raised by my father I was daddy''s girl. ', 52565, 0), (430341, 'We should all aspire in life to do a multitude of things well - to be a great father, to be a good husband, to be a good lover, you know, to try to do things the best you can is very important to me.', 68364, 0), (430342, 'I imagine God to be like my father. My father was always the voice of certainty in my life. Certainty in the wisdom, certainty in the path, certainty always in God. For me God is certainty in everything. Certainty that everything is good and everything is God.', 11977, 0), (430343, 'The best thing about being a dad? Well, I think it''s just the thing that every man wants - to have a son and heir.', 23092, 0), (430344, 'I would love to be a father. I had a great father who taught me how gratifying that is. I''m not going to deny myself that. I think I''d be good at it. Everybody wants that experience. I definitely do.', 68365, 0), (430345, 'My dad''s not here, but he''s watching in heaven.', 68366, 0), (430346, 'I''m always going to love my father.', 67644, 0), (430347, 'Fatherhood is the best thing that could happen to me, and I''m just glad I can share my voice.', 68367, 0), (430348, 'This is the price you pay for having a great father. You get the wonder, the joy, the tender moments - and you get the tears at the end, too.', 439, 0), (430349, 'I can definitely say the older I''ve got the better I''ve become at being a dad and a husband.', 44554, 0), (430350, 'We looked up to our father. He still is much greater than us.', 22730, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (430351, 'In our house, Mother''s Day is every day. Father''s Day, too. In our house, parents count. They do important work and that work matters. One day just doesn''t cut for us.', 23135, 0), (430352, 'I had no expectations about fatherhood, really, but it''s definitely a journey I''m glad to be taking. Number one, it''s a great learning experience. When my mother told me it''s a 24/7 job, she wasn''t kidding.', 67796, 0), (430353, 'I wasn''t anything special as a father. But I loved them and they knew it.', 67573, 0), (430354, 'To be as good as our fathers we must be better, imitation is not discipleship.', 24952, 0), (430355, 'When it comes to Father''s Day, I will remember my dad for both being there to nurture me and also for the times he gave me on my own to cultivate my own interests and to nurture my own spirit.', 68368, 0), (430356, 'Our dad was a great guy and we will never forget him.', 68369, 0), (430357, 'I''m a good dad I spend a lot of time with my kids. ', 68370, 0), (430358, 'The number one thing I''ve been doing is being daddy.', 68371, 0), (430359, 'Father''s Day is hopefully a time when the culture says, ''This is our moment to look at who our men and boys are.''', 51291, 0), (430360, 'Old as she was, she still missed her daddy sometimes.', 185, 0), (430361, 'Smiling is definitely one of the best beauty remedies. If you have a good sense of humor and a good approach to life, that''s beautiful.', 18940, 0), (430362, 'Everything is funny, as long as it''s happening to somebody else.', 1122, 0), (430363, 'I love a man with a great sense of humor and who is intelligent - a man who has a great smile. He has to make me laugh. I like a man who is very ambitious and driven and who has a good heart and makes me feel safe. I like a man who is very strong and independent and confident - that is very sexy - but at the same time, he''s very kind to people.', 25639, 0), (430364, 'Be strong, believe in freedom and in God, love yourself, understand your sexuality, have a sense of humor, masturbate, don''t judge people by their religion, color or sexual habits, love life and your family.', 67561, 0), (430365, 'Laughter is an instant vacation.', 3598, 0), (430366, 'Comedy is simply a funny way of being serious.', 2206, 0), (430367, 'From there to here, and here to there, funny things are everywhere.', 3, 0), (430368, 'Everywhere is within walking distance if you have the time.', 922, 0), (430369, 'Laughter is the closest distance between two people.', 2249, 0), (430370, 'Celebrate your successes. Find some humor in your failures.', 34844, 0), (430371, 'Kindness and a generous spirit go a long way. And a sense of humor. It''s like medicine - very healing.', 68372, 0), (430372, 'My childhood, adolescence and high school days are unusually important. If there has ever been a time that I developed a uniqueness and sense of humor and the ability to organize, it was then. In those early days, I developed the skills that gave me a certain degree of success in American politics.', 45226, 0), (430373, 'My life is part humor, part roses, part thorns.', 68373, 0), (430374, 'Our brand of democracy is hard. But I can promise that a year from now, when I no longer hold this office, I''ll be right there with you as a citizen - inspired by those voices of fairness and vision, of grit and good humor and kindness that have helped America travel so far.', 1693, 0), (430375, 'I believe that singing is the key to long life, a good figure, a stable temperament, increased intelligence, new friends, super self-confidence, heightened sexual attractiveness, and a better sense of humor.', 18504, 0), (430376, 'I realize that humor isn''t for everyone. It''s only for people who want to have fun, enjoy life, and feel alive.', 21306, 0), (430377, 'Try to find someone with a sense of humor. That''s an important thing to have because when you get into an argument, one of the best ways to diffuse it is to be funny. You don''t want to hide away from a point, because some points are serious, but you''d rather have a discussion that was a discussion, rather than an argument.', 1451, 0), (430378, 'Honestly, I like someone who is really grounded, super sweet, honest. I need them to have a sense of humor. I need them to laugh at what''s funny, I need them to get jokes and be funny and be witty and sarcastic.', 68374, 0), (430379, 'I think the sexiest thing about a woman is confidence, but confidence in a humble way, not in an arrogant way. Sense of humor is definitely important. And sunglasses always hide a multitude of sins. Sunglasses and a great pair of heels can turn most outfits around.', 67831, 0), (430380, 'In the household in which I was raised, the themes were pretty simple. ''Work hard. Don''t quit. Be appreciative, be thankful, be grateful, be respectful. Also, never whine, never complain. And always, for crying out loud, keep a sense of humor.''', 68375, 0), (430381, 'It''s your outlook on life that counts. If you take yourself lightly and don''t take yourself too seriously, pretty soon you can find the humor in our everyday lives. And sometimes it can be a lifesaver.', 1377, 0), (430382, 'If we went by the world''s definition of who I''m supposed to be because I look weird... ''Well, surely, this guy can''t have a productive life, surely, he doesn''t have a sense of humor. Surely, he can''t love life.'' We stereotype people in this world. And so... if the world thinks you''re not good enough, it''s a lie, you know. Get a second opinion.', 1832, 0), (430383, 'If you''re feeling blue, lock yourself in a room, stand in front of a mirror, and dance - and laugh at yourself and be sexy. Dance the silliest and ugliest you''ve ever danced. Make fun of yourself and try to recover your sense of humor.', 68376, 0), (430384, 'You can turn painful situations around through laughter. If you can find humor in anything, even poverty, you can survive it.', 2059, 0), (430385, 'Transparency, honesty, kindness, good stewardship, even humor, work in businesses at all times.', 68377, 0), (430386, 'Most comedy is based on getting a laugh at somebody else''s expense. And I find that that''s just a form of bullying in a major way. So I want to be an example that you can be funny and be kind, and make people laugh without hurting somebody else''s feelings.', 1217, 0), (430387, 'I do find the sibling connection endlessly fascinating, as I do all family dynamics. I like how siblings seem to create their own parentless mini-civilization within a family, one that has its own laws, myths, language, humor, its own loyalties and treacheries.', 255, 0), (430388, 'It''s always funny until someone gets hurt. Then it''s just hilarious.', 544, 0), (430389, 'People with a sense of humor tend to be less egocentric and more realistic in their view of the world and more humble in moments of success and less defeated in times of travail.', 51805, 0), (430390, 'The more I live, the more I think that humor is the saving sense.', 68378, 0), (430391, 'What a newspaper needs in its news, in its headlines, and on its editorial page is terseness, humor, descriptive power, satire, originality, good literary style, clever condensation, and accuracy, accuracy, accuracy!', 45228, 0), (430392, 'I could not tread these perilous paths in safety, if I did not keep a saving sense of humor.', 20802, 0), (430393, 'A person without a sense of humor is like a wagon without springs. It''s jolted by every pebble on the road.', 2175, 0), (430394, 'A little perspective, like a little humor, goes a long way.', 46215, 0), (430395, 'My legacy would be that you don''t have to give up anything. You can be chic but have a sense of humor, you can be sexy but comfortable, you can be timeless but fresh.', 68379, 0), (430396, 'Congratulations, you have a sense of humor. And to those who didn''t: Go stick your head in the mud.', 16709, 0), (430397, 'I''m not funny. What I am is brave.', 1814, 0), (430398, 'A joke''s a very serious thing.', 20545, 0), (430399, 'Humor can help you cope with the unbearable so that you can stay on the bright side of things until the bright side actually comes along.', 46215, 0), (430400, 'My favorite kind of humor is basically, if it was happening to you, it wouldn''t be funny, but to observe it, it''s hilarious.', 67895, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (430401, 'Humor comes from self-confidence.', 138, 0), (430402, 'Gamer humor ranges all over the place. What it comes down to is taking a lot of what we see in gaming and we''re familiar with in gaming and being like, ''OK, hold on, let''s re-examine this for a second. Isn''t this funny? Isn''t this strange? Isn''t this a little bit ridiculous?'' That''s where it is.', 68380, 0), (430403, 'The humor section is the last place an author wants to be. They put your stuff next to collections of Cathy cartoons.', 2192, 0), (430404, 'If you can get humor and seriousness at the same time, you''ve created a special little thing, and that''s what I''m looking for, because if you get pompous, you lose everything.', 1017, 0), (430405, 'Humour is the weapon of unarmed people: it helps people who are oppressed to smile at the situation that pains them.', 54731, 0), (430406, 'I like beautiful writing, pain, unexpected humor, and the message that, at the last second, people are going to be kind to each other. It almost doesn''t matter what the genre is.', 68381, 0), (430407, 'Humor is everywhere in that there''s irony in just about anything a human does.', 13455, 0), (430408, 'Bad humor is an evasion of reality good humor is an acceptance of it. ', 9186, 0), (430409, 'I have seen what a laugh can do. It can transform almost unbearable tears into something bearable, even hopeful.', 13132, 0), (430410, 'Good humor is the health of the soul, sadness is its poison.', 68382, 0), (430411, 'The problem with having a sense of humor is often that people you use it on aren''t in a very good mood.', 2081, 0), (430412, 'A sense of humor is a major defense against minor troubles.', 1932, 0), (430413, 'I have never believed much in luck, and my sense of humor has tended to walk on the dark side.', 126, 0), (430414, 'I want someone who can keep me on my toes, has a good sense of humor and a good heart.', 67099, 0), (430415, 'The ultimate storyteller is Shakespeare, who was able to get the ''groundlings'' to laugh at his bawdy humor and storylines but could still be studied by scholars to this day for the complexity of his language, meter, and symbolism. That''s the real guy.', 68269, 0), (430416, 'The thing that I fear discriminating against is humor and truth.', 78, 0), (430417, 'I wasn''t shy, but I was really hyper. Nobody got my sense of humor. I was a black skater kid.', 19593, 0), (430418, 'Analyzing humor is like dissecting a frog. Few people are interested and the frog dies of it.', 994, 0), (430419, 'Good planning is important. I''ve also regarded a sense of humor as one of the most important things on a big expedition. When you''re in a difficult or dangerous situation, or when you''re depressed about the chances of success, someone who can make you laugh eases the tension.', 12199, 0), (430420, 'Nothing like a little judicious levity.', 449, 0), (430421, 'Humor can alter any situation and help us cope at the very instant we are laughing.', 46215, 0), (430422, 'As a person, he was wonderful. He really was a great person. He was full of life. He had a great sense of humor. Very talented, of course, but very caring to his parents. There was a very endearing quality about Elvis.', 65005, 0), (430423, 'One of the things that binds us as a family is a shared sense of humor.', 68383, 0), (430424, 'Confidence is at the root of so many attractive qualities, a sense of humor, a sense of style, a willingness to be who you are no matter what anyone else might think or say and it''s true, I do have a certain fondness for women that have dark hair.', 38634, 0), (430425, 'Our subconscious minds have no sense of humor, play no jokes and cannot tell the difference between reality and an imagined thought or image. What we continually think about eventually will manifest in our lives.', 10101, 0), (430426, 'You can find heroism everyday, like guys working terrible jobs because they''ve got to support their families. Or as far as humor, the things I see on the job, on the street, are far funnier than anything you''ll ever see on TV.', 1034, 0), (430427, 'We get to live in a time that we get to use social media as a tool. It''s not just a face on a piece of paper, and that''s what makes you someone''s favorite model. We can have a very similar sense of humor as someone, and that''s why we''re their favorite model, or our personal style, off the runway, is why we''re their favorite.', 60670, 0), (430428, 'Humor does not rescue us from unhappiness, but enables us to move back from it a little.', 12469, 0), (430429, 'Well, the most terrible fear that anybody should have is not war, is not a disease, not cancer or heart problems or food poisoning - it''s a man or a woman without a sense of humor.', 60426, 0), (430430, 'We''re all screwed up. And the way Christians mess things up is we act like we''ve got it going on. And if we would just stay in that place of, ''Hey, we''re all screwed up and but for the grace of God, none of us have a shot here.'' We need to have a sense of humor about it; that''s kind of the way I''ve always faced my comedy.', 1491, 0), (430431, 'I met Woz when I was 13, at a friend''s garage. He was about 18. He was, like, the first person I met who knew more electronics than I did at that point. We became good friends, because we shared an interest in computers and we had a sense of humor. We pulled all kinds of pranks together.', 1064, 0), (430432, 'I am attracted to intelligence, a witty sense of humor, an adventurous outlook on life and spiritual awareness about one''s self and the world.', 68384, 0), (430433, 'Think about scary movies: There''s a fine line between horror and humor.', 68385, 0), (430434, 'Imagination was given to man to compensate him for what he is not a sense of humor to console him for what he is. ', 1035, 0), (430435, 'I can imagine no more comfortable frame of mind for the conduct of life than a humorous resignation.', 235, 0), (430436, 'Humor is one of the best ingredients of survival.', 5358, 0), (430437, 'Humor has become so cliche and boring that nothing''s funny anymore unless it involves something totally disgusting that offends somebody or makes them feel really uncomfortable.', 68386, 0), (430438, 'I should say, one of the things about being a widow or a widower, you really, really need a sense of humor, because everything''s going to fall apart.', 852, 0), (430439, 'Humor is the ability to see three sides to one coin.', 62566, 0), (430440, 'Imagination was given to man to compensate him for what he isn''t. A sense of humor was provided to console him for what he is.', 1081, 0), (430441, 'A sense of humor... is needed armor. Joy in one''s heart and some laughter on one''s lips is a sign that the person down deep has a pretty good grasp of life.', 64069, 0), (430442, 'Humor is the affectionate communication of insight.', 1898, 0), (430443, 'Everything human is pathetic. The secret source of humor itself is not joy but sorrow. There is no humor in heaven.', 286, 0), (430444, 'The secret source of humor is not joy but sorrow there is no humor in Heaven. ', 286, 0), (430445, 'The duty of comedy is to correct men by amusing them.', 1695, 0), (430446, 'Humor is the most engaging cowardice.', 35, 0), (430447, 'A well-developed sense of humor is the pole that adds balance to your steps as you walk the tightrope of life.', 1820, 0), (430448, 'I think being funny is not anyone''s first choice.', 281, 0), (430449, 'Humor has bailed me out of more tight situations than I can think of. If you go with your instincts and keep your humor, creativity follows. With luck, success comes, too.', 1429, 0), (430450, 'Everybody I know who is funny, it''s in them. You can teach timing, or some people are able to tell a joke, though I don''t like to tell jokes. But I think you have to be born with a sense of humor and a sense of timing.', 51091, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (430451, 'People who know me, they know I have a sense of humor, I''m a bit of a joker, a bit of a clown really, and I would love someone to exploit that side of me and send me a romantic comedy.', 3625, 0), (430452, 'I am a candid interview and I have a dark and dry sense of humor - a very Canadian sense of humor and I am only learning now stupidly that you can''t read tongue. When I say something funny in a newspaper and I meant it to be funny, it doesn''t read that way.', 68387, 0), (430453, 'You have to have a sense of humor about life to get through it.', 68388, 0), (430454, 'There''s a certain type of character that you can''t help but come in contact with growing up and living in Brooklyn and Long Island. A certain mixture of moxie, heart, and a wise guy sense of humor.', 19773, 0), (430455, 'Absurdity is what I like most in life, and there''s humor in struggling in ignorance. If you saw a man repeatedly running into a wall until he was a bloody pulp, after a while it would make you laugh because it becomes absurd.', 18666, 0), (430456, 'If one tends to be a humorous person and you have a sense of humor the rest of your life then you can certainly lighten the load, I think, by bringing that to your trials and tribulations. It''s easy to have a sense of humor when everything is going well.', 68389, 0), (430457, 'A book without potty humor is like a banana split without hot fudge. It can still be good, I suppose, but you kinda get the feeling that something is missing.', 68390, 0), (430458, 'Basically, I think you need two things to get by in this world: a sense of humor and the ability to laugh when your ego is destroyed.', 68391, 0), (430459, 'I love dry British humor. I love to sketch in my off time. I love tequila.', 68246, 0), (430460, 'It has always surprised me how little attention philosophers have paid to humor, since it is a more significant process of mind than reason. Reason can only sort out perceptions, but the humor process is involved in changing them.', 26588, 0), (430461, 'The President has a wonderful sense of humor, which is one of the reasons it is so much fun to work for him.', 68392, 0), (430462, 'I love poking fun at myself. I have a rather mean sense of humor.', 32294, 0), (430463, 'If the blood humor is too strong and robust, calm it with balance and harmony.', 46458, 0), (430464, 'Men will confess to treason, murder, arson, false teeth, or a wig. How many of them will own up to a lack of humor?', 47554, 0), (430465, 'Humor is not a mood but a way of looking at the world. So if it is correct to say that humor was stamped out in Nazi Germany, that does not mean that people were not in good spirits, or anything of that sort, but something much deeper and more important.', 1163, 0), (430466, 'At the risk of appearing disingenuous, I don''t really think of myself as ''writing humor.'' I''m simply reporting on the world I observe, which is frequently hilarious.', 8957, 0), (430467, 'I am often the brunt of my own humor.', 1789, 0), (430468, 'I love a girl with a sense of humor. Someone who can make me laugh and that I can get along with and talk with and who is just sweet overall, inside and out.', 25636, 0), (430469, 'I like the brooding man - a brooding man with a sense of humor.', 21173, 0), (430470, 'My mom taught me the power of love. I learned to focus on the long-term big picture from my father. His sense of humor and light-hearted approach always make me smile. My husband is a pivotal anchor in my life. His influence encourages me to be independent and take risks.', 48341, 0), (430471, 'Wit and playfulness represent a desperately serious transcendence of evil. Humor is both a form of wisdom and a means of survival.', 105, 0), (430472, 'As an actor, I''m attracted to drama; as a director, it''s humor - because it''s the story of my life, and I can''t be that serious about it. Being alone is a big theme in all my movies, both as a director and as an actress.', 63992, 0), (430473, 'Comedy is difficult for an actor. But I think I have a good sense of humor and manage to make people laugh and make them happy.', 68393, 0), (430474, 'Professional comedians, surprisingly, have a lack of humor. They''re insensitive to the insanity of our times.', 17490, 0), (430475, 'You can defeat fear through humor, through pain, through honesty, bravery, intuition, and through love in the truest sense.', 21170, 0), (430476, 'I''ve got a sense of humor. I''m a funny guy.', 68394, 0), (430477, 'I''m a sarcastic person, and people don''t get my humor sometimes.', 68395, 0), (430478, 'I''ve dated girls that aren''t, this is gonna sound so horrible, that aren''t super smart, but they still are super confident, and that''s more what I''ve been attracted to is the confidence and the sense of humor.', 68396, 0), (430479, 'Humor and laughter - not necessarily derogatory derision - are my pet tools. This may come from my general philosophy of never taking the world too seriously - for fear of dying of boredom.', 1473, 0), (430480, 'There''s something very authentic about humor, when you think about it. Anybody can pretend to be serious. But you can''t pretend to be funny.', 8651, 0), (430481, 'Ad agencies do all kinds of market research that ask people what they think they want, and instead, you should be creating things that you want. If you do something and you get it, the rest of the world will get it, too. Trust your own instincts, your own intellect, and your own sense of humor.', 21312, 0), (430482, 'I''m an off-the-charts introvert. To me, being around groups of strangers is exhausting. I''ve had to sort of train myself to think about two tactics: finding common ground and invoking humor.', 68397, 0), (430483, 'Humor is the oxygen of children''s literature. There''s a lot of competition for children''s time, but even kids who hate to read want to read a funny book.', 45694, 0), (430484, 'What I wrote all the time when I was a kid - I don''t want to call it ''poetry,'' because it wasn''t poetry. I was not that kind of a writer. I was a rhymer. I was a fan of Dorothy Parker''s, so maybe I wrote poetry to that extent, but my main focus was the humor of it, and word construction, and the slant. Your words, it''s a very powerful experience.', 1288, 0), (430485, 'Humor is always based on a modicum of truth. Have you ever heard a joke about a father-in-law?', 22689, 0), (430486, 'Humor, humility, and, of course, honesty, all are qualities that work in public and cultural diplomacy.', 66928, 0), (430487, 'In truth, politeness is artificial good humor, it covers the natural want of it, and ends by rendering habitual a substitute nearly equivalent to the real virtue.', 1207, 0), (430488, 'This is a feminist bookstore. There is no humor section.', 68398, 0), (430489, 'Those years on the golf course as a caddie, boy, those people were something. They were vulgar, some were alcoholics, racist, they were very difficult people to deal with. A lot of them didn''t have a sense of humor.', 10201, 0), (430490, 'Humor must not professedly teach and it must not professedly preach, but it must do both if it would live forever.', 286, 0), (430491, 'I used to watch ''The Waltons'' and sob because my family was nothing like that. We had a cruel sense of humor in my family.', 6225, 0), (430492, 'I just try to write what I think would really happen, and with grief and tragedy, there are these naturally occurring moments of levity and humor and absurdity. I think that''s what life is really like. Sadness gets interrupted, and happiness gets interrupted.', 436, 0), (430493, 'Humor is a powerful tool, and some of these politicians are so far out and easy to lampoon. They just provide such delicious opportunity.', 45192, 0), (430494, 'Humor in a relationship is so important. Many women will say that. Some say, ''If they can make you laugh, it''s the sexiest thing on earth.''', 18136, 0), (430495, 'My view of life is colored by humor and looking at the best in any situation.', 1856, 0), (430496, 'Well, I mean, if a joke or humor is bawdy, it''s got to be funny enough to warrant it. You can''t just have it bawdy or dirty just for the sake of being that - it''s got to be funny.', 1377, 0), (430497, 'I don''t think I would describe my sense of humor. Doesn''t sound like the kind of thing I''d do.', 10856, 0), (430498, 'Humor is very healing.', 12780, 0), (430499, 'In rough times, pathfinders rely on work, friends, humor and prayer. They develop a support network.', 30206, 0), (430500, 'If I didn''t try to eavesdrop on every bus ride I take or look for the humor when I go for a walk, I would just be depressed all the time.', 9768, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (430501, 'The nation that complacently and fearfully allows its artists and writers to become suspected rather than respected is no longer regarded as a nation possessed with humor or depth.', 1843, 0), (430502, 'Newspaper people, once celebrated as founts of ribald humor and uncouth fun, have of late lost all their gaiety, and small wonder.', 9597, 0), (430503, 'One of my pet peeves is that sometimes the talents of my band get overlooked because, and it was the same problem that Frank Zappa had, with a lot of groups that use humor, people don''t realize there''s a lot of craft behind the comedy.', 27702, 0), (430504, 'After spending 460 days as a hostage, I did emerge a fundamentally changed person. But I think, like everyone does as they grow older and probably wiser, I can look back at my earlier life - my history, my mistakes, the joy I felt as a young woman traveling the world - with some objectivity and even some humor.', 16246, 0), (430505, 'Who I was was not acceptable to black L.A. youth: the way I spoke and my sense of humor. Everybody else had relaxers and pressed hair. I wore my hair in an Afro puff. Nappy. The way I dressed. It was all about name brands at the time in L.A. I had no idea. All those things, I failed miserably at.', 68399, 0), (430506, 'Humor helps ease the tension of race and the differences in society. If there wasn''t comedy I don''t know if Obama could have ever become president.', 68400, 0), (430507, 'Advertisers also know that humor can help bond us to their product.', 46215, 0), (430508, 'Today''s business and health care climate may not be pleasant. Cutbacks, pay cuts and layoffs do not make anyone''s job easy. But that does not mean that the humor need stop.', 46215, 0), (430509, 'They say you don''t want to meet your heroes, but those two guys, you do want to meet them, because they do not disappoint. Walken has this amazing sense of humor, and Pacino is like just a sweetheart of a guy.', 67895, 0), (430510, 'I think I''m too cynical for L.A. My sense of humor doesn''t go down well here, which probably affects my love life. I need to have a laugh track following me around so people know I''m trying to be funny.', 67169, 0), (430511, 'I''m a Larry David fan, right? And it seems to me that Jewish history from the Talmud on has been a self-deprecating, self-critical kind of humor.', 68401, 0), (430512, 'Humor, for me, is really a gate of departure. It''s a way of enticing a reader into a poem so that less funny things can take place later. It really is not an end in itself, but a means to an end.', 8651, 0), (430513, 'I hate to say it but I hate black humor. I feel like a Klan member saying it, but it''s just not funny.', 68399, 0), (430514, 'People of humor are always in some degree people of genius.', 1910, 0), (430515, 'It is quite true, as some poets said, that the God who created man must have had a sinister sense of humor, creating him a reasonable being, yet forcing him to take this ridiculous posture, and driving him with blind craving for this ridiculous performance.', 178, 0), (430516, 'I think kids want the same thing from a book that adults want - a fast-paced story, characters worth caring about, humor, surprises, and mystery. A good book always keeps you asking questions, and makes you keep turning pages so you can find out the answers.', 80, 0), (430517, 'Denzel Washington has a great sense of humor. He did all those ''Nutty Professor'' movies.', 12824, 0), (430518, 'Humor is an antidote to all ills.', 5890, 0), (430519, 'I don''t think it''s possible to have a sense of tragedy without having a sense of humor.', 1188, 0), (430520, 'While many of us never knew Ronald Reagan personally, we felt close to him because we shared his lighthearted sense of humor, admired his uncommon virtue, and were moved by his remarkable wisdom.', 68402, 0), (430521, 'Expand the definition of ''reading'' to include non-fiction, humor, graphic novels, magazines, action adventure, and, yes, even websites. It''s the pleasure of reading that counts; the focus will naturally broaden. A boy won''t read shark books forever.', 2214, 0), (430522, 'Humor is just another defense against the universe.', 2237, 0), (430523, 'Poor David Hume is dying fast, but with more real cheerfulness and good humor and with more real resignation to the necessary course of things, than any whining Christian ever dyed with pretended resignation to the will of God.', 2485, 0), (430524, 'Laughter, and the broader category of humor, are key elements in helping us go on with our life after a loss.', 46215, 0), (430525, 'Humor is by far the most significant activity of the human brain.', 26588, 0), (430526, 'The first ingredient in conversation is truth, the next good sense, the third good humor, and the fourth wit.', 19164, 0), (430527, 'My type of humor is me not caring whether people know what I''m talking about or not.', 13090, 0), (430528, 'There are two insults no human being will endure: that he has no sense of humor, and that he has never known trouble.', 4033, 0), (430529, 'Get well cards have become so humorous that if you don''t get sick you''re missing half the fun.', 40017, 0), (430530, 'It''s a funny old world.', 1945, 0), (430531, 'I think the scariest person in the world is the person with no sense of humor.', 1856, 0), (430532, 'Men are happy to be laughed at for their humor, but not for their folly.', 995, 0), (430533, 'A good actor is someone who knows how to take the part and make it real and make it honest and be effective in it. If it''s in a funny movie and, as long as they are cast in an appropriate way, humor will come from it.', 68403, 0), (430534, 'You find out in life that people really like you funny. So what do you give ''em? Humor. And then if you show them the other side, they don''t like you as much. I find, too, that I can hide behind the idiot''s mask being funny, and you never see the sorrow or the pain.', 67040, 0), (430535, 'We can''t understand when we''re pregnant, or when our siblings are expecting, how profound it is to have a shared history with a younger generation: blood, genes, humor. It means we were actually here, on Earth, for a time - like the Egyptians with their pyramids, only with children.', 457, 0), (430536, 'Humor and seriousness are not in opposition to each other.', 11414, 0), (430537, 'Among my friends, I''m not a little Boy Scout, and they love my humor, thank God.', 53024, 0), (430538, 'All my humor is based on destruction and despair. If the whole world were tranquil, without disease and violence, I''d be standing in the bread line - right in back of J. Edgar Hoover.', 2212, 0), (430539, 'There are men so philosophical that they can see humor in their own toothaches. But there has never lived a man so philosophical that he could see the toothache in his own humor.', 411, 0), (430540, 'I''m actually a perpetual 13-year-old. I''ve never advanced beyond 13. Every day, tomorrow is my 14th birthday. That''s my kind of humor.', 25037, 0), (430541, 'My wife has a good sense of humor, and instead of calling me psychic with my novels, she simply refers to me as being ''psycho.'' That''s because multiple things in my books have come true.', 17502, 0), (430542, 'Humor is a serious thing. I like to think of it as one of our greatest earliest natural resources, which must be preserved at all cost.', 1843, 0), (430543, 'Any man who has had the job I''ve had and didn''t have a sense of humor wouldn''t still be here.', 16121, 0), (430544, 'Always have a sense of humor about life - you''ll need it - but always be courteous to boot.', 68404, 0), (430545, 'With any character I play, I gravitate to the juxtaposition and humor.', 68405, 0), (430546, 'People ask if I feel pigeon-holed by always doing the same kind of humorous role. But my tool has always been humor because it''s the most entertaining way to put any ideology across, and it''s fun, and it''s positive, and it''s a healer. Laughter is God''s gift. I feel privileged to be able to do it.', 1245, 0), (430547, 'Negative humor is forgotten immediately. It''s the stuff that makes us feel better about our lives that lives long. Much more satisfying. Enter children''s books.', 13948, 0), (430548, 'Humor can be one of our best survival tools.', 46215, 0), (430549, 'I believe that economists put decimal points in their forecasts to show they have a sense of humor.', 63944, 0), (430550, 'Okay, sense of humor: plus one. Being able to laugh at yourself: plus one. Being able to laugh at other people without being mean: plus one. Vanity: minus one.', 67905, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (430551, 'Cynicism is humor in ill health.', 3173, 0), (430552, 'When humor works, it works because it''s clarifying what people already feel. It has to come from someplace real.', 1219, 0), (430553, 'I like George Carlin''s jokes. I like his humor. He''s one of my heroes, and I like what he did with talking about everyday things.', 922, 0), (430554, 'When people are in the midst of really heavy stuff and still have a sense of humor, I admire that.', 68406, 0), (430555, 'There is nothing like the way people feel after they''ve seen ''The Intouchables.'' They feel amazing. The word of mouth on this film is incredible. It''s intelligent-feeling good. You''re not insulted by the low-browness or stupidity of some of the humor. It''s so smart and terrific.', 68012, 0), (430556, 'Anybody with a sense of humor is going to put on my album and laugh from beginning to end.', 392, 0), (430557, 'Using no control and using humor will build a relationship and make a dent to where the client puts the counselor in their quality world and then begins to relate and seek out the counselor. Effective therapy begins with the acceptance of the therapist into the client''s quality world.', 11428, 0), (430558, 'A sense of humor is good for you. Have you ever heard of a laughing hyena with heart burn?', 13132, 0), (430559, 'I have a fine sense of the ridiculous, but no sense of humor.', 3231, 0), (430560, 'The satirist shoots to kill while the humorist brings his prey back alive and eventually releases him again for another chance.', 2274, 0), (430561, 'Great men are rarely isolated mountain peaks they are the summits of ranges. ', 62370, 0), (430562, 'Honest good humor is the oil and wine of a merry meeting, and there is no jovial companionship equal to that where the jokes are rather small and laughter abundant.', 944, 0), (430563, 'If you could choose one characteristic that would get you through life, choose a sense of humor.', 68407, 0), (430564, 'A sense of humor is the ability to understand a joke - and that the joke is oneself.', 8863, 0), (430565, 'Total absence of humor renders life impossible.', 68408, 0), (430566, 'A lot of my humor does come from anger. It''s like, you''re not gonna pull one over on me - which is pretty much my motto anyways.', 68409, 0), (430567, 'Humor can be an incredible, lacerating and effective weapon.', 2257, 0), (430568, 'Wit is a weapon. Jokes are a masculine way of inflicting superiority. But humor is the pursuit of a gentle grin, usually in solitude.', 43825, 0), (430569, 'In my opinion, I think sarcasm and humor in a song, without turning it into a novelty song, is really charming.', 21687, 0), (430570, 'Sometimes it takes ten seconds to see some humor in your dilemmas, sometimes ten years.', 46215, 0), (430571, 'Throughout history, great leaders have known the power of humor.', 46215, 0), (430572, 'If this humor be the safety of our race, then it is due largely to the infusion into the American people of the Irish brain.', 9728, 0), (430573, 'I wore goofy hats to school and did musical theater. Most people thought I was a dork. But if you have a sense of humor about it, no one can bring you down.', 68410, 0), (430574, 'We are really living the American dream, to be a successful brand in the States and in Europe and to steep ourselves in our heritage. But we do it with a sense of humor. We don''t take ourselves too seriously in fashion.', 66781, 0), (430575, 'Everybody''s got a different sense of humor. It''s just different styles.', 36389, 0), (430576, 'I think Canadian humor is a little less broad than American humor.', 24547, 0), (430577, 'I don''t need someone with a hot body. He can be fat or overweight and have a belly. It''s very much about style and substance and humor, interest, curiosity and really being smart.', 68411, 0), (430578, 'My parents armed me with an amazing sense of humor, and it''s what you need when, well, it''s what anyone needs in this world.', 67118, 0), (430579, 'The reason why you know more funny dudes than funny chicks is that dudes are funnier than chicks. If my daughter has a mediocre sense of humor, I''m just gonna tell her, ''Be a staff writer for a sitcom. Because they''ll have to hire you, they can''t really fire you, and you don''t have to produce that much. It''ll be awesome.''', 16775, 0), (430580, 'I was a product of a divorced family and I used humor as a weapon to combat sadness. I used comedy to make my mother laugh in light of the darkness that she faced, and to me it became a very powerful tool at a very young age, at six. I saw how therapeutic it could be.', 68412, 0), (430581, 'Michael Pollan is a champion. In all ways. A man of great integrity, humor, and common sense and kindness.', 21173, 0), (430582, 'I couldn''t really take a girl from Berlin to live in Leeds. I love it here. I miss the Yorkshire sense of humor and things like bitter and Yorkshire puddings, but I can still get my hands on salt ''n'' vinegar crisps.', 68413, 0), (430583, 'I think it''s important to find humor anywhere you can. In real life, with the darkest, scariest, most intense moments, if you can find something funny, that''s good.', 68414, 0), (430584, 'My humor is channeling everything through my brain. For example, when I talk about something, it''s how Richard Lewis feels about it. I''m a storyteller. I do a lot of free association.', 68415, 0), (430585, 'I like art with a sense of humor. I don''t have a huge art education to understand everything. I don''t think that means that art has to be watered down to the lowest common denominator, though. I don''t think you have to go to college to be able appreciate great art, but I like art that doesn''t take itself too seriously.', 24982, 0), (430586, 'I used to be neurotic. I didn''t like myself very much. But somewhere in my mid-40s, my neuroses stopped seeming so important. I developed a sense of humor.', 22243, 0), (430587, 'If you look at terrorists, they really have no sense of humor.', 11414, 0), (430588, 'Humor is probably the most significant characteristics of the human mind. Far more significant than reason. In fact, reason is actually a very cheap commodity.', 26588, 0), (430589, 'Humor has to surprise us; otherwise, it isn''t funny. It''s a death knell for a writer to be labeled a humorist because then it''s not a surprise anymore.', 1205, 0), (430590, 'There is something really horrific for any human being who feels he is being consumed by other people. I''m talking about a writer''s critics, who don''t address what you''ve written, but want to probe into your existence and magnify the trivia of your life without any sense of humor, without any sense of context.', 6613, 0), (430591, 'Racial humor was about 35% of my act when I first started. But I realized that it was a crutch. What brought it home was when another comedian said to me, ''If you changed color tomorrow, you wouldn''t have any material.'' He meant it as a put-down, but I took it as a challenge.', 2059, 0), (430592, 'Ontologically, chocolate raises profoundly disturbing questions: Does not chocolate offer natural revelation of the goodness of the Creator just as chilies disclose a divine sense of humor? Is the human born with an innate longing for chocolate? Does the notion of chocolate preclude the concept of free will?', 59636, 0), (430593, 'I''m not 17 anymore. I still have some of the same sort of anger, but I have a sense of humor about it... a sense of being constructive with that anger.', 68416, 0), (430594, 'I have a really dry sense of humor. I don''t think it''s funny when people wink at the camera. That''s more of an actor thing, just committing to whatever the thing is.', 68417, 0), (430595, 'Reading ''Youth in Revolt'' might have ruined my career because suddenly I wanted to abandon all the emotional truth of something and just go out far on a literary limb with completely implausible things that relied completely on voice and humor. And what saved me is realizing that I couldn''t do that very well.', 8600, 0), (430596, 'The key to humor is often self-loathing or sarcasm. In a sense, that''s how self-loathing is made palatable.', 68418, 0), (430597, 'I do find things funny. When you see life through the eyes of someone with a good sense of humor, which my grandmother did, life is a human comedy.', 45192, 0), (430598, 'If you are a small company taking on a big company, you need to have a sense of humor.', 5248, 0), (430599, 'I come from a family of teasers myself. My grandfather was from Liverpool, and he had a dry sense of humor, and he would tease us terribly. My brother Beau was so skilled in his teasing that he could get a rise out of me by simply pointing at me.', 67519, 0), (430600, 'Justice Scalia was a lion of the law. Agree or disagree with him, all of his colleagues on the bench shared his wisdom and his humor. And like them, I miss him.', 66620, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (430601, 'My mother was very funny. My dad had a great sense of humor. My grandmother, too.', 51091, 0), (430602, 'My humor is my creativity, and my skepticism is a gift.', 68419, 0), (430603, 'When humor can be made to alternate with melancholy, one has a success, but when the same things are funny and melancholic at the same time, it''s just wonderful.', 11832, 0), (430604, 'Picking my topics is sort of a process of elimination for me. Most things don''t work for me. I like to cover science and unexpected things happening in labs. Also, theoretical research doesn''t work for my style. I need scenes and interactions. Then, humor. I''m having the most fun when I can have fun with my work.', 1554, 0), (430605, 'As fandom grew more variegated, genzines reflected a broadening of interests, carrying personal columns of humor and reflection, science articles, amateur fiction, stylish gossip, and inevitably, thoughtful pieces on the future of fandom.', 17617, 0), (430606, 'I''ve learned to start from a really sound argument, boil down the essence of what you''re trying to say, then build your humor around that, rather than starting with, ''This sounds funny,'' and going from there.', 68420, 0), (430607, 'I love people who have a good sense of humor, tell a good story, tell a good joke.', 68421, 0), (430608, 'Poop humor is fun. If you do the toilet scenes well and commit to them, they can be really, really powerful.', 68422, 0), (430609, 'I grew up on EC comic books and ''Tales From the Crypt,'' which were all loaded with humor, bad jokes, and puns. I can have that kind of fun and make these comic book movies but, at the same time, talk about things I want to talk about - whether it''s consumerism or the Bush administration or war.', 60732, 0), (430610, 'Everyone is flailing through this life without an owner''s manual, with whatever modicum of grace and good humor we can manage.', 457, 0), (430611, 'Humor works, and it''s the best way to get attention without spending a lot of money.', 67031, 0), (430612, 'I want to have fun. Life ain''t no dress rehearsal. I want to have fun. I''m a comedian; I ain''t no politician. So everything I do is with humor, with love.', 68423, 0), (430613, 'Writing a novel is one of those modern rites of passage, I think, that lead us from an innocent world of contentment, drunkenness, and good humor, to a state of chronic edginess and the perpetual scanning of bank statements.', 2312, 0), (430614, 'Every time I do a movie like ''Finding Neverland'' or ''Chocolat'' or ''Shakespeare'' in Love,'' we deal with the creative process, but there''s humor and fun along the way. I always love that kind of movie.', 68012, 0), (430615, 'We get the worrywart, the hypochondriac, the money-grubbing miser, the intractable negotiator... Some would say certain of these refer to the stereotypical, or ''stage'' Jew. But objectively speaking, the only crime in humor is an unfunny joke.', 62972, 0), (430616, 'I''ve never met a person who has more integrity than my husband. I respect that. There''s his humor and intelligence, too, and he''s really cute, all those things - but if you don''t respect your partner, you''ll get sick of him.', 67509, 0), (430617, 'I consider myself to have a decent sense of humor. What''s life without a sense of humor?', 68424, 0), (430618, 'Well, it''s a humor strip, so my first responsibility has always been to entertain the reader... But if, in addition, I can help move readers to thought and judgment about issues that concern me, so much the better.', 68425, 0), (430619, 'The waltz is a very important part of my life. It''s a very important way for me to express my positiveness, bringing humor to the world.', 68426, 0), (430620, 'Suspense is very important. Even though this is humor and they''re short stories, that theory of building suspense is still there.', 16797, 0), (430621, 'I was pretty much a child of ''Monty Python.'' I grew up loving that type of humor and even structured a lot of humor in the same fashion.', 68427, 0), (430622, 'Teasing and a sense of humor, if you can develop that in your kids, and if you can exercise it with the kids, just makes for a pleasanter atmosphere.', 10731, 0), (430623, 'I think that humor has become a principle means of communication among Americans about politics.', 10731, 0), (430624, 'I love practical jokes and humor. That there''s frankly no joke that I don''t think is funny. I love practical jokes, but I don''t like being scared.', 52321, 0), (430625, 'I have five boys in the family, and it''s constant competition, sport, humor, and practical jokes.', 52321, 0), (430626, 'I think I have always had a little humor.', 1, 0), (430627, 'You know those things that you throw the twigs into and it spits them out? That''s what I do. The branches are like life, and I throw them into my head and some of it comes out as humor.', 922, 0), (430628, 'I''ve been encouraging documentary filmmakers to use more and more humor, and they''re loath to do that because they think if it''s a documentary it has to be deadly serious - it has to be like medicine that you''re supposed to take. And I think it''s what keeps the mass audience from going to documentaries.', 17499, 0), (430629, 'In a way, a lot of my humor comes from presenting things that are dramatic or shocking and then people not having socially appropriate responses, having people denying the drama by failing to react to it, and that''s a really classic form of humor.', 30, 0), (430630, 'I think people appreciate a songwriter who shows different sides. The whole angst thing is cool, but if that''s all you''ve got, it''s just boring. Everything I write, whether it''s happy or sad, has a sense of humor to it.', 746, 0), (430631, 'Sad music, I always thought, is more beautiful than other music. But at the same time, I am in my personal life a very happy guy. I have a sense of humor. I am not the kind of depressed guy all the time brooding. No. I am very enthusiastic about things.', 60783, 0), (430632, 'My daughter doesn''t even get my humor. She''s like, ''Um, no. I don''t get it, Dad. Mmm, no, not that one, Dad.''', 44935, 0), (430633, 'The difference between me as Brian Warner or Marilyn Manson is just words. Same personality, sensibility, sense of humor, behavior. He is me.', 2519, 0), (430634, 'Humor is my default mode.', 135, 0), (430635, 'Why anybody gets my sense of humor I never know, but I do know that when they do, I keep them as close as I possibly can.', 1099, 0), (430636, 'I never write anything without humor, just because I like humor, but at the same time, it is a way for anything fantastical to become relatable.', 1099, 0), (430637, 'People often think that you have a sense of humor because you think that life is funny. Life isn''t funny at all. It''s appalling and tragic.', 4223, 0), (430638, 'Edward Norton and I have known each other awhile. I just think he''s the real deal, supremely talented and smart. He''s got a great sense of humor.', 60302, 0), (430639, 'George Carlin is brilliant with words, and Johnny Winters is very creative. It''s taking something common and drawing out the humor, being clever with words.', 2059, 0), (430640, 'Now, Richard Pryor was unique. Many misunderstood his humor. He lit up the hallway, but they didn''t understand his use of profanity. He didn''t use it just to be using it; he used it in the context of his satire.', 2059, 0), (430641, 'There is hope for the future because God has a sense of humor and we are funny to God.', 2059, 0), (430642, 'Sometimes I find I''m wearing a divided, split brain in terms of drama and humor.', 68428, 0), (430643, 'My sense of humor is a turkey, and I pull it out of the oven and baste it in reality.', 68238, 0), (430644, 'I want to show the world my humor.', 68238, 0), (430645, 'If I had to describe my sense of humor, I would say it''s contemporary wit, you know what I''m saying?', 68238, 0), (430646, 'I met Elton John at an Interview dinner, and we just sort of became friends. He''s got such a wicked sense of humor.', 67002, 0), (430647, 'Political correctness? In my humor, I never talk about politics. I was never much into all that.', 53024, 0), (430648, 'Half the battle is that people have to like you before you say one joke, one bit of humor.', 53024, 0), (430649, 'Down the road, I''ll probably have a kid or two or three. And there will probably be political events or spiritual things to comment on, and humor.', 21687, 0), (430650, 'A sense of humor keen enough to show a man his own absurdities will keep him from the commission of all sins, or nearly all, save those worth committing.', 4111, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (430651, 'I love Stephen Colbert and Jon Stewart because they''re bringing irony back into American humor, which is a delicious treat. The entire Colbert persona of being extreme right-wing when he''s not at all is highly amusing. He does it so well, but sometimes a little too well. My wife is convinced he''s completely that way.', 14227, 0), (430652, 'Bob Dole used to be really funny. Barney Frank can be kind of funny. Bob Kerrey has a good sense of humor.', 11414, 0), (430653, 'There is - I mean - I found early in life that righteous indignation is a little off-putting, and so I try to couch it with humor.', 11414, 0), (430654, 'There''s plenty of room for humor in politics, God knows, but it''s a serious business.', 11414, 0), (430655, 'You''re not going to see my sense of humor on the football field. That''s not a place for me to joke around.', 66949, 0), (430656, 'I''m a huge Muppets fan. Gigantic. I think they''re genius. I think they''re some of the best work out there and completely underrated, just because of how genius they are. I love that kind of humor. It''s so innocent but brilliant.', 67003, 0), (430657, 'I''ll speak for myself, but there''s a lot of humor to be found in sarcasm and darkness. You talk to any paramedic, they survive by developing a pretty off-kilter sense of humor.', 67437, 0), (430658, 'Wit - the salt with which the American humorist spoils his intellectual cookery by leaving it out.', 224, 0), (430659, 'Sites like Funny or Die and College Humor are great, but I''d say it''s appealing to 80% men and 20% women.', 22856, 0), (430660, 'Humor is a part of spirituality.', 22856, 0), (430661, 'I''m very confident that Nick Hornby always gets it right as a writer. He has the vernacular and passion. He is adroit and dry, and balances humor with the humanity of life.', 67399, 0), (430662, 'I defuse everything I can with it. Humor is such a great shield.', 34097, 0), (430663, 'Humor has justly been regarded as the finest perfection of poetic genius.', 3061, 0), (430664, 'True humor springs not more from the head than from the heart. It is not contempt; its essence is love. It issues not in laughter, but in still smiles, which lie far deeper.', 3061, 0), (430665, 'One seldom expects the country''s president to adequately note the passing of a rocker, but Jimmy Carter''s assessment of Elvis Presley''s appeal - ''energy, rebelliousness and good humor'' - is remarkably close to the mark.', 2253, 0), (430666, 'OK, in all seriousness, I would say I couldn''t be in a relationship without equality, generosity, integrity, spirit, kindness and humor. And awesomeness.', 883, 0), (430667, 'You know, Freud accepted his lot very stoically and very well and with a sense of humor. He aged and died gracefully, and there''s a lot to be said for that.', 2042, 0), (430668, 'My dad was very much a John Wayne kind of guy, but he was also a great guy, great sense of humor, a real dedicated dad. I don''t think he ever missed a hockey game I was in.', 17500, 0), (430669, 'I''m really happy I went to a Catholic school because a lot of the repressive tactics they use make for great senses of humor.', 17500, 0), (430670, 'Bob Hope, like Mark Twain, had a sense of humor that was uniquely American, and like Twain, we''ll likely not see another like him.', 12496, 0), (430671, 'I don''t think that because you die and move on to somewhere else that you lose your sense of humor.', 3497, 0), (430672, 'I don''t think arrested-adolescent humor will fade. Maybe the form will change, but I guarantee its replacement will still be based in immature behavior from mature figures.', 23202, 0), (430673, 'Different taste in jokes is a great strain on the affections.', 215, 0), (430674, 'A lot of people can find something to laugh at in my humor, I guess.', 1252, 0), (430675, 'The wealthy don''t have any sense of humor. It''s not like the English, where the theater is perhaps the one place where they have a sense of humor about themselves.', 12582, 0), (430676, 'I love puns. I''ve been known to turn the car around just to take advantage of a good pun situation. It really is the highest form of humor.', 28327, 0), (430677, 'I think a sense of humor will help get a girl out of a dark place.', 7842, 0), (430678, 'The overwhelming majority of Americans are possessed of two great qualities a sense of humor and a sense of proportion.', 2261, 0), (430679, 'For me, I really love ''Tim and Eric'' and ''Dr. Steve Brule'' and a lot of the Adult Swim shows, so I like strange, weird, sometimes slightly upsetting humor.', 67541, 0), (430680, 'I like a man who can be a real friend, has a good sense of humor, a good pair of shoes and a healthy gold card.', 67831, 0), (430681, 'My sense of humor lies a little closer to the middle.', 58696, 0), (430682, 'My family is pretty funny. My mother is British, so she''s got a very dry sense of humor. That''s where I got that from.', 58696, 0), (430683, 'I''m a comedian, and I definitely see the humor in a lot of things. I am also sad a lot. I cry often and easily. I think you''re supposed to feel all kinds of things.', 1217, 0), (430684, 'I''m still trying to figure out how to write about cancer and my family''s experience with it. If I had been able to write ''The Pura Principle'' back in those days, I''m positive it would have had no humor in it. Which means the story would have been false.', 560, 0), (430685, 'Since the very beginning, Emeril''s had a sense of humor about me calling him names and poking fun at him.', 6719, 0), (430686, 'Sometimes I used to think to myself, ''Have I lost a sense of humor?'' but I don''t think that I have. I think one can be as snarky and sarcastic as lots of people, but I have never found that it makes me particularly happy.', 63679, 0), (430687, 'I have a very dark sense of humor. I swear. I have a very playful relationship with Jesus.', 457, 0), (430688, 'Wit is the lowest form of humor.', 3348, 0), (430689, 'Going to AA helped me to see that there were other people who had problems that had found a way to talk about them and find relief and humor through that.', 1288, 0), (430690, 'I don''t understand how somebody wouldn''t have a sense of humor about themselves.', 18212, 0), (430691, 'Tony and I had a good on and off screen relationship, we are two very different people, but we did share a sense of humor, we now live in different parts of the world but when we find ourselves in the same place it is more or less as if there had been no years in between.', 67012, 0), (430692, 'The comic is the perception of the opposite humor is the feeling of it. ', 736, 0), (430693, 'There are certain things I learned when I first started learning about acting, to try and place the character physically and emotionally. And the way you place them emotionally is often with humor.', 54756, 0), (430694, 'I''ve met a lot of people who''ve lost their jobs and they still have a sense of humor.', 536, 0), (430695, 'I''m sure I''ve all but lost friends by maintaining that, despite their love for it, I always saw Stanley Kramer''s ''It''s a Mad, Mad, Mad, Mad World'' as more of an exercise in anti-comedy than humor.', 12902, 0), (430696, '''Guardians of the Galaxy'' is tongue-in-cheek and has a sense of humor about itself. But it''s nothing like ''Deadpool.'' ''Deadpool'' is this super-bizarre thing. The best thing about it is that it''s R-rated.', 67691, 0), (430697, 'I think that what comes through in Chicago humor is the affection. Even though you''re poking fun at someone or something, there''s still an affection for it.', 51805, 0), (430698, 'Humor''s a weapon if you want to make it one.', 51805, 0), (430699, 'I don''t know how many sacred cows there are today. I think there''s a little confusion between humor and gross passing for humor. That''s kind of regrettable.', 51805, 0), (430700, 'I think there''s a little confusion between humor and ''gross'' passing for humor. That''s kind of regrettable, because they aren''t the same thing.', 51805, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (430701, 'The schizophrenic has no sense of humor. His world is a constantly daunting, unfriendly place.', 51805, 0), (430702, 'Humor is so important to the American scene throughout history.', 51805, 0), (430703, 'What you see on stage is pretty much the way I am... a dry sense of humor.', 51805, 0), (430704, 'I think there''s something about the Irish experience - that we had to have a sense of humor or die.', 20529, 0), (430705, 'That''s what kept us going - a sense of absurdity, rather than humor.', 20529, 0), (430706, 'For some reason, I had a responsibility to my family and the people who lived around me. I felt that I had to convey their dignity - the way they dealt with adversity and poverty - and their good humor.', 20529, 0), (430707, 'Humor is the first of the gifts to perish in a foreign tongue.', 113, 0), (430708, 'I''ve got a great sense of humor, and if I''m able to say or do something in a movie that people feel like they want to repeat, that''s hugely flattering.', 2387, 0), (430709, 'I have the humor of a 9-year-old boy, and sometimes I''ve had laughing fits on-air.', 8452, 0), (430710, 'My wife, my daughters, even my grandchildren are funny. You''ve got to keep a sense of humor because anger destroys you.', 40738, 0), (430711, 'I suppose I miss the British cynicism and the humor.', 44554, 0), (430712, 'Jeffrey Zeldman had an astonishing ability to craft a seductive coolness using educated references, dry humor, and retro/organic imagery.', 68429, 0), (430713, 'I''m able to see humor in a lot of things.', 67016, 0), (430714, 'If you don''t have humor, you''re not going to make it. You''re going to be one of those people who walks around with your head about to explode.', 2138, 0), (430715, 'I can''t not put humor in a book.', 61610, 0), (430716, 'My humor is traced with dark - I''ve got dark patches all over the place.', 61610, 0), (430717, 'Sometimes the only way to deal with horrific things in life is through a dark sense of humor.', 2324, 0), (430718, 'It''s good to be able to laugh at yourself and the problems you face in life. Sense of humor can save you.', 2324, 0), (430719, 'I think it''s critical, a sense of humor. It did help me - it does help me, continuously.', 66969, 0), (430720, 'When I teach the formal curriculum, I have the chance to think about it ahead of time. I can rehearse it. I can illustrate it with self-deprecating humor and humble-sounding personal disclosure. I can try to make it comes out just right.', 4328, 0), (430721, 'I think humor is such a personal thing, and you put a microphone in somebody''s face, they''re going to say something that offends somebody.', 68248, 0), (430722, 'Anyone who knows me, and most of my fans, know that I have a sense of humor.', 66906, 0), (430723, 'It''s weird doing red carpets it''s uncomfortable. But you can have a sense of humor about it. ', 68430, 0), (430724, 'Anyone who''s married to Mariah Carey - I''m pretty sure - doesn''t have a great sense of humor. I mean, let''s be honest: she''s ridiculous. What is her game plan?', 2202, 0), (430725, 'Paul Rudd has a very specific brand of humor.', 68251, 0), (430726, '''War on Everyone,'' I think... the script was hilarious to me, but it''s very dark, dark humor. It''s super dark.', 68251, 0), (430727, 'When you finish a drama, you go, ''I can''t wait to do a comedy.'' When you finish a comedy, you go, ''I want to do a dramedy, dark humor.''', 68251, 0), (430728, 'People think I''m a very serious actor, which I am. But you know, if you don''t have a sense of humor doing what I do, you perish.', 68431, 0), (430729, 'Nobody enjoys the ''little show about nothing'' humor more than me, but that is never the way I look at it.', 2195, 0), (430730, 'I have a need to always make people laugh. I have a desperate need. I love a great sense of humor. The people I sort of surround myself with have that.', 68432, 0), (430731, 'Women respond to comfort and a sense of humor. I was always able to make them laugh, so that helps a lot.', 68432, 0), (430732, 'My father could be very witty, even if the humor was always on the darker side of irony.', 585, 0), (430733, 'I make jokes because humor is the greatest healing factor that there is.', 68433, 0), (430734, 'In Buddhism, they say attachment to anything only leads to suffering. So when we laugh, it''s our way of saying, ''I''m unattached to that.'' You''re tickled by it, it makes your lobes do something on their own. So humor is very important to me. I always take that to the stage first.', 397, 0), (430735, 'People who have any kind of illness use humor as a type of coping.', 68434, 0), (430736, 'I''m a huge fan of Steve Martin. He''s hilarious, but he has this depth to him and this way of dealing with the difficult things in life with a sense of humor that I think has helped me as an actress.', 68435, 0), (430737, 'I''m not a particularly dark individual. I have my moments, it''s true, but I do have a sense of humor.', 1001, 0), (430738, 'I was a timid little guy when I was a kid. I used humor as a defense; I became the class clown. But deep inside, I felt real vulnerable.', 17681, 0), (430739, 'And, you know, I liked writing humor. Well, I should say, I wanted to write seriously, but it kept turning funny.', 18054, 0), (430740, 'The real important things are kindness and a sense of humor. I''ve been fortunate to have dated and could have easily married women who have those qualities, and time and circumstances didn''t work out. Timing plays a big part.', 68255, 0), (430741, 'I don''t think of myself as funny - I don''t fill up a room with my humor... I would fail miserably as a stand-up comedian.', 47094, 0), (430742, 'Sometimes when I try to make jokes or have a sense of humor in interviews, it doesn''t go over very well. But Twitter made my life easier in this way that I didn''t expect. It would have taken probably 10 times as long for people to accept my voice and my sense of humor if I didn''t have Twitter.', 12145, 0), (430743, 'I''ve got a great sense of humor.', 48587, 0), (430744, 'Twitter is the place where I try to be more funny. And then I use Instagram just as my diary. I pull some jokes on there, but I think people have a better sense of humor on Twitter.', 60670, 0), (430745, 'I guess, for me, I''ve always thought that there was humor everywhere. And as a kid, I just, you know, I grew up an only child, and I - sort of nothing made me happier than to make my parents laugh. I remember I had costumes and things laying around the house that I was, you know, anything that I could do to make my parents laugh.', 58477, 0), (430746, 'Humor is very interesting to me. My films are not comedies, but there''s comedy in them from time to time, absurdities, just like in real life.', 18666, 0), (430747, 'It''s always the girl comedy and the guy comedy. It bums me out. You''d think there''d be a progression, from James L. Brooks and Nora Ephron into more subtle humor and behavior and psychology. All these interesting things people can learn about themselves by watching talented writers comment intelligently on someone else''s emotional life.', 67023, 0), (430748, 'Our records, if you have a dark sense of humor, were funny, but our records weren''t about comedy. They were about protests, fantasy, confrontation and all that.', 26404, 0), (430749, 'In high drama or high tragedy or anything, it''s not really human unless there''s some humor at the same time. And vice versa. So I guess I tend to gravitate towards projects which tread a dodgy tightrope between two things, which aren''t really one or another.', 68436, 0), (430750, 'You don''t necessarily equate me with humor!', 68437, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (430751, 'I came from a dysfunctional family - very dysfunctional. And my father used to find great humor in throwing me down the stairs.', 68438, 0), (430752, 'My sense of humor often gets me in trouble.', 68439, 0), (430753, 'I have a sense of humor, and sometimes it gets me into trouble.', 68439, 0), (430754, 'I like telling stories with a sense of humor. But humor can also distance you from the subject you''re writing about. I''m interested in using humor as a portal to something a bit more serious.', 68440, 0), (430755, 'Any band that doesn''t have a sense of humor has a little bit of a problem.', 68440, 0), (430756, 'It doesn''t take many people to have a bad sense of humor to get in trouble at a corporation.', 101, 0), (430757, 'Humor without sadness underneath it feels cheap and aggressive.', 57404, 0), (430758, 'A laugh is a surprise. And all humor is physical. I was always athletic, so that came naturally to me.', 67037, 0), (430759, 'Let''s not call physical comedy falling down and pratfalls. All humor is physical, no matter how you dish it out. It''s timing, like a dancer or an athlete would have.', 67037, 0), (430760, 'I come from a much freer kind of performance thing, where I rely on my own improv and my own sense of humor.', 67037, 0), (430761, 'I''m just very amused by five-year-old humor.', 68388, 0), (430762, '''Take Shelter'' is a tough movie because there''s no humor in it, so there''s really no way to judge how you''re doing - whether people are still with you or not.', 68441, 0), (430763, 'Impropriety is the soul of wit.', 235, 0), (430764, 'You are not angry with people when you laugh at them. Humor teaches tolerance.', 235, 0), (430765, 'One of the great things about the Internet is that you can read what everybody has to say about everything. It is fascinating to me, the critiques about humor by people who have no sense of humor.', 538, 0), (430766, 'It''s funny. People often compare me to other humor essayists. They''re usually quite nice comparisons; I will accept those gladly. But I am always sort of appalled at the idea of being lumped with other, more chick-y female writers. And the truth is probably that neither comparison is accurate.', 1436, 0), (430767, 'I think a lot of humor is about distracting yourself. Pretend you''re not trying to make it funny. Because for some reason the effort to be funny smells like sulphur in our culture.', 1436, 0), (430768, 'It''s easier to sit there and say you don''t like feminists because they don''t have a sense of humor.', 68442, 0), (430769, 'And I loved Fats Waller. I love his instrumental abilities, his vocal abilities and his sense of humor.', 67, 0), (430770, 'I think the humor, when applied in the right amount, only serves to intensify the other emotions in a given song; it highlights them, makes them stand out.', 67046, 0), (430771, 'It''s an amusing idea to some, this feminism thing - this audacious notion that women should be able to move through the world as freely, and enjoy the same inalienable rights and bodily autonomy, as men. At least, that''s the impression given when feminism and feminists are all too often the targets of lazy humor.', 9530, 0), (430772, 'My humor had changed from foolishness to making sense.', 68423, 0), (430773, 'I go out and speak to women''s groups all the time, and I say, ''Guys, you gotta laugh and find the humor in things. You gotta pass it on.''', 58173, 0), (430774, 'A sense of humor is great - it goes a long, long way in a marriage.', 2171, 0), (430775, 'A woman who knows that she doesn''t have to get all decked out to look good is sexy. A woman who can make you feel smart with her conversation skills is also sexy. I believe the sense of humor is important.', 7847, 0), (430776, 'One thing I have that the majority of other designers don''t is humor. That''s distinctly my approach, and it was distinctly Franco Moschino''s, too.', 38405, 0), (430777, 'People, I guess, generally come to see me do stand-up with a working knowledge of my broad sense of humor on ''The Daily Show''... I don''t think anyone would mistake me as an actual anchor.', 17770, 0), (430778, 'Writing is not for me. I completely lose my sense of humor when I write. I become extremely pathetic, very sensational. Images give me possibilities that I don''t have with words.', 2030, 0), (430779, 'I feel like I''ve always had a sordid sense of humor, and it''s only gotten more twisted as I''ve gotten older.', 68235, 0), (430780, 'You can''t do anything to be funny. That''s cringeworthy. If your humor comes out of a place of love every time, you don''t make the joke bigger than you. The funniest comedians are in touch with their emotional level.', 68268, 0), (430781, 'It''s great to be able to connect parents with children both emotionally and through humor. I look forward to exploring family entertainment once again and examining the specifics of our day-to-day lives against the backdrop of an extraordinary adventure.', 68269, 0), (430782, 'I can''t begin to tell you how fulfilling the perennial nature of ''Elf'' on television has been for me. It''s great to be able to connect parents with children both emotionally and through humor.', 68269, 0), (430783, 'Wit is an explosion of the compound spirit.', 68443, 0), (430784, 'Working on newspapers, you''re writing to a certain length, often very brief pieces; you tend to look for easy forms of humor - women can''t drive, things like that. That''s about the level of a lot of newspaper humor. It becomes a form of laziness.', 2476, 0), (430785, 'I think ''Country Girl'' is one song that can veer into country or hip-hop or rap. You can listen to it and enjoy the humor and the fun in it.', 66563, 0), (430786, 'I like bawdy humor. I love bawdy humor, but not dirty humor.', 1377, 0), (430787, 'Sometimes you can take those dramatic roles and maybe interject a little humor into them, and I think the reverse also works.', 68444, 0), (430788, 'When I''ve had to edit my albums, I''ll listen to it one time through, and I''ll make edits. I want to remember to set up a camera to record myself listening to my set, because I don''t even slightly crack a smile, I am just listening for technical details, and I look like somebody that has absolutely no sense of humor. I look insane.', 67056, 0), (430789, 'My paintings capture the humor, zaniness, and depth of the Batman villains as well as the Freudian motivations of Batman as an all-too-human, venerable, and funny vigilante superhero.', 68445, 0), (430790, 'I get called ''Mayor West'' a lot in airports. I''ve been very fortunate to have a fan base that keeps growing, and the work gets such a warm response and humor from people.', 68445, 0), (430791, 'I''ve hung on for a long time in this business and had some success, and I think it''s keeping an open mind and being curious and having a sense of humor about oneself that''s important.', 68445, 0), (430792, 'I do not have a sense of humor of any recognizable sort.', 10856, 0), (430793, 'I admired Stephen Daldry very much; I think he''s a brilliant director, and also, I feel close to him because he has a lot of theater behind him. He''s also a man of great imagination and a lovely sense of humor.', 68446, 0), (430794, 'Ingmar Bergman had a great sense of humor, and he had a very special, characteristic laugh that you always recognized - if he went to watch a theater show, ''Ah! He is here tonight.''', 68446, 0), (430795, 'I am a political human being. I have - that''s one of my interests. I studied political science in college. I was actually going to get my Ph.D. in poli-sci. And a lot of my material from early on in my career dealt with politics, so I''ve always considered myself as somebody who enjoys political humor. So I''m not going to stop.', 50659, 0), (430796, 'Humor is always important. There are people who help us deal with difficulty or hardship; from the concentration camps to the court jester, there was a need for humor. As long as these kinds of things exist, with repressive regimes, you need it to deal with the weight of daily life.', 50659, 0), (430797, 'You have to laugh at yourself. I do a lot of humor about all ethnicities that are at the show - Latinos, Asians, Indians... What I say is, ''We''re laughing together. I''m laughing with you, not at you.'' Never say, ''Oh, I''m better than you.''', 50659, 0), (430798, 'I think the main thing about comedy and humor is that it''s impossible and always was impossible to define.', 23139, 0), (430799, 'The people in New York - their humor is on a level that goes, uh, very deep, you know?', 56664, 0), (430800, 'I compare Stephen Sondheim with humor, because humor is unanalyzable. You can''t analyze humor. You just have to get through it.', 56664, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (430801, 'Life is never all one thing. It bounces around. Certainly, my own life has. Look at Woody Allen''s funny movies - all the humor comes out of sad stuff. Sometimes you have to laugh, no matter what life deals you.', 3159, 0), (430802, 'Love, as wonderful and horrible as it is, has at its center a kind of pitiful humor.', 3159, 0), (430803, 'I love the diversity of America. I love the plain, normal sense of humor Americans have. It is not wicked, like in some countries. And I also love how new America is.', 68447, 0), (430804, 'From sixteen to twenty, all women, kept in humor by their hopes and by their attractions, appear to be good-natured.', 24527, 0), (430805, 'Married people should not be quick to hear what is said by either when in ill humor.', 24527, 0), (430806, 'I think humor can be an effective way of getting the point across, but there are definitely times where I just write very earnestly.', 68448, 0), (430807, 'I don''t know if I realized that I was funny, but I realized how healing and important humor was in my childhood.', 12780, 0), (430808, 'There''s humor in everything. There''s gotta be humor in everything.', 274, 0), (430809, 'There is also this benefit in brag, that the speaker is unconsciously expressing his own ideal. Humor him by all means, draw it all out, and hold him to it.', 62284, 0), (430810, 'Me and Matt love to argue, but in general our sense of humor is pretty much alike.', 6876, 0), (430811, 'The thing about For Better or Worse is the only thing that made me an okay director for that is that I have a sense of humor, and it was supposed to be funny.', 68449, 0), (430812, 'I have such a respect for comedy. It''s a lot harder than doing drama, in my opinion; you have to have sort of an innate sense of humor. There are rules to comedy you can learn. But ultimately, it really does require a certain point of view on the world, and that really does appeal to me.', 68450, 0), (430813, 'Everybody in my family had a real sick, twisted sense of humor. Most of the jokes we make in our house, we would just never even dream of making anywhere else. Just sick, horrible stuff. That wasn''t anything new to college.', 12824, 0), (430814, 'Having a sense of humor has served me more than it has hurt me - just in the sense that it has allowed me to keep my sanity.', 68451, 0), (430815, 'There''s a film I did years ago, ''Love Serenade,'' that I still really love. It''s such an oddball sense of humor. It was a really special film for me when I did it.', 68452, 0), (430816, 'What''s great about the geek spirit is that life never seems to stop us, and they never seem to kill our enthusiasm, our optimism and our hunger to experience the world. We keep our sense of humor, we protect our dignity, we talk to our friends about the experience and then we start again fresh the very next day.', 17478, 0), (430817, 'Women''s humor seems to be a little more supportive. It''s just kind of trying to make the other one laugh through funny voices and kind of talking about other people. I respond to that. I feel less like I''m going to get beat up in a room full of women than I do in a room full of guys.', 17478, 0), (430818, 'In Australia, even the darkest subject matter has a little pinch of humor. A little sweet to make the sour go down.', 68453, 0), (430819, 'I''m sure there are people who survive tragedy without humor, but I''ve never met any of them. Nor would I be particularly interested in writing about them if I did meet them.', 21992, 0), (430820, 'I do talk about celebrity relationships like Kim Kardashian''s. I like to find the humor in love.', 68280, 0), (430821, 'I like to be able to feel as many parts of myself while watching a movie at one time. I think that''s what ''Super'' is - it''s funny, but it''s also sad. It''s very touching in certain ways, and it''s also got a very dark sense of humor. So it''s allowed to go anywhere.', 68454, 0), (430822, 'There are different kinds of humor, some is sarcastic, some introspective. Introspective fit my personality better.', 2210, 0), (430823, 'Kindness is really important to me in finding my own prince - so are patience and a sense of humor. Without those qualities he''s no Prince Charming!', 67062, 0), (430824, 'I personally have dealt with any adversity in my life with humor. That''s why I told America to ''Read my hips!'' on ''Dancing With the Stars'' or was happy to play along with Jason Alexander and Jerry Seinfeld in the great restaurant scene on ''Seinfeld.''', 67063, 0), (430825, 'Humor comes in all forms, and everyone has their cup of tea about what makes them laugh. But the day we censor humor is a sad one for sure.', 67063, 0), (430826, 'I need a woman to have a quirky sense of humor. There''s a bunch of jokes I use, and if she doesn''t get them, she''s probably not for me.', 68455, 0), (430827, 'I was intentionally curbing the impulse to be funny and hiding the ability. I wrote any number of very serious attempts at poems, short stories, novels - horrible. At a certain point, I recognized that it was fun to write dialogue that had a degree of lightness and humor.', 13083, 0), (430828, 'I use a lot of humor, and I follow the saying that if you want to tell people the truth, you better make them laugh first; otherwise, they will shoot you.', 68456, 0), (430829, 'Mixing humor and politics is something that works.', 33509, 0), (430830, 'I read the script and decide if a particular character looks fun to play. I look for complexity and a sense of humor. Those are crucial, real things to life.', 19773, 0), (430831, 'I just like playing interesting, complex, complicated characters. I like films that also have an element of humor.', 19773, 0), (430832, 'You either have chemistry or you don''t, but a lot of what attracts me is a guy''s mind and humor and talent. I need to get to know all those things before I fall for someone.', 68457, 0), (430833, 'The only way I could get comfortable around people was to make them laugh. I was an obedient girl, and humor was my one form of rebellion. I used comedy to deflect. Like, ''Hey, check out my zit!'' - you know, making fun of yourself before someone else has a chance to.', 1219, 0), (430834, 'I loved Peter Sellers. I thought he was the perfect mix of physical comedy with out-of-the-box humor. I loved his tone I loved his physicality I loved everything about what he was doing as a comedic actor. ', 67383, 0), (430835, 'I love British humor. It''s just so - surreal.', 9972, 0), (430836, 'When I was young, my favorite picture book was ''Fletcher and Zenobia,'' written by Edward Gorey and illustrated by Victoria Chess. It''s long out of print now, but its mix of macabre humor and 1960s psychedelia made it a perfect children''s book for the times.', 80, 0), (430837, 'I like guys with a sense of humor who smile a lot and are kind.', 68458, 0), (430838, 'As far as how I approach the humor, I think the best comedy is going to happen when I''m myself and act organically to a news item or situation.', 68458, 0), (430839, 'All my relatives and friends have been pretty aware of my brand of humor for a while, so none of them have been shocked.', 68458, 0), (430840, 'Humor can bring people under the tent. And a good joke can deflect some of the intensity surrounding a serious subject.', 68406, 0), (430841, 'I''ve always had a sick sense of humor, and I''ve always wanted that to permeate the music because I don''t take myself seriously. I take the music seriously, but I know I''m not God''s gift to anyone except my mom.', 20120, 0), (430842, 'I don''t have a caustic sense of humor. What I find funny, that humor comes from a much gentler place.', 68459, 0), (430843, 'I think God gave us senses of humor, and we should use them.', 68459, 0), (430844, 'I''m drawn to the unconventional because I''ve been drawn unconventionally. I believe that I''m supposed to topple over these false images of what''s idealistically beautiful. Because, of course, these intangible qualities are very attractive to women. Sincerity. Sense of humor. Success.', 58187, 0), (430845, 'I think being a parent is knowing how to love. Sometimes love is discipline, sometimes it''s humor, sometimes it''s listening.', 22747, 0), (430846, 'You see, that''s another thing that my parents gave me: an enormously great sense of humor.', 68200, 0), (430847, 'I just am a snob when it comes to humor.', 68409, 0), (430848, 'Humor is a wonderful way to deal with our suffering because if we can laugh at our troubles, we can feel better. Thich Nhat Hanh is a special man who has helped millions with their suffering with incredible technique. But he doesn''t know real suffering, because he has not dated as much as I have.', 68460, 0), (430849, 'I have this horrible sense of humor where I think discomfort is funny - partly because I experience discomfort a lot, and it''s a way of laughing at it and getting a release.', 68461, 0), (430850, 'Some people say my humor focuses too much on stereotypes. It doesn''t. It focuses on facts.', 18382, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (430851, 'The darker the film, the more vital everyone''s sense of humor is on set.', 68462, 0), (430852, 'I think, in our darkest moments, you have to find the humor, and you have to find the lightness.', 68463, 0), (430853, 'Humor is richly rewarding to the person who employs it. It has some value in gaining and holding attention, but it has no persuasive value at all.', 4940, 0), (430854, 'A lot of stars don''t have a sense of humor.', 2356, 0), (430855, 'My fam is just a regular family. But all of them have great senses of humor.', 21158, 0), (430856, 'For me, whenever I would see a lot of ''black films,'' I didn''t feel represented in it. I didn''t feel connected to the characters or the situations or the humor.', 68464, 0), (430857, 'I''m happy to say that at 62, I think I''ve reached that point where stuff doesn''t bother me as much, and my gratitude level has gone way up, especially having gone through the loss that I''ve had, and losing so many of the great artists that I was close to. They taught me how to see it with a grain of salt and a lot of humor and perspective.', 10602, 0), (430858, 'One of my favorite things about ''Star Trek'' wasn''t just the overt banter but the humor in that show about the relationships between the main characters and their reactions to the situations they would face there was a lot of comedy in that show without ever breaking its reality. ', 32870, 0), (430859, 'I find that people find a way out of misery through humor and it''s humor that''s often unacceptable to people who are not in quite such a state of misery.', 67451, 0), (430860, 'Being Jewish is a big part of my artistic sensibility and my humor... I think it gives me a certain take on the world on a literary level.', 50328, 0), (430861, 'I always thought the biggest failing of Americans was their lack of irony. They are very serious there! Naturally, there are exceptions... the Jewish, Italian, and Irish humor of the East Coast.', 4794, 0), (430862, 'I realized women and humor were linked very closely.', 494, 0), (430863, 'It''s hard to force creativity and humor.', 27702, 0), (430864, 'No mind is thoroughly well organized that is deficient in a sense of humor.', 1910, 0), (430865, 'To me, Ann Romney sounds like a better candidate than her husband. She put her MS into remission through horseback riding, alternative therapies, and a healthy diet. She knows how to pace herself. She has a sense of humor and an innate honesty, and her hair moves in the wind. Maybe she should run.', 18445, 0), (430866, 'Texas humor and Southern humor are pretty similar.', 24382, 0), (430867, 'People are wired for lots of things. We''re wired for novelty. We''re wired for humor. We''re wired for new pieces of information that surprise us in some way or add value to our lives. We''re wired for fear.', 2922, 0), (430868, 'I don''t think I could ever do a network sitcom because the humor is often based on some trite circumstance. I don''t want to be a part of a show where it''s mostly about coming up with the jokes.', 68465, 0), (430869, 'Feature-length film comedy is harder to pull off than the episodic sitcom - it doesn''t have the same factory machinery up and running, teams of writers putting familiar characters through permutations - but that doesn''t explain the widening quality gap that makes movie humor look like a genetic defective.', 67706, 0), (430870, 'I don''t happen to have a sense of humor personally, so I don''t know what''s funny about a character... This happens to be a feature of my life generally.', 61303, 0), (430871, 'Jon Stewart, Bill Maher, Stephen Colbert. Those are the guys I look at who are telling me pretty much the truth. And they throw humor into it which makes it much more interesting to listen to.', 64763, 0), (430872, 'Humor is such a wonderful thing, helping you realize what a fool you are but how beautiful that is at the same time.', 9768, 0), (430873, 'I''ve always thought my strengths were I''m smart, and I have a good sense of humor. I definitely struggle with feeling confident.', 2398, 0), (430874, 'I''m a humor writer, so I don''t always present myself in the best light.', 2325, 0), (430875, 'Humor''s an excellent way to make a point more palatable and/or relatable.', 2325, 0), (430876, '''The Sundial'' is written with the kind of humor that would make a guillotine laugh.', 28809, 0), (430877, 'I quite like dark humor.', 68466, 0), (430878, 'Sure, I am funny and have a good sense of humor. Mostly, though, I just tell the truth. The internal dialogue people have in their heads - I just write it.', 68467, 0), (430879, 'I don''t feel that I''m strictly Danish I don''t feel that my sense of humor is strictly Danish or my human sensibility is strictly Danish. ', 68468, 0), (430880, 'For me, humor is everything!', 4858, 0), (430881, 'Mother humor is such a universal theme. I wrote a show called ''25 Questions for a Jewish Mother.'' I had people coming up to me after the show saying, ''I''m Baptist, and my mother is just like yours.''', 4858, 0), (430882, 'I love the vulgar. I kind of have the humor of a 17-year-old boy.', 4858, 0), (430883, 'If you''re that hypersensitive about color and don''t have a sense of humor, don''t marry out of your race.', 12362, 0), (430884, 'The total absence of humor from the Bible is one of the most singular things in all literature.', 2606, 0), (430885, 'When I look at a lot of older stuff that I''ve written, I think one sign of amateur humor writing is when you see people trying too hard.', 2192, 0), (430886, 'My stories are very somber, so I think I need the comic ingredient. Besides, life has so much humor.', 9731, 0), (430887, 'I don''t think humor is forced upon my universe it''s a part of it. ', 9731, 0), (430888, 'I got my sense of humor from my grandmother. You know, my grandmother was very funny.', 67081, 0), (430889, 'From an early age onward, it was said that ''Ingmar has no sense of humor.''', 3396, 0), (430890, 'Most of the people in my family were pretty funny. Everyone had a good sense of humor. I came to California right after college, wanting to be a musician.', 68469, 0), (430891, 'I get asked, ''How can you have such failures in your films?'' Well, what else is life about? There''s some sense of constant failure in something. Humor gives you a distance from it.', 68470, 0), (430892, 'I don''t really have a type. I don''t want to be a cliche. But personality is a big thing for me. You can find cute guys all over. But he''s got to have some sort of sense of humor, which is so hard to find in a guy. He''s got to be a bit smart.', 68471, 0), (430893, 'Religious humor is not really my area, so I probably wouldn''t do anything about that, or politics or something.', 68472, 0), (430894, 'I think God has a tremendous sense of humor.', 30291, 0), (430895, 'I like being a Baha''i who has an out-there sense of humor. God gives us talents and faculties, and making people laugh is one of mine.', 30291, 0), (430896, 'I love Sell Out, I think it''s great. I love the jingles. The whole thing as an album is a wonderful piece of work. The cover. Everything about it. It''s got humor, great songs, irony.', 68473, 0), (430897, 'Certainly my personality, my sense of humor, my outlook on life was informed by the experiences of my parents and the stories they shared with me.', 67087, 0), (430898, 'Without a sense of humor, I would have been gone a long time ago.', 57186, 0), (430899, 'In the ''Hurt Locker'' there''s a lot of me in there, a sense of humor, a man of few words and a lot of action.', 68474, 0), (430900, 'I often have said that to be a college president, you need a thick skin, a good sense of humor, and nerves like sewer pipes.', 68475, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (430901, 'I tend to deal with most issues with humor... always have and always will.', 68475, 0), (430902, 'The biggest void that people can have in their lives is a sense of humor. Spending your life with someone who doesn''t have that wouldn''t be palatable.', 62716, 0), (430903, 'I think the thrust of any child is to try to fit in and be part of it. And I can''t tell you how many times my humor, you know, what I thought was humor ended up making me the outsider. Like I''d be, I go, ''It''s a joke.'' And they''d go, ''Well, what was funny?'' And they just thought I was insane.', 62716, 0), (430904, 'Part of my humor is the fact that I love coming out of left field. I don''t want people to expect what is going to happen next.', 62716, 0), (430905, 'In conversation, humor is worth more than wit and easiness more than knowledge.', 3428, 0), (430906, 'I like doing comedy, I like doing drama. Naturally I like to do, I like doing dramas, I like conflict, and when I do a comedy, you know, I''ve found that, like, romantic comedy is the trickiest one, because often it''s neither: it''s not romantic and it''s not funny. So, like, I like a comedy that''s biting. It''s biting humor or really quirky humor.', 68476, 0), (430907, 'Our ability to find humor in the world, to make connections between previously unconnected notions, to create new ideas, to share in a common culture: All these essentially human acts depend on memory.', 13388, 0), (430908, 'I can''t not find humor in elements of most parts of life, but at the same time nothing ever seems perpetually funny to me.', 68477, 0), (430909, 'I wasn''t the sharpest tool in the shed, and I wasn''t the biggest, so I got real good at running my mouth and making people laugh and using humor as a way to not get into fights.', 68478, 0), (430910, 'Philip Larkin has a tough honesty and sense of humor that I find irresistible, as a contemporary poet.', 68479, 0), (430911, 'You know, I''m Australian, and we have got the worst sense of humor. We are cruel to each other.', 15778, 0), (430912, 'I tried to go out for theater or theater arts, but I was too scared or too intimidated. But I had a lot of friends on the cross country team that had great senses of humor.', 20329, 0), (430913, 'If you stop and think about it, nearly all great humor is at the expense of someone or something.', 62972, 0), (430914, 'And humor has always been a weapon. You want to get even on somebody? You want to attack somebody? Make fun of them.', 62972, 0), (430915, 'There''s a charm, there''s a rhythm, there''s a soul to Jewish humor. When I first saw Richard Pryor perform, I told him, ''You''re doing a Jewish act.''', 62972, 0), (430916, 'What we''re doing is fun - if you have any sense of humor at all!', 66804, 0), (430917, 'I like to deal with EVERY aspect of our condition, and that means terror and humor in equal mix. Some books have more room for humor than others.', 591, 0), (430918, 'I need a man with a good sense of humor and a kind heart.', 68480, 0), (430919, 'I like Strahan a lot. I''ve known him for years. He was a Giant here - in many ways. Had a big following with the New York Giants. He''s very funny. He''s got a great sense of humor.', 66610, 0), (430920, 'I''m a pretty tenacious person; I get that from my mom. So sometimes, I use dark humor. I can''t take myself too seriously.', 12393, 0), (430921, 'Life is just so much fun and so filled with humor.', 68481, 0), (430922, 'I would say just start writing. You''ve got to write every day. Copy someone that you like if you think that perhaps could become your sound, too. I did that with Hemingway, and I thought I was writing just like Hemingway. Then all of a sudden it occurred to me - he didn''t have a sense of humor. I don''t know anything he''s written that''s funny.', 1806, 0), (430923, 'Humor reminds you, when you''re flattened by sorrow, that you''re still human.', 8274, 0), (430924, 'You write the way you think about the world. My motto in times of trouble - and I''m speaking of life, not writing - is ''no humor too black.''', 8274, 0), (430925, 'People come up to me as I leave the stage after a performance and tell me tey saw my mother onstage with me every time I sing. I keep a sense of humor about it.', 68482, 0), (430926, 'Short fiction is like low relief. And if your story has no humor in it, then you''re trying to look at something in the pitch dark. With the light of humor, it throws what you''re writing into relief so that you can actually see it.', 8274, 0), (430927, 'There are two MFA programs here at the University of Texas, and I read on the jury of both of them. And it''s amazing to me how many really talented young writers seem to fear humor.', 8274, 0), (430928, 'A lot of people into Tool, for some reason, are not interested in humor.', 9698, 0), (430929, 'If golf wasn''t enjoyable and there wasn''t a lot of humor and enjoyment, even though the game is so frustrating, you would wonder why you put yourself through it.', 2319, 0), (430930, 'The comics that are just conversing with you up there and drawing on their own life, yeah, I guess so. I guess some do political humor, some do topical humor, but the ones that I like, the ones that are appealing to me, were guys who were just talking to you about their life.', 2319, 0), (430931, 'I never worry about people not taking my work seriously as a result of the humor. In the end, the comic''s best trick is the illusion that comedy is effortless. That people imagine what he''s doing is easy is an occupational hazard.', 8957, 0), (430932, 'Quite often, intent on conveying how things can go wrong for a culture (science fiction) or an individual (horror) or all of magical creation (fantasy), works of fantastika often preclude comedy, because humor gets in the way of messages of doom or struggle.', 9691, 0), (430933, 'All I know about humor is that I don''t know anything about it.', 13077, 0), (430934, 'I''ve heard too many times where people say that I''m this ultra-serious guy. In truth, I''ve got an extremely absurd sense of humor. I thrive on the absurd - I love it.', 68483, 0), (430935, 'My own life is wonderful, but if I had to live the life of someone else, I''d gladly choose that of Julia Child or Dr. Seuss: two outrageously original people, each of whom fashioned an idiosyncratic wisdom, passion for life, and sense of humor into an art form that anyone and everyone could savor.', 12039, 0), (430936, 'Yes, I have a good sense of humor to sort of last a long time in show business, and I think to be able to find comedic value in who you are and the people that you work is always a good thing.', 68484, 0), (430937, 'I think it''s hilarious at 40 years old to bring out my roller skates from ''Starlight Express.'' I find the humor and even the sadness in it hilarious and something to celebrate.', 68484, 0), (430938, 'With Ricky Gervais, it''s all shades of wrong, it''s my kind of humor.', 68485, 0), (430939, 'It''s just my natural way - to be funny. I don''t know why that is. But as I''ve said, humor is a quick cover for shock, horror, confusion. The critics hate funny writers for the most part. They think funny is not serious, but I think that funny can be even more serious than nonfunny. And it can be more affecting, too.', 9578, 0), (430940, 'If I ever have sex with someone I might be able to develop a sense of humor.', 68486, 0), (430941, 'To me, sadness and humor aren''t disrelated and humor is the best tool I''ve had against the sadness in my life.', 68487, 0), (430942, 'I think that sense of humor is important in marriage. A sense of humor gets people through marriage.', 68488, 0), (430943, 'Sometimes a scene may be about one thing, and it may end up still being about that, but the emotionality of it comes from somewhere else, or the humor of it comes from somewhere else, and it gives it that real-life quality.', 68488, 0), (430944, 'I really hate sitcoms on television with canned laughter and stuff. What really makes me laugh is the real-life stuff. I''ve got a dry sense of humor.', 60478, 0), (430945, 'I wish I could be as thin as Jessica Simpson. I think she looks gorgeous! I have had Jessica on my show several times, and I can tell you that girl is genuine and funny with a great self-deprecating sense of humor.', 68489, 0), (430946, 'It''s continuously humbling to work hard, you know? As long as you''ve got a good work ethic and a sense of humor, I don''t think anybody can become too much of an egoist under those circumstances.', 68489, 0), (430947, 'Laughter is involuntary. If it''s funny you laugh.', 13542, 0), (430948, 'My books are shelved in different places, depending on the bookstore. Sometimes they can be found in the Mystery section, sometimes in the Humor department, and occasionally even in the Literature aisle, which is somewhat astounding.', 2257, 0), (430949, 'Humor can be an incredible lacerating and effective weapon. And that is the way I use it.', 2257, 0), (430950, 'Daddy was hilarious. He could take the most mundane event and tell it so that we all on the floor laughing. He trained me in the joys of humor.', 68490, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (430951, 'I like dark humor. My favorite movie of all time is ''Harold and Maude.''', 68491, 0), (430952, 'Humor is the only way to tell a story. Especially the dark ones.', 2479, 0), (430953, 'I''ve always adored the filmmaker Sam Fuller. The first time I watched ''Shock Corridor'' was such a magnificent discovery. I love his lack of subtlety, the way he tackles serious topics with bold and inappropriate humor.', 2479, 0), (430954, 'Every time I''ve done comedy in, like, traditional comedy clubs, there''s always these comedians that do really well with audiences but that the other comedians hate because they''re just, you know, doing kind of cheap stuff like dancing around or doing, like, very kind of base sex humor a lot, and stuff like that.', 12128, 0), (430955, 'Over the years, I''ve learned that a sense of humor is the only skill that allows you to turn sucking at life into a career.', 68492, 0), (430956, 'My childhood was great because my family has an amazing sense of humor, and it was just all making videos and jokes and doing skits and things.', 68492, 0), (430957, 'My parents and my brother instilled in me my sense of humor. That''s kind of the way we communicate with each other, and it''s always been a way for me to get to know people.', 68492, 0), (430958, 'Depending on where my self-confidence was, growing up, I would use humor either to bring people closer, or to keep them away from certain feelings I had.', 68492, 0), (430959, 'Humor disarms people. It opens them up to starting a dialogue about things they wouldn''t normally talk about. I don''t understand how people who don''t have a sense of humor get through life.', 68492, 0), (430960, 'Even when something sad or tragic happens, I find a way to look at it in a positive light. People who don''t have a sense of humor must be so sad all the time.', 68492, 0), (430961, 'It''s amazing how many companies aren''t really in tune to the needs of different travelers. There''s just so many embarrassing situations that you go through when you travel. You have to have a sense of humor about it and take it in stride. My whole approach is to embrace spontaneity.', 68492, 0), (430962, 'People who know me know I have a sense of humor that can really push the envelope.', 67099, 0), (430963, 'I was always silly in high school. I used to always get in trouble because I was laughing. I''ve always thought I was funny but never thought I could use it to make money. In 1996, I decided I was going to use my humor to get on TV to make money.', 68493, 0), (430964, 'My humor is a lot like Kristen Wiig''s from ''Saturday Night Live'' or ''Bridesmaids.'' Quirky, off the beaten path.', 68494, 0), (430965, 'Every black film feels like it''s Tyler Perry, and that just needs to stop. But people seem to slowly be looking for what else is out there - ''Is there something else besides this type of humor?'' ''I''m tired of seeing men in dresses.''', 68399, 0), (430966, 'Puns are a form of humor with words.', 40284, 0), (430967, 'I don''t know if my sense of humor goes over Americans'' heads.', 68495, 0), (430968, 'I make fun of situations and try and find the humor in things, but it''s never at the expense of the other guy.', 68496, 0), (430969, 'I''ve always been a fan of a Johnny Carson because he was so great with an audience and not afraid of self-deprecating humor.', 68497, 0), (430970, 'For the most part, comedians are pretty friendly with each other. They always say they badmouth each other, but most of the time, they''re friends. We''re the only ones that can really stand our type of humor.', 36389, 0), (430971, 'Jerry Seinfeld is amazing in many ways, not the least of them his ability to find humor, and convincing us to find it, too, in the million-and-two details about modern life that under different circumstances might send us into paroxysms of rage.', 68498, 0), (430972, 'My parents have always had a great sense of humor. And I really appreciate good humor in songs, witty lyrics that sneak up on you and then you listen again, and say: ''That''s so funny.'' John Prine''s songs have always had this really witty tone.', 68110, 0), (430973, 'If you''re playing a good guy, you show some darkness. If you''re playing a dark guy, you show something different, like humor, that will mix it up and hopefully surpass the audience''s expectations. What I''m battling all the time is complacency in the audience. I try to bring a little mystery to what might happen because that engages people more.', 68499, 0), (430974, 'Well, darkness with humor... I''m not an extremely suicidal or sad person.', 68500, 0), (430975, 'As far as humor goes, I''ve always been a very insecure person and I''ve always wanted to be liked.', 68500, 0), (430976, 'The woman who runs the Pennsylvania Innocence Project told me that there''s a man she''s been trying to get out of prison for 26 years. Every night before she goes to bed, she thinks, ''What is he doing?'' She says you don''t sleep. And yet, she has the greatest sense of humor and this light that comes out of her.', 67106, 0), (430977, 'You probably found ''How to Survive a Robot Uprising'' in the humor section. Let''s just hope that is where it belongs.', 15991, 0), (430978, 'There was a time I was very much blaming the way I felt on L.A, that it was a vacuum of creativity, of humor or anything organic, and I was really angry at the place. But then today I feel completely different - I love L.A.!', 67575, 0), (430979, 'You''ve got to have a sense of humor to keep your sanity.', 68104, 0), (430980, 'I have wit in my work and a sense of humor, but I do not use irony in any way.', 48839, 0), (430981, 'I think in my case, I had no choice but to have a good sense of humor. I grew up with my dad, Danny Thomas, and George Burns and Bob Hope and Milton Berle and Sid Caesar and all those guys were at our house all the time and telling jokes and making each other laugh.', 34804, 0), (430982, 'The rejection that we all take and the sadness and the aggravation and the loss of jobs and all of the things that we live through in our lives, without a sense of humor, I don''t know how people make it.', 34804, 0), (430983, 'I''m a comedian, and I have my share of anxiety and depression; so do most of my friends. My humor tends to lie in the juxtaposition of extreme lightness - I''m a huge musical-theater fan - and extreme darkness. And so I really like playing with those because that''s how I feel.', 68501, 0), (430984, 'I''m not sure. But that bless-his/her-heart kind of melancholic humor is among my favorite things in the world. I guess it exposes a kind of humanity - or that''s the hope, at least - a kind of grudging respect for human frailty. Unless it''s actually kicking human frailty while it''s down - I''m not sure.', 13164, 0), (430985, 'I''m looking at some comedic horror films because I have often been accused of being too dark. I''m not dark, not compared with ''Saw'' or anything like that. So I''m looking at live-action horror films, but not slasher ones - ones that have humor and maybe some social satire.', 68294, 0), (430986, 'It''s amazing how these little guys can say things that a mortal human could never get away with. There''s some sort of unspoken license... when outlandish things come out of an inanimate object, somehow it equals humor.', 13245, 0), (430987, 'I''ve worked a lot in comedy. As much as I love playing dramatic roles, it''s always nice to be able to have some humor around when working.', 68502, 0), (430988, 'Lucifer has a sense of fun about life he just likes to play with people. But the sense of humor of the show is what makes the show entertaining as opposed to dark. ', 68502, 0), (430989, 'There''s some sort of unspoken license... when outlandish things come out of an inanimate object, somehow it equals humor.', 13245, 0), (430990, 'It is characteristic of all deep human problems that they are not to be approached without some humor and some bewilderment.', 11410, 0), (430991, 'Reilly Brown is a master of balancing action, humor, and extreme violence, and his character designs for some of the alien races and technology that we encounter is just amazing.', 68503, 0), (430992, 'I can''t be as open on national television as I can when I''m having dinner with friends. But that doesn''t mean the type of person I am is different. My values, my dislikes, my sense of humor are the same.', 68504, 0), (430993, 'Be fun! I don''t like homes or rooms that don''t have a sense of humor or have some sense of whimsy or a personality. Your home should reflect who you are, and what you love. I would never have something in my home because it''s the thing to have. I have to love it and it needs some connection to me.', 10716, 0), (430994, 'My parents and my sister died... very close together, and after that, I lost quite a bit of my sense of humor. Most of it I think has kind of come back, but I know there was a time when I didn''t think things were funny anymore. I kind of think they''re funny again.', 4685, 0), (430995, 'God has a most wicked sense of humor.', 66873, 0), (430996, 'Bathroom humor, fart, and poo poo humor in movies gets a laugh. It''s a pretty easy audience, and that''s been around for ages.', 68505, 0), (430997, 'I learned early in my career to not let myself get in the way of humor but, instead, find what is great in a talented person.', 68506, 0), (430998, 'I always had to genuinely like the actors I worked with and use my enthusiasm and vision to give them confidence to push their creativity and their humor.', 68506, 0), (430999, 'My humor tends to be a little more edgy than is appropriate for ''Twilight,'' although I got some in there. That was fun! There''s just a tonal difference. For me, storytelling is storytelling. But, I do like writing for grown ups.', 68507, 0), (431000, 'Don''t wish me happiness - I don''t expect to be happy it''s gotten beyond that, somehow. Wish me courage and strength and a sense of humor - I will need them all.', 1407, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (431001, 'The way humor''s usually used in horror, it''s as a pressure-release valve; without it, the drama would escalate out of all control almost immediately.', 23799, 0), (431002, 'Whatever else an American believes or disbelieves about himself, he is absolutely sure he has a sense of humor.', 994, 0), (431003, 'When you meet someone new who instantly gets you, your sense of humor and your attitudes and your worldview, even if theirs are different - and you get them in return. You both talk and talk and agree and laugh and nod and yes, yes, of course you should get another round of drinks.', 520, 0), (431004, 'You can''t be funny if you don''t have good material.', 68508, 0), (431005, 'Both conservatives and liberals watch ''Parks and Recreation,'' and they each think the show is for them, which is really cool. ''SNL'' was totally different. It was exciting because everyone was paying attention. Political humor works when people know what you''re talking about.', 1498, 0), (431006, 'Humor is perhaps a sense of intellectual perspective: an awareness that some things are really important, others not; and that the two kinds are most oddly jumbled in everyday affairs.', 8661, 0), (431007, 'There are so many things to talk about between black people, Hispanic people, white people, gay people, men, women, it''s all based on fear. We all have fears, this thing that stops us from embracing as we are one. We are never going to be one. People are messed up, but humor lets us see how ignorant we can be.', 68400, 0), (431008, 'You learn timing on the road. You learn structure and how to read an audience. You learn so much about the business of laughter that you can''t learn on a set, because it''s all on you. Sometimes you bomb, and you know not to tell that joke again... You just hope people find the humor in the awkwardness.', 68400, 0), (431009, 'It felt as if things were literally slipping through my fingers. Things were just streaming away from me. I lost my sense of humor. I''m still looking for that.', 68509, 0), (431010, 'With actors like Steve McQueen, Paul Newman and Harrison Ford, what made them such icons is that even in dramatic movies, their characters had a sense of humor.', 41316, 0), (431011, 'I try to cope with everything through humor.', 66955, 0), (431012, 'I came into the ''Comedy Bang! Bang!'' TV show with a level of confidence that I don''t think I would''ve had if I hadn''t been doing the podcast for three years already. I certainly had to figure out in those three years the sense of humor I wanted to do and the way to talk to celebrities without being incredibly intimidated by them.', 68510, 0), (431013, 'If I can''t see the humor in it, how am I going to be funny?', 68511, 0), (431014, 'The guys in my band are great-we watch movies, we eat pizza, take walks, read books. Everybody has a really great sense of humor. And my boyfriend comes and visits me on the road.', 8136, 0), (431015, 'Any film which views the darker side of life, which is death with a sense of humor, is very much to my taste.', 68048, 0), (431016, 'If somebody is not on the same page with me humor wise, I can''t give them that.', 34519, 0), (431017, 'Brits have a better sense of humor in most ways. It''s darker, more cutting.', 34519, 0), (431018, 'Maybe the bar is low, but most of the strips that are 50, 60, 70 years old that are on their second or third generation of artists, the humor is pretty bland. There are others by people that were raised on ''Family Guy'' or ''South Park'' that are edgier. Mine''s not as edgy as those, but it''s edgier than ''Beetle Bailey.''', 34519, 0), (431019, 'Thomas, my 15-year-old, is effectively my editor, I''ve always trusted his voice, more than anybody, on the strip for years. He has one of those ears that''s just tuned to the rhythm of humor, so if he says something''s not funny, my stomach just hurts because I know he''s right, and it''s already been drawn.', 34519, 0), (431020, 'I think there''s always room for humor, especially when you''re talking about really serious issues.', 212, 0), (431021, 'I thought I was going to be known for my humor. But then I had an idea for a story, which was absolutely not humorous. But, of course, that''s the one that sells and becomes big.', 212, 0), (431022, 'It''s always amazed me how little attention philosophers, psychologists, or anyone else actually has paid to humor.', 26588, 0), (431023, 'I still haven''t found the humor in getting hit by a cement truck. My knees still hurt when I think about it, so no jokes about that yet.', 68296, 0), (431024, 'I think sometimes my humor is extremely dry, and a lot of times I would say things that I thought were very funny but... I have a reputation of - people think of me as a very fundamentalist, humorless fellow.', 34875, 0), (431025, 'Humor does not diminish the pain - it makes the space around it get bigger.', 46215, 0), (431026, 'When you do find humor in trying times, one of the first and most important changes you experience is that you see your perplexing problems in a new way - you suddenly have a new perspective on them.', 46215, 0), (431027, 'When we are dealing with death we are constantly being dragged down by the event: Humor diverts our attention and lifts our sagging spirits.', 46215, 0), (431028, 'Whether planned or not, humor takes our mind off of our troubles.', 46215, 0), (431029, 'Any attempts at humor immediately after September 11th were deemed tasteless.', 46215, 0), (431030, 'Since the goal of my programs is to show audiences how humor can both help them heal as well as deal with not-so-funny stuff, I decided to discuss the events of the previous week, the pain all of us were feeling, and how humor and some laughter might be beneficial.', 46215, 0), (431031, 'In looking for humor, keep in mind this guideline: Sometimes it takes a little time to see the humor in your upsets; you may not find something to laugh about immediately.', 46215, 0), (431032, 'When we can find some humor in our upsets, they no longer seem as large or as important as they once did.', 46215, 0), (431033, 'Humor expands our limited picture frame and gets us to see more than just our problem.', 46215, 0), (431034, 'Humor can inform and break down stigma, which is a huge issue in the military.', 68425, 0), (431035, 'I wish there were more humor in my work than I see in it.', 19770, 0), (431036, 'The best way to make your audience laugh is to start laughing yourself.', 2204, 0), (431037, 'People with no humor, they''re outta my life.', 66236, 0), (431038, 'I visited Jobs for the last time in his Palo Alto, Calif., home. He had moved to a downstairs bedroom because he was too weak to go up and down stairs. He was curled up in some pain, but his mind was still sharp and his humor vibrant.', 1992, 0), (431039, 'Some major writers have a huge impact, like Ayn Rand, who to my mind is a lousy fiction writer because her writing has no compassion and virtually no humor. She has a philosophical and economical message that she is passing off as fiction, but it really isn''t fiction at all.', 27533, 0), (431040, 'I think all good drama is funny. All the best drama is ultimately very funny. Life is funny. You can''t have any honest treatise on life without bumping into some humor.', 67681, 0), (431041, 'Because I was a television writer for many years, I write very conversationally. I put things straight, and with a lot of humor.', 6023, 0), (431042, 'Stephen King has inspired me with his humor and honesty, and his admonition that the author''s job is to tell the truth.', 3119, 0), (431043, 'There is humor in the darkest of moments - People who I have loved and passed away, and very high stake situations where you can''t help but laugh. I think that''s very human.', 68512, 0), (431044, 'Humor is always more interesting when it comes from someone who''s had more than, like, five experiences.', 58944, 0), (431045, 'One of the things that would be great is to some day have so many women comedy writers that we wouldn''t say there''s just one type of female humor. There''s lots.', 58944, 0), (431046, 'In prehistoric times, mankind often had only two choices in crisis situations: fight or flee. In modern times, humor offers us a third alternative; fight, flee - or laugh.', 3158, 0), (431047, 'Humor starts like a wildfire, but then continues on, smoldering, smoldering for years.', 3158, 0), (431048, 'I remember when humor was gentle pokes. I used to call it ''arm around the shoulder'' humor. Now they go for the jugular and they take no prisoners. It''s mean, mean stuff.', 3158, 0), (431049, 'President Ford used humor a great deal.', 3158, 0), (431050, 'I think that humor is part of what saves us from despair.', 57314, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (431051, 'My dad was a very funny man - he''s the one who taught me life would be awfully hard without humor! I''m sure his Irish wit in some way influenced my decision to become an actress.', 68513, 0), (431052, 'I''m a big fan of gallows humor. When my aunt passed away, she was in a coma for a day before my cousins pulled the plug. And the amount of joking and base humor that went on that day around her bed was so insane. It''s crazy how people talk when something horrible is happening.', 68514, 0), (431053, 'There are psychological repercussions to illness and we need a little more help to get through the effects not only on the afflicted but on the family. And I think there''s even a place for humor in that.', 68389, 0), (431054, 'I don''t really like using ridicule as a form of humor.', 55098, 0), (431055, 'A pun is the lowest form of humor, unless you thought of it yourself.', 5026, 0), (431056, 'There seems to be no lengths to which humorless people will not go to analyze humor. It seems to worry them.', 2188, 0), (431057, 'I have this idyllic love life, but my mind just won''t accept that. I would like to bring a new guy home every night. I try to make humor out of that situation.', 49833, 0), (431058, 'I will say that as I get older and calmer and quieter in my own self, the one quality in a woman that I find more and more attractive is kindness. A sense of adventure and humor is important too, but I truly find kindness and consideration for others to be the most attractive thing in anyone.', 26628, 0), (431059, 'I''ll do humor about myself, I''ll poke fun and everything, but that''s me and I can do it to me. I think it''s cruel to do it to somebody else.', 68515, 0), (431060, 'M*A*S*H offered real characters and everybody identified with them because they had such soul. The humor was intelligent and it always assumed that you had an intellect.', 68516, 0), (431061, 'I think the Canadian sense of humor is dryer than America''s and juicier than Britain''s. I think it''s a cross between the two of them, really.', 24547, 0), (431062, 'I was born in England - though both of my parents are American - and there''s something about the ''Muppets'' where they have this combination of English and American humor.', 47435, 0), (431063, 'There''s a lot of movies, and I''ve made some of them that could be categorized this way, but there''s definitely been a trend in animated features of all types to be a little bit cynical, if you will, to have a little bit of ''knowing'' humor to them, kind of a wink to the audience.', 68517, 0), (431064, 'I talk about race and culture, and that''s what my fans respond to. If you grew up in an environment where race and culture were never an issue for you, or where you don''t see the humor in our so-called differences, then you might not respond to what I''m doing.', 68518, 0), (431065, 'Men love it. They have a sense of humor, whereas a lot of women are threatened or just don''t get it.', 66874, 0), (431066, 'Comedy, we may say, is society protecting itself - with a smile.', 16669, 0), (431067, 'Even celebrities, most people have a sense of humor. Most of the people we meet who we''ve done on the show, like it.', 68519, 0), (431068, 'I love the idea of things being strict and things being uniform. That''s the reason why I surround each collection with humor or irony. I want to make sure that it''s not too serious and that there is some element that throws it off because otherwise that would make it really boring. There''s always a story that''s somewhat fantastical.', 68520, 0), (431069, 'I wasn''t close to my father, but I wanted to be all my life. He had a funny sense of humor, and he laughed all the time - good and loud, like I do. He was a gay Irish gentleman and very good-looking. And he wanted to be close to me, too, but we never had much time together.', 346, 0), (431070, 'What a strange world this would be if we all had the same sense of humor.', 59555, 0), (431071, 'Russian humor is to adapt or make some sense or nonsense out of the insanity of their lives.', 2851, 0), (431072, 'People in Russia adapt to misery by a deep, deep humor.', 2851, 0), (431073, 'I don''t have a disregard for my reader in humor pieces.', 2851, 0), (431074, 'I think what is important for things to be funny is if you the listener, or the reader, get a chance to supply the humor of it yourself.', 2851, 0), (431075, 'With reporting, if you work hard, you can usually pull something out. But writing humor doesn''t respond to working hard, necessarily. I mean, you could just sit there and look at the page all day and maybe something will come.', 2851, 0), (431076, 'Writing humor for me is more like a watchful-ness. You have to watch. When you say something funny, or someone else does, it''s more like you wait for the piece.', 2851, 0), (431077, 'My fans have great senses of humor and eat too much chocolate.', 612, 0), (431078, 'As a kid, I loved ''Godot'' because of the poetry and the humor and the strangeness, but then as you get older, it''s much more resonant.', 68521, 0), (431079, 'I think in life, the sense of humor and comedy always exists.', 68522, 0), (431080, 'Sometimes Americans don''t quite get my sense of humor. My good ol'' British sarcasm seems to go over their heads.', 68523, 0), (431081, 'I appreciate humor so much, but I''m actually not a funny girl.', 68524, 0), (431082, 'I was a little shocked at how adult some of the humor was, because I was never that into animation before and when I watched ''Shrek'' I really laughed out loud.', 68525, 0), (431083, 'Rowling is a luminous storyteller. I love her sense of humor and the intricate wizarding world she built around Hogwarts. I think all writers aspire to be like her, to capture readers like she does. But I didn''t think about ''Harry Potter'' when I wrote ''The Bone Season.''', 14689, 0), (431084, 'I have a very silly sense of humor. I''ve never laughed harder in my entire life than seeing someone with toilet paper stuck on the bottom of their shoe.', 6225, 0), (431085, 'The love of truth lies at the root of much humor.', 2472, 0), (431086, 'If you look at the game and everything, it''s not quite like looking at an animated film, because that''s total character. This, this is really movement, but it''s got funny little things if you look for the humor. They''re actually getting to the character.', 68526, 0), (431087, 'The whole ability to look at the complexity of race and any sort of associated -ism and still find humor, that''s a very interesting space.', 68527, 0), (431088, 'Funny songs aren''t usually that good. Like Weird Al and maybe a couple of Beatles songs, but it''s kind of hard to bring humor into rock music in an interesting way.', 68528, 0), (431089, 'I lean toward anything with a dark sense of humor. And since I''ve been out of school, the majority of my books have been contemporary; basically, I like my characters to have electricity - even better, a TV.', 6813, 0), (431090, 'The more women sit down and write something in a woman''s voice for a woman, they more you''ll see women in comedy because gender doesn''t define sense of humor. Imagination and intelligence and perspective do.', 55979, 0), (431091, 'Rather than writing about my experiences with other people, ''Ugly Cherries'' is the first song I''ve ever written about myself. It''s a confrontation: an attempt to unpack my own queerness with humor and self care.', 68529, 0), (431092, 'You are not just a funny person or just a journalist. Most people are hybrids of having a smart opinion and a great sense of humor.', 68530, 0), (431093, 'My dad is just like everybody else''s dad. I see him as kind of a goofy guy with a great sense of humor. I try to get in a battle of wits with him, but he always gets me. I emulate him because I''ve never seen anyone work as hard as he does.', 68531, 0), (431094, 'Food is sort of like the Jewish sense of humor, a defense mechanism. It is one of the things that helped the Jews survive through 2,000 years of an often very harsh Diaspora.', 68532, 0), (431095, 'Insult is powerful. Insult begets both rage and humor and often at the same time.', 66744, 0), (431096, 'I''m not an expert on the Malaysian sense of humor.', 68533, 0), (431097, 'There is a collective as well as an individual humor inclining peoples to sadness or cheerfulness, making them see things in bright or somber lights. In fact, only society can pass a collective opinion on the value of human life; for this the individual is incompetent.', 15804, 0), (431098, 'I think probably the qualities that I look for in a man are somewhat different than they were before I became a public person, but not that much different. I think that, sort of, the element of trust is certainly much bigger for me, but the other things that - the other qualities, intelligence and kindness and sense of humor, those things.', 68534, 0), (431099, 'Along with a sense of humor, my songs have to be sincere, and they have to be sung from a position of inner conviction.', 68391, 0), (431100, 'Sometimes the only way to make palatable that which is appalling and apprehensive is to season it with some humor.', 68535, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (431101, 'I think hip-hop does a very good job of infusing comedy and humor and wit into music, a lot more than other genres.', 22973, 0), (431102, 'With Portlandia, I don''t think our intention is always to find something funny. Sometimes the humor comes from taking something really seriously. We''re okay with making somebody feel uncomfortable or uneasy.', 22973, 0), (431103, 'Cathy was the first widely syndicated humor strip created by a woman. The strip was pretty revolutionary at the time not only because it starred a female, but also because it was so emotionally honest about all the conflicting feelings many women had in 1976.', 11928, 0), (431104, 'I''m lucky that my real-life Mom has both a great sense of humor about herself and an amazing ability to slip into complete denial if the subject matter gets a little too close to home.', 11928, 0), (431105, 'Humor comes from the surprise release of some buried tension.', 339, 0), (431106, 'There''s a hysterical, tired sense of humor that comes after working 14 hours a day, six days a week. I like those things because they take the pressure off the constant stress.', 68536, 0), (431107, 'Both of my kids have my sense of humor - they''re definitely entertaining.', 38171, 0), (431108, 'Someone asked me what the key to being a good frontman was, and I think having a sense of humor about it is pretty near the top of that list. It''s a very strange place to be in, and I don''t take that role too seriously.', 68537, 0), (431109, 'I''d probably describe my sense of humor as ''twisted,'' I guess. It''s not hard to make me laugh, especially when I''m surrounded by my close friends, especially my bandmates.', 67140, 0), (431110, 'They don''t make you pay for the humor. It''s up and down, but they''re trying to give you as many laughs as possible in 2 minutes. They are the most honest comedians ever.', 33801, 0), (431111, 'If you don''t infuse humor into a subject matter, no matter how dark, the audience can''t accept the message of a film. It closes them down. Humor can open them up.', 68538, 0), (431112, 'Confidence and a good sense of humor can usually win a chick over.', 68539, 0), (431113, 'If it gets laughs, it''s funny.', 68540, 0), (431114, 'He was just trying to tease me - I knew that later - but he said he''d have to leave because it wasn''t fair to have anyone in the room who was going to make fun of what he had to say. He had a good sense of humor, really.', 68541, 0), (431115, 'My dad''s sense of humor was direct and sometimes surreal - his quick wit is well known amongst our family and friends. He raised me on Spike Jones records and W.C. Fields movies, and his sense of humor fell somewhere in between.', 68542, 0), (431116, 'Bands from Akron have a sense of humor and don''t tend to take themselves too seriously.', 68543, 0), (431117, 'I''m not for gratuitous nudity, but if there''s humor, I don''t have a problem.', 68544, 0), (431118, 'I have a dark sense of humor.', 68545, 0), (431119, 'However, frat-boy humor is funny and it always will be.', 68546, 0), (431120, 'People always ask me how I manage to find humor in so much bleakness. I think this is almost a necessary skill to have.', 11633, 0), (431121, 'I think it would be hard to go the distance in this business without a sense of humor.', 68547, 0), (431122, 'Women, as they grow older, rely more and more on cosmetics. Men, as they grow older, rely more and more on a sense of humor.', 6546, 0), (431123, 'A farce, or slapstick humor, does well universally.', 24983, 0), (431124, 'Sure, the comedians who swear or use scatological humor can get laughs, but they''re uncomfortable laughs.', 24983, 0), (431125, 'Do feminists have a sense of humor? Yes.', 68548, 0), (431126, 'There''s such an odd, eclectic group of people that make up the town of Plymouth, New Hampshire. I don''t think I could avoid not coming out of there with a pretty good sense of humor.', 68549, 0), (431127, 'I never particularly thought of myself as great with girls. I can be awkward, and I have a strange sense of humor at times. But I''ve also been learning to try and embrace that.', 68550, 0), (431128, 'My dad has a dry, deadpan sense of humor, and my mom has an unexpected, wacky take on things. They really encouraged laughing at ourselves and the weirdness of situations that come up growing up in politics.', 34537, 0), (431129, 'Both of my parents have great senses of humor.', 34537, 0), (431130, 'I like good humor.', 67149, 0), (431131, 'Even as a kid I was never the generator of humor, but I always knew who was funny, who to hang out with.', 68551, 0), (431132, 'Athletes tend to have less of a sense of humor than most people. They are heroes to so many. That might be part of it.', 67151, 0), (431133, 'Humor that is edgy is never squeaky clean.', 67151, 0), (431134, 'A taste for irony has kept more hearts from breaking than a sense of humor, for it takes irony to appreciate the joke which is on oneself.', 3164, 0), (431135, 'I always felt different as a kid, and the Kinks were like, ''Yeah, we''re the Kinks.'' Celebrate your difference; don''t be afraid of your sense of humor, or your personality, or who you are. It emboldened me.', 68552, 0), (431136, 'I liked the humor of it, I''ve always enjoyed a sense of humor in God and in religion and in spirituality.', 66820, 0), (431137, 'Conservative humor is frankly harder than liberal humor. You get points for just being liberal. You can get more points if you make fun of your own side sometimes.', 17804, 0), (431138, 'The polls indicated that I was feisty, that I was tough, that I had a sense of humor, but they weren''t quite sure if they liked me and they didn''t know whether or not that I was sensitive.', 17466, 0), (431139, 'I try to bring it across on my record, in my dress, in what I do and what I say because to me humor is important. You should have a dose of that and I guess giving it is what I''m here for.', 68553, 0), (431140, 'I genuinely liked all of the cast members very much. Steve had a wicked sense of humor. I remember Russell coming to my rescue, once. I watched Eric evolve before everyone''s eyes. Maurice loved what he did, so. He treated his character with respect, down to the costuming.', 68554, 0), (431141, 'With humor, it''s so subjective that trying to think of what the ideal reader would think would drive you crazy.', 2232, 0), (431142, 'There''s always a source for humor.', 2232, 0), (431143, 'Those who knew Lincoln described him as an extraordinarily funny man. Humor was an essential aspect of his temperament. He laughed, he explained, so he did not weep.', 17905, 0), (431144, 'Evangelicals always assume that humor and faith are contradictory. It''s OK to smile, to be nice, but not frivolous.', 16455, 0), (431145, 'I think up until the point when we started in the business, which was in the early ''70s, most of the humor was political. The smart humor was political satire.', 68555, 0), (431146, 'I''m not too modest of a person. I''ve got a pretty blue sense of humor.', 68556, 0), (431147, 'I have a very dark sense of humor.', 68557, 0), (431148, 'We''re starting to push the envelope in terms of the expectations, and you can also have your own style, personality and sense of humor, because now we''re allowed to.', 68558, 0), (431149, 'Humor is rare in science fiction... there''s so little of it that it automatically reminds you of other heroes with that acerbic humor when you find it.', 4764, 0), (431150, 'When I did ''Sex and the City,'' it was like, ''Let''s do a comedy where the humor is not coming from innuendo but from the a truthful place. This is a show where we''re going to be able to say and do what we want.''', 68559, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (431151, 'I think the next best thing to solving a problem is finding some humor in it.', 27528, 0), (431152, 'Humor''s always been the problem of my work, hasn''t it? When working, I feel satisfied when I surprise myself. And when I surprise myself, I wind up laughing.', 68560, 0), (431153, 'I did the ''Bionic Woman,'' which of course had a lot of humor in it, and that was really a function of a lot of the ad-libbing and the things that I did in it.', 68561, 0), (431154, 'While it is true that Frank had a great sense of humor, he was also very serious about composing music. In reality there are only a handful of skilled players who can play his most complex pieces. It takes a lot of patience to learn and requires a fantastic memory.', 68562, 0), (431155, 'I''ve always littered my songs with jokes. You might need to dig a little deeper to find the humor, but I would totally object to being some kind of distraught personality. I''ve never tried to attach myself to that.', 68563, 0), (431156, 'I manage through a sense of humor. We all work hard, and work has to be a really interesting, fun place. And that has to start at the top.', 68564, 0), (431157, 'My own inclination is to skew towards humor. They say that some people view life as a comedy, others as a tragedy. Me? Comedy all the way.', 6693, 0), (431158, 'Jazz can be so serious, no sense of humor.', 68565, 0), (431159, 'Academics tend to have wonderfully infantile senses of humor.', 68308, 0), (431160, 'Leonard Cohen has a way with words and with humor that remind me to lighten up, which I appreciate very much.', 22702, 0), (431161, 'I mean, yeah, I''m sure that Python and the other things have paved the way for a greater understanding of the British sense of humor, but I don''t think it''s all that different than the American sense of humor.', 27368, 0), (431162, 'I think at its best the American sense of humor is the same as the British sense of humor at its best, which is to be wry and ironic and self deprecating.', 27368, 0), (431163, 'I don''t really dissect comedy. Nothing kills off humor more than overanalyzing it.', 62919, 0), (431164, 'Roosevelt''s humor was broad, his manner friendly. Of wit there was little; of philosophy, none. What did he possess? Intuition, inspiration, love of adventure.', 68566, 0), (431165, 'I think shows that are completely dramatic are a lie. People use humor to cope. That is how we deal with things. In the darkest situations, there''s humor. And if you don''t show that, you''re not being true to real life.', 68567, 0), (431166, 'You feel like you need to deal with a lot if you''re from Cleveland, so you learn to let things roll off your back, and you learn that humor is the best way to deal with it.', 68568, 0), (431167, 'Comedy is still alive, and there are still funny people. Jews are still overrepresented in comedy and psychiatry and underrepresented in the priesthood. That immigrant Jewish humor is still with us.', 68144, 0), (431168, 'I''d like to explore the more abstract side of people''s minds, as opposed to the usual sitcom stuff. I don''t want to do the typical sitcom-type humor. I''d want to do stuff like go bowling with pineapples.', 17145, 0), (431169, 'I don''t think my sense of humor has changed at all; I was born with this, for better or for worse.', 68403, 0), (431170, 'But it also became the experience, or was the experience, of the writers who were attracted to this kind of humor. They''re all men or women who come from the same kind of experience in their own lives.', 68569, 0), (431171, 'I''ve always chosen my band members based on their sense of humor. It might sound stupid, but it means not only are they fun to live with on a tour bus for years, but humor implies intelligence.', 43562, 0), (431172, 'I''ll let you in on a secret: I can''t stand Jay Ward. I hate being compared to Rocky and Bullwinkle. It''s just a different style of humor.', 68570, 0), (431173, 'Joe Barbera''s s always complaining that he can''t get humor into cartoons anymore. Just do it. You''ve got your money. Why do they let the networks run their lives?', 68570, 0), (431174, 'But if you read Jane Austen, you know that she had a wicked sense of humor. Not only was she funny, but her early writing was very dark and had a gothic tone to it.', 2391, 0), (431175, 'I find any sort of acting that doesn''t have any humor in it is mind-numbingly boring. ''Serious acting'' is the kind of acting that I don''t ever respond to.', 68571, 0), (431176, 'My uncle worked in emergency wards dealing with people who came in with terrible injuries. He talked about the sketch shows they would put on to lighten the atmosphere. You often find this sense of grim humor in hospitals. The injuries people are suffering are ghastly. You have to laugh at something or you''d otherwise cry.', 68572, 0), (431177, 'I find any sort of acting that doesn''t have any humor in it is mind-numbingly boring.', 68571, 0), (431178, 'There is a lack of humor in fashion. To me, it''s always been the fun, cool industry to work in, and I always wanted people to be on my side and see how much fun we really have behind the scenes.', 67999, 0), (431179, 'Somebody says, ''Do a Tom Bodett, a folksy kind of thing,'' and it sounds like something out of ''Hee Haw,'' very insulting. They turn wry humor into disparaging sarcasm, and you get what amounts to insulting advertising.', 60, 0), (431180, '''The Sopranos'' is filled with really retrograde humor. Bathroom humor, falls, stupid puns, bad jokes - infantile, adolescent stuff, but it makes me laugh.', 68573, 0), (431181, 'As I get older, my sense of humor is my biggest asset.', 68574, 0), (431182, 'I try to find humor in everything I do, because I think all great plays - even great tragedies - have enormous humor in them.', 68575, 0), (431183, 'I enjoy ''Murphy Brown,'' but I am shocked that people really like ''Married... With Children.'' These shows are toilet humor, and none of them have good characters.', 68576, 0), (431184, 'Humor is the secret into the audience''s other ranges of emotions.', 68577, 0), (431185, 'I think bands, when they''re on the road, they keep their sanity by developing an internal sense of humor.', 68578, 0), (431186, 'The humor is essentially dark for a cartoon and sophisticated. But at the same time, being a cartoon gives the writers more freedom than in a normal sitcom. It always pushes the line that, despite human failings, the Simpsons are really decent people.', 68579, 0), (431187, 'Guys usually like my sense of humor, and I am pretty down to earth. And I''m a driven person.', 68580, 0), (431188, 'I think American guys tend to be a bit more forward, a bit more chatty and open than the Brits. The Brits seem to have a darker sense of humor, though I have met some Americans who have adopted bits of the British dry sense of humor as well.', 68581, 0), (431189, 'I think people are sexy when they have a sense of humor, when they are smart, when they have some sense of style, when they are kind, when they express their own opinions, when they are creative, when they have character.', 66827, 0), (431190, 'I am a great believer that what makes our show different is the humor.', 67184, 0), (431191, 'Being a Hot Mom means being respected as a mom and a woman. And, the key to being a Hot Mom is having a sense of humor about yourself and all the crazy situations that arise.', 68582, 0), (431192, 'Sometimes I''ll be sitting with my friends; I''ll say something Koothrappali-esque and make a face. There is a lot of Koothrappali in me as a human being. A lot of mannerism, humor, mischievousness, my innocence. So I don''t know if I bring him home so much as I bring myself to him at work.', 51443, 0), (431193, 'My platform has been to reach reluctant readers. And one of the best ways I found to motivate them is to connect them with reading that interests them, to expand the definition of reading to include humor, science fiction/fantasy, nonfiction, graphic novels, wordless books, audio books and comic books.', 2214, 0), (431194, 'Without humor, I cannot go on and I doubt many of my readers would go on either. Humor is so important. I am here to have fun here with my work.', 9639, 0), (431195, 'One thing my family has shown me is that having a sense of humor is everything.', 68583, 0), (431196, 'I find humor to be the most attractive characteristic, but I certainly won''t cancel anything out, considering when you love someone you love someone, and sometimes you just can''t explain it.', 68583, 0), (431197, 'The ''Twilight'' movies are great in their own right, but they certainly don''t have any sense of humor to them.', 60918, 0), (431198, 'The main problem with films is that everybody always thinks of us as a violent people. We are not. We are spiritual. And when you show someone without a sense of humor or families, which is the way you usually see Indians in movies, then they are without a spiritual base and become subhuman.', 68584, 0), (431199, 'When a chick has a sense of humor, there''s nothing more attractive.', 68585, 0), (431200, 'I have no idea what a British sensibility or a British sense of humor is. I have no concept of what that is. I have no concept of what American sensibility is. I was born in Great Britain, but I was only there for six months, and we moved to Belgium, where I grew up.', 67547, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (431201, 'Humor has been the balm of my life, but it''s been reserved for those close to me, not part of the public Lana.', 68586, 0), (431202, 'There''s such a rich history in ''SNL'' of political humor, and I think audience members expect that from us.', 68587, 0), (431203, 'There are just certain things that turn my head. It may be a girl''s sense of humor, it may be her wit, or her belief system; it could be a lot of different things.', 68588, 0), (431204, 'I choose my actors well and get to know the quirks of their personalities - and, most of all, I share humor with them. Then I keep my eyes open when they rehearse and perform, because you never know where the next stimulation comes from.', 63524, 0), (431205, 'My family has been amazing, and they understand how blessed I am. They''ve been able to keep my sense of humor.', 68589, 0), (431206, 'It''s very hard to write humor.', 5859, 0), (431207, 'I think great humor lies in playing the truth of a situation.', 68590, 0), (431208, 'I think great humor lies in playing the truth of a situation. I see myself as a performer and that applies to a Greek drama or a modern comedy.', 68590, 0), (431209, 'I certainly didn''t say while writing ''Gossip Girl,'' ''Oh this is going to be big!'' It was really like, ''Oh god, everyone''s gong to hate these people! They''re so bratty!'' But I actually think what is so appealing about them is the humor in them.', 690, 0), (431210, 'So my humor, I''d say, comes from a mixture of lowbrow comedy shows and highbrow theater. It''s an interesting mix.', 686, 0), (431211, '''24'' is a pretty serious show - there isn''t a lot of improv that is happening. Having said that, I do play around with the delivery. A lot of the humor comes from playing a character who is very furious and really up in her own brain and in a serious situation. That is humorous to me.', 68591, 0), (431212, 'There are the horror fans that love the ''Evil Dead'' because of the humor, but I''m sure it''s not all of them. Not all horror fans love ''Evil Dead'' because of the humor, at least not me.', 68592, 0), (431213, 'I''m not just a big-haired redhead country singer who dresses flamboyantly, has this wicked sense of humor and wears rhinestones.', 68593, 0), (431214, 'A lot of people say, ''Hey, God doesn''t have a sense of humor.'' Yes, He does. God has a great sense of humor.', 53127, 0), (431215, 'The most terrible fear that anybody should have is not war, is not a disease, not cancer or heart problems or food poisoning - it''s a man or a woman without a sense of humor.', 60426, 0), (431216, 'We do not take humor seriously enough.', 2533, 0), (431217, 'I really wouldn''t want to live in America. I found New York claustrophobic and dirty. I missed England when I was there, simple things like smells and the British sense of humor.', 68594, 0), (431218, 'I like Thomas Jefferson, though he intimidated me. I thought he would have been very tough to be around. I don''t know if he had such a sense of humor.', 21173, 0), (431219, 'He has such a patronizing tone and manner, and such a sarcastic sense of humor. I found him rather brutal, a kind of elegant brutality which appealed. No, I think he came pretty much off the page.', 68595, 0), (431220, 'The script was just the best I''d read in a long time and I love the humor, which I wasn''t expecting, and I like the fact that my six year old daughter can see the show without being, you know, protected from it.', 39081, 0), (431221, 'Back in 2004, Kellie Overbey handed me her play ''Girl Talk'' to read. I fell in love with her brutally delicious humor and the fearlessly deft way in which she drew her characters. They jumped off the page and begged me to give them a space in which to stomp around.', 68596, 0), (431222, 'I think Damien Hirst is hilarious. And I think he''s a true artist. He''s not hilarious first; I think he is a real artist, and I also think he''s got an amazing sense of humor.', 68597, 0), (431223, 'Although humor is present in every one of my films, it has always been used as a way to make the darker, heavier stuff in my stories more palatable. I never set out to make ''Humpday'' a comedy.', 68598, 0), (431224, 'Putting a little time aside for clean fun and good humor is very necessary to relieve the tensions of our time.', 68599, 0), (431225, 'Americans are pragmatic, relatively uncomplicated, hearty and given to broad humor.', 59745, 0), (431226, 'One can never speak enough of the virtues, the dangers, the power of shared laughter.', 642, 0), (431227, 'People may think of Southern humor in terms of missing teeth and outhouse accidents, but the best of it is a rich vein running through the best of Southern literature.', 68385, 0), (431228, 'Robert Walker as Bruno was excellent. He had elegance and humor, and the proper fondness for his mother.', 3570, 0), (431229, 'Sometimes in the most tragic situation, something just profoundly funny happens.', 68600, 0), (431230, 'Humor is a way to deal with stresses. It is a way to cope.', 68601, 0), (431231, 'But because it was able to balance that kind of humor with a sweet story and characters you really rooted for and also got across the girls'' point of view, I''ve heard nothing but great things from younger and older females as well.', 68602, 0), (431232, 'I want everything I do to have humor in it, because it seems to me that all of life has that.', 46822, 0), (431233, 'I think it''s because it''s so different and it takes risks. Plus, it''s really smart humor. It gives the audience credit in terms of not needing to tell them when to laugh. I love that about the show. There''s no laugh track.', 68603, 0), (431234, 'Cervantes is the most important Spanish writer. But he is not the most representative of the Spanish. His irony, his sense of humor - they are too subtle to seem Spanish.', 68604, 0), (431235, 'Humor was not important only for me, humor was important for this nation for centuries, to survive, you know.', 68605, 0), (431236, 'Keep your sense of humor, my friend; if you don''t have a sense of humor it just isn''t funny anymore.', 68606, 0), (431237, 'The thing that makes ''Dirty Jobs'' different is that it''s one of the few shows that portrays work in a way that doesn''t highlight the drudgery. Instead, it highlights the humor.', 6052, 0), (431238, 'G.I. humor is similar to cop humor.', 2299, 0), (431239, 'A boy is naturally full of humor.', 68607, 0), (431240, 'Even people that I agree with can do something that would be a target for a bit of humor.', 68608, 0), (431241, 'But it was this tough little character part that I was playing, a very funny little guy that I invented over a weekend, because I realized I was not contributing to the humor of this thing. And I had to do something.', 68609, 0), (431242, 'All I try to do is as earnestly and as acutely as I can, conceive a character and try to portray this character just honestly. If the humor is within the absurdity and the awfulness of situations, then let it be seen that way.', 68610, 0), (431243, 'I''m interested not just in projects that I''ll be starring in, but producing film and TV that''s really quality and great for adults; and when I say ''great for adults,'' it doesn''t mean without humor, because I''m also interested in doing comedy.', 68611, 0), (431244, 'As people, we''re generally optimistic, no matter how disabled our lives are, and we find the humor in the darkest situations.', 68612, 0), (431245, 'I grew up in a family that was very barbed and difficult, and there was a lot of humor. None of it was painless humor. All of it was at someone else''s expense. It was kind of always about power.', 68612, 0), (431246, 'I can''t fall apart every time I mention that my mother''s gone. I actually laugh about stories or things or situations. Of course there''s a wound that will never be patched up, but I approach it with humor. Of course, I don''t overlook it and go straight for the humor, but I think we have to have humor to move forward.', 68613, 0), (431247, 'I like working on stories where I can explore the darker corners of childhood without illustrations but with humor.', 37029, 0), (431248, 'I think very long and hard about every possibly offensive joke I want to make. I really hate mean humor and would hate to make anyone reading my jokes feel truly bad.', 68614, 0), (431249, 'Men live by intervals of reason under the sovereignty of humor and passion.', 4506, 0), (431250, 'I have been definitely influenced more by Latin American writers than by any other type of writer. They are very close in terms of voice - their humor, their fatalism, their... well, that over-used term ''magical realism.'' It''s a wonderful term that''s just been used so much, we don''t know what it means anymore.', 68615, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (431251, 'Humor distorts nothing, and only false gods are laughed off their earthly pedestals.', 24996, 0), (431252, 'Humor brings insight and tolerance. Irony brings a deeper and less friendly understanding.', 24996, 0), (431253, '''Hill Street,'' because of the wacky nature of many of our characters, really allowed us to indulge a kind of cheek-to-jowl juxtaposition of high drama with very low humor.', 68616, 0), (431254, 'When you say a friend has a sense of humor do you mean that he makes you laugh, or that he can make you laugh?', 3825, 0), (431255, 'I am in the Master of Professional Writing program teaching Humor Writing, Literary and Dramatic.', 68617, 0), (431256, 'I''m not really big on slapstick humor. I like gentle humor.', 57967, 0), (431257, 'If you can understand the humor in the drawing part you''ll probably get the humor in the audio part.', 68618, 0), (431258, 'Humor is healing.', 68619, 0), (431259, 'A lot of my humor centers on the act of telling jokes and I think this can prevent certain audiences from suspending their feeling of disbelief. It might piss a few people off, but I can''t help it.', 68620, 0), (431260, 'The quickest way to defuse fear or insecurity or anger is usually humor. I think comics figure that out quickly, and, once you figure it out, you think, ''Hey, if I can do this and get paid, that would be kind of cool.''', 67394, 0), (431261, 'I love ''Dexter.'' The dark sense of humor is wonderful.', 9814, 0), (431262, 'John Lennon, who was a good friend of mine, he had one of the best senses of humor of any human being. And Keith Richards, fantastic sense of humor. They were smart, sharp. They had their own thoughts on matters.', 68063, 0), (431263, 'The key to gallows humor is to make the joke, no matter how certain the gallows is.', 68621, 0), (431264, 'In sitcoms, the women are so beautiful, understanding and well-bred. They have humor, but sort of display it with a twinkle of the eye and not a guffaw. But there''s no juice in that for me.', 67942, 0), (431265, 'There''s public humor, and there''s private humor, and they''re all appropriate in their own way, and you shouldn''t - just as you wouldn''t have a megaphone and say certain things that you would say around your friends - things that are perfectly all right within your close social group with whom you share a certain context.', 68622, 0), (431266, 'Humor levels the playing field. I understood that early on - that was something I had.', 68622, 0), (431267, 'The interesting thing about humor is that in humor, you - in logic, something is A or not A. In humor, it''s both A and not A.', 68622, 0), (431268, 'The line between humor and bad taste is your audience, in which some people will find everything offensive, and some people will find nothing offensive, but the truth is that most humor originates in what would be called bad taste.', 68622, 0), (431269, 'One question about a joke is, how well is the strangeness of the situation resolved? At ''The New Yorker'', we retain a lot of incongruity, tapping the playful part of the mind - Monty Python-type stuff. We also try to use humor as a vehicle for communicating ideas. Not editorial comment, but observation.', 68622, 0), (431270, 'Humor - I see it as a survival skill.', 45371, 0), (431271, 'Humor is the truth wit is an exaggeration of the truth. ', 35728, 0), (431272, 'Probably it is impossible for humor to be ever a revolutionary weapon. Candide can do little more than generate irony.', 13991, 0), (431273, 'I''m a great admirer of Primo Levi''s work. It''s always mind-boggling, the idea of how much pain people can endure and still come back from the edge with a sense of humor, with this tremendous animal desire we have to get on with life.', 31020, 0), (431274, 'At NBC I wasn''t really sure if the grandparents were going to get my sense of humor on a particular topic.', 68623, 0), (431275, 'I suppose I look for humor in most situations because it humanizes things; it makes a character much more three-dimensional if there''s some kind of humor. Not necessarily laugh-out-loud type of stuff, just a sense that there is a humorous edge to things. I do like that.', 68624, 0), (431276, 'All the people who follow me on Twitter know my sense of humor. I sometimes forget the blogosphere will give it more weight than I intended.', 68625, 0), (431277, 'I love doing comedy. You don''t get many good comedy scripts. They''re rare. But, I do love playing comedy. Even in drama, I like to try to find the humor because I think it''s very human.', 68624, 0), (431278, 'Sense of humor is important in life, not just in clothing. How boring to live a life in beige.', 68626, 0), (431279, 'Candidates should be extremely cautious in displaying a sense of humor. If he or she tells a joke with a point, there is almost certain to be some minority group offended.', 68627, 0), (431280, 'I''m a novelist first, and I wrote a bunch of books, and everything I write, I just find people are more interesting when there''s an element of humor to it.', 462, 0), (431281, 'My father was an electrical engineer who worked at Westinghouse in Pittsburgh. When I was growing up, my mother wrote humor columns for the local paper. She was the Erma Bombeck of Murrysville, Pa.', 68628, 0), (431282, 'Set your compass to beauty, humor, and grief; stay the course no matter what, and I''ll support you with everything I''ve got.', 67234, 0), (431283, 'I find intelligence sexy. I find a sense of humor sexy. I find sensitivity sexy.', 68629, 0), (431284, 'If someone is genuine, compassionate and kind, that is a turn-on. A sense of humor is a huge turn on, and that goes hand in hand with intelligence.', 68630, 0), (431285, 'Stand-up comics reflect less of a visual humor and more of a commentary.', 79, 0), (431286, 'Funny is a good foil. Humor is illuminating, and it also gives you power.', 68419, 0), (431287, 'I''ve learned to have a sense of humor about myself. Lord knows everyone else does!', 68631, 0), (431288, 'We have always had gross humor. But we try for funny, not gross.', 39824, 0), (431289, 'I never wanted to do observational humor because I never wanted to tell people what they were seeing.', 68415, 0), (431290, 'The first glass is for myself, the second for my friends, the third for good humor, and the forth for my enemies.', 19164, 0), (431291, 'Lesbian humor isn''t trying to sell anything, it doesn''t have to sell out. Coming out as a lesbian onstage is still a very political act; if it weren''t, more women would do it.', 68632, 0), (431292, 'Humor is the instinct for taking pain playfully.', 49510, 0), (431293, 'It is the ability to take a joke, not make one, that proves you have a sense of humor.', 49510, 0), (431294, 'We are, in the comics, the last frontier of good, wholesome family humor and entertainment.', 1672, 0), (431295, 'A humorist is a person who feels bad, but who feels good about it.', 21321, 0), (431296, 'If you approach Cannes with a sense of humor, nothing is that bad. You have to take it for what it is; otherwise, it''s silly.', 68633, 0), (431297, 'Perhaps naively I thought people understand what humor was, that it was invented by the human race to cope with the dark areas of life, problems and terrors.', 68634, 0), (431298, 'I like to think my sense of humor is sort of smart and dumb at the same time. I like to work on multiple levels - smart and dumb, funny and sad, profound and mundane, cynical and hopeful.', 68635, 0), (431299, 'It used to take me forever to read and comprehend stuff, so I decided not to make the ''Captain Underpants'' books too challenging. Don''t get me wrong - the humor and ideas are often sophisticated - but the books aren''t hard to read. I wanted kids who hate reading to find these books irresistible.', 68390, 0), (431300, 'A good sense of humor will get you everywhere.', 68636, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (431301, 'A strong sense of humor, a really awesome personality, and maturity is also really important in a boyfriend. I tend to only be attracted to older guys for that reason. I just love guys who have a really strong sense of who they are.', 68637, 0), (431302, 'Comedy has to be based on truth. You take the truth and you put a little curlicue at the end.', 68638, 0), (431303, 'I think films about men are often about characters who don''t want to express their feelings. You''re supposed to kind of admire them for not expressing their feelings. And I feel that''s a bit dull. Women''s stories often have stronger emotional content, which I enjoy doing. What I really love doing is mixing that with humor.', 68639, 0), (431304, 'Hope for the best, survive the worst, find humor wherever you can.', 68640, 0), (431305, 'This I conceive to be the chemical function of humor: to change the character of our thought.', 1317, 0), (431306, 'One has to develop a sense of humor to cope.', 68641, 0), (431307, 'I grew up as a very sarcastic person. I was always the class clown, and to date girls, I had to be really funny. I was really skinny growing up. I was so thin, I had to run around in the shower to get wet. That kind of thin. So I always had to rely on humor and sarcasm.', 68642, 0), (431308, 'Gags die, humor doesn''t.', 13069, 0), (431309, 'It never seems to occur to some people, that, like beauty, a sense of humor may sometimes be fatal.', 6974, 0), (431310, 'The sense of humor has other things to do than to make itself conspicuous in the act of laughter.', 62853, 0), (431311, 'So once I thought of the villain with a sense of humor, I began to think of a name and the name "the Joker" immediately came to mind. There was the association with the Joker in the deck of cards, and I probably yelled literally, ''Eureka!'' because I knew I had the name and the image at the same time.', 68643, 0), (431312, 'Humor is merely tragedy standing on its head with its pants torn.', 59066, 0), (431313, 'I think humor is a very serious thing. I use it as a way of weakening the reader''s defenses so that I can more easily take him to something more.', 65118, 0), (431314, 'If you look at ''The Best Man,'' there''s a lot of humor in that, but I never consider that movie a comedy. I felt that it was a drama with comedic elements and comedic parts to it.', 68644, 0), (431315, 'People ask me what the most important thing to take on the race is, and I always say it''s a sense of humor. If you''ve got nothing but a sense of humor, you will survive.', 68645, 0), (431316, 'There is humor in the specter of the worst disaster in our nation''s history. All I have to do is sweep away the debris of shock to find it.', 17468, 0), (431317, 'I value humor, kindness, and the ability to tell a good story far more than money, status, or the kind of car someone drives.', 1416, 0), (431318, 'I need to end up with someone who is strong, intelligent, independent, someone I really admire - sensitive, sensuous, warm, a sense of humor.', 68646, 0), (431319, 'Our humor turns our anger into a fine art.', 68647, 0), (431320, 'There is no defense against adverse fortune which is so effectual as an habitual sense of humor.', 62370, 0), (431321, 'I can''t live without a sense of humor. I need to be laughing and entertained at all times.', 68648, 0), (431322, 'Sometimes I make myself laugh, but that''s because I appreciate my sense of humor.', 68649, 0), (431323, 'Incongruity, they say, is one of the main ingredients of humor. Maybe it''s because everybody can feel superior to me. I honestly don''t know.', 68650, 0), (431324, 'One doesn''t have a sense of humor. It has you.', 51804, 0), (431325, 'All my jobs have been with food in one way or another since 1948. My parents were in the hotel business, and I just loved the warm hearted people who worked so hard with such good humor.', 22441, 0), (431326, 'Humor is an affirmation of dignity, a declaration of man''s superiority to all that befalls him.', 16881, 0), (431327, 'I love the Swedish people for their detective novels, their archipelago, their sense of humor, their carbonated vodka, and most especially, for their wonderful hospitality.', 68651, 0), (431328, 'You need to talk about sex with a sense of humor, especially because sex is a sensitive area for a lot of people.', 68652, 0), (431329, 'The two most powerful warriors are patience and time.', 93, 0), (431330, 'Sometimes by losing a battle you find a new way to win the war.', 64643, 0), (431331, 'We don''t even know how strong we are until we are forced to bring that hidden strength forward. In times of tragedy, of war, of necessity, people do amazing things. The human capacity for survival and renewal is awesome.', 441, 0), (431332, 'You must not fight too often with one enemy, or you will teach him all your art of war.', 1702, 0), (431333, 'Know thy self, know thy enemy. A thousand battles, a thousand victories.', 1026, 0), (431334, 'Even today we raise our hand against our brother... We have perfected our weapons, our conscience has fallen asleep, and we have sharpened our ideas to justify ourselves as if it were normal we continue to sow destruction, pain, death. Violence and war lead only to death.', 6248, 0), (431335, 'I must study politics and war that my sons may have liberty to study mathematics and philosophy.', 4179, 0), (431336, 'Build me a son, O Lord, who will be strong enough to know when he is weak, and brave enough to face himself when he is afraid, one who will be proud and unbending in honest defeat, and humble and gentle in victory.', 2273, 0), (431337, 'The object of war is not to die for your country but to make the other bastard die for his.', 57896, 0), (431338, 'War does not determine who is right - only who is left.', 95, 0), (431339, 'A really strong woman accepts the war she went through and is ennobled by her scars.', 68653, 0), (431340, 'The soldier above all others prays for peace, for it is the soldier who must suffer and bear the deepest wounds and scars of war.', 2273, 0), (431341, 'Battle is the most magnificent competition in which a human being can indulge. It brings out all that is best it removes all that is base. All men are afraid in battle. The coward is the one who lets his fear overcome his sense of duty. Duty is the essence of manhood. ', 57896, 0), (431342, 'Politics is war without bloodshed while war is politics with bloodshed.', 15795, 0), (431343, 'War is never a lasting solution for any problem.', 1798, 0), (431344, 'To be prepared for war is one of the most effective means of preserving peace.', 3161, 0), (431345, 'Victorious warriors win first and then go to war, while defeated warriors go to war first and then seek to win.', 1026, 0), (431346, 'The art of war teaches us to rely not on the likelihood of the enemy''s not coming, but on our own readiness to receive him; not on the chance of his not attacking, but rather on the fact that we have made our position unassailable.', 1026, 0), (431347, 'Mankind must put an end to war before war puts an end to mankind.', 1680, 0), (431348, 'No event in American history is more misunderstood than the Vietnam War. It was misreported then, and it is misremembered now.', 9695, 0), (431349, 'Older men declare war. But it is the youth that must fight and die.', 7777, 0), (431350, 'The Cold War isn''t thawing; it is burning with a deadly heat. Communism isn''t sleeping; it is, as always, plotting, scheming, working, fighting.', 9695, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (431351, 'Thus, what is of supreme importance in war is to attack the enemy''s strategy.', 1026, 0), (431352, 'During the time men live without a common power to keep them all in awe, they are in that conditions called war; and such a war, as if of every man, against every man.', 2593, 0), (431353, 'It was my duty to shoot the enemy, and I don''t regret it. My regrets are for the people I couldn''t save: Marines, soldiers, buddies. I''m not naive, and I don''t romanticize war. The worst moments of my life have come as a SEAL. But I can stand before God with a clear conscience about doing my job.', 2455, 0), (431354, 'European nations began World War I with a glamorous vision of war, only to be psychologically shattered by the realities of the trenches. The experience changed the way people referred to the glamour of battle; they treated it no longer as a positive quality but as a dangerous illusion.', 68175, 0), (431355, 'The condition of man... is a condition of war of everyone against everyone.', 2593, 0), (431356, 'In an era in which war and terrorism - at home and abroad - are often based on racial, religious and ethnic differences, rediscovering the wisdom of love and compassion may help us increase our survival at a time when an increasingly divided country and world so badly need it.', 45749, 0), (431357, 'I joined the army on my seventeenth birthday, full of the romance of war after having read a lot of World War I British poetry and having seen a lot of post-World War II films. I thought the romantic presentations of war influenced my joining and my presentation of war to my younger siblings.', 11749, 0), (431358, 'We shall defend our island, whatever the cost may be, we shall fight on the beaches, we shall fight on the landing grounds, we shall fight in the fields and in the streets, we shall fight in the hills; we shall never surrender.', 3621, 0), (431359, 'Bad things do happen in the world, like war, natural disasters, disease. But out of those situations always arise stories of ordinary people doing extraordinary things.', 68654, 0), (431360, 'Brave men rejoice in adversity, just as brave soldiers triumph in war.', 65434, 0), (431361, 'I saw courage both in the Vietnam War and in the struggle to stop it. I learned that patriotism includes protest, not just military service.', 16042, 0), (431362, 'We owe our World War II veterans - and all our veterans - a debt we can never fully repay.', 68655, 0), (431363, 'The atomic bomb made the prospect of future war unendurable. It has led us up those last few steps to the mountain pass and beyond there is a different country. ', 7792, 0), (431364, 'Quickness is the essence of the war.', 1026, 0), (431365, 'I am tired and sick of war. Its glory is all moonshine. It is only those who have neither fired a shot nor heard the shrieks and groans of the wounded who cry aloud for blood, for vengeance, for desolation. War is hell.', 65193, 0), (431366, 'The lesson of the Cold War is that against nuclear weapons, only nuclear weapons can hold the peace.', 68656, 0), (431367, 'The more you sweat in peace, the less you bleed in war.', 4137, 0), (431368, 'The art of war is simple enough. Find out where your enemy is. Get at him as soon as you can. Strike him as hard as you can, and keep moving on.', 9689, 0), (431369, 'What a cruel thing war is... to fill our hearts with hatred instead of love for our neighbors.', 1924, 0), (431370, 'My father was very disappointed by war and fighting. And he thought language could help us out of cycles of revenge and animosity. And so, as a journalist, he always found himself asking lots of questions and trying to gather information. He was always very clear to underscore the fact that Jewish people and Arab people were brother and sister.', 8684, 0), (431371, 'There is no avoiding war it can only be postponed to the advantage of others. ', 947, 0), (431372, 'World War I was not inevitable, as many historians say. It could have been avoided, and it was a diplomatically botched negotiation.', 3083, 0), (431373, 'Be at war with your vices, at peace with your neighbors, and let every new year find you a better man.', 1077, 0), (431374, 'Our Generation has had no Great war, no Great Depression. Our war is spiritual. Our depression is our lives.', 30, 0), (431375, 'Not all moral issues have the same moral weight as abortion and euthanasia. There may be legitimate diversity of opinion even among Catholics about waging war and applying the death penalty, but not... with regard to abortion and euthanasia.', 856, 0), (431376, 'My first wish is to see this plague of mankind, war, banished from the earth.', 3161, 0), (431377, 'Communism has never come to power in a country that was not disrupted by war or corruption, or both.', 1680, 0), (431378, 'We should keep on going along the path of globalization. Globalization is good... when trade stops, war comes.', 66598, 0), (431379, 'Ten soldiers wisely led will beat a hundred without a head.', 542, 0), (431380, 'When we are sick, we want an uncommon doctor; when we have a construction job to do, we want an uncommon engineer, and when we are at war, we want an uncommon general. It is only when we get into politics that we are satisfied with the common man.', 7777, 0), (431381, 'The great questions of the day will not be settled by means of speeches and majority decisions but by iron and blood.', 4746, 0), (431382, 'A quality education grants us the ability to fight the war on ignorance and poverty.', 41313, 0), (431383, 'There are two problems for our species'' survival - nuclear war and environmental catastrophe - and we''re hurtling towards them. Knowingly.', 1955, 0), (431384, 'I had a very strong feeling about the Vietnam War, and I had a strong feeling about participating in it. The military draft was in place, I was summoned for a physical exam, and I was either going to be classified as fit for military service or make my objection to it. So I made my objection to it.', 12392, 0), (431385, 'I''m a Canadian. Outside Canada I carry the flag. Canadian nationalism isn''t as insidious as American nationalism, though. It''s good natured. It''s all about maple syrup, not war.', 67707, 0), (431386, 'As a soldier, I survived World War I when most of my comrades did not.', 17580, 0), (431387, 'Great is the guilt of an unnecessary war.', 4179, 0), (431388, 'The United Nations'' founders understood that decisions affecting war and peace should happen only by consensus, and with America''s consent, the veto by Security Council permanent members was enshrined in the United Nations Charter. The profound wisdom of this has underpinned the stability of international relations for decades.', 50689, 0), (431389, 'I covered the Vietnam War. I remember the lies that were told, the lives that were lost - and the shock when, twenty years after the war ended, former Defense Secretary Robert S. McNamara admitted he knew it was a mistake all along.', 9501, 0), (431390, 'This union has been divided in like a civil war - brother against brother - sister against sister. And I''m pulling it together. We''ve already seen evidence of that in New York, in Pennsylvania, in California. The first thing is we have to get on the same page. We have to be united in one cause.', 68657, 0), (431391, 'Serious sport has nothing to do with fair play. It is bound up with hatred, jealousy, boastfulness, disregard of all rules and sadistic pleasure in witnessing violence. In other words, it is war minus the shooting.', 521, 0), (431392, 'Something is wanting, and something must be done, or we shall be involved in all the horror of failure, and civil war without a prospect of its termination.', 68658, 0), (431393, 'We make war that we may live in peace.', 1116, 0), (431394, 'We live in an age, in an era where there is so much negativity, there is so much violence in the world, there is so much unrest and people are at war, that I wanted to promote the word love and red signifies love.', 1620, 0), (431395, 'War is cruelty. There is no use trying to reform it. The crueler it is, the sooner it will be over.', 65193, 0), (431396, 'World War II is the greatest drama in human history, the biggest war ever and a true battle of good and evil. I imagine writers will continue to get stories from it, and readers will continue to love them, for many more years.', 9110, 0), (431397, 'There is no hunting like the hunting of man, and those who have hunted armed men long enough and liked it, never care for anything else thereafter.', 110, 0), (431398, 'An asteroid or a supervolcano could certainly destroy us, but we also face risks the dinosaurs never saw: An engineered virus, nuclear war, inadvertent creation of a micro black hole, or some as-yet-unknown technology could spell the end of us.', 10864, 0), (431399, 'Marriage is an adventure, like going to war.', 67663, 0), (431400, 'The problems we face now - poverty and violence at home, war and destruction abroad - will last only as long as we continue relying on the same politicians who created them in the first place.', 64643, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (431401, 'The most terrifying moment in my life was October 1962, during the Cuban Missile Crisis. I did not know all the facts - we have learned only recently how close we were to war - but I knew enough to make me tremble.', 49481, 0), (431402, 'The day that the balance between the two sections of the country - the slaveholding States and the non-slaveholding States - is destroyed is a day that will not be far removed from political revolution, anarchy, civil war, and widespread disaster.', 63147, 0), (431403, 'There is always inequality in life. Some men are killed in a war and some men are wounded and some men never leave the country. Life is unfair.', 1680, 0), (431404, 'You can no more win a war than you can win an earthquake.', 16068, 0), (431405, 'Empathy is really the opposite of spiritual meanness. It''s the capacity to understand that every war is both won and lost. And that someone else''s pain is as meaningful as your own.', 679, 0), (431406, 'World War I broke out largely because of an arms race, and World War II because of the lack of an arms race.', 62777, 0), (431407, 'If men can develop weapons that are so terrifying as to make the thought of global war include almost a sentence for suicide, you would think that man''s intelligence and his comprehension... would include also his ability to find a peaceful solution.', 2119, 0), (431408, 'Terrorism has become the systematic weapon of a war that knows no borders or seldom has a face.', 68659, 0), (431409, 'What gunpowder did for war the printing press has done for the mind.', 24952, 0), (431410, 'I have not yet begun to fight!', 29366, 0), (431411, 'Every war when it comes, or before it comes, is represented not as a war but as an act of self-defense against a homicidal maniac.', 521, 0), (431412, 'Remember that politics, colonialism, imperialism and war also originate in the human brain.', 68660, 0), (431413, 'There are only two sides to this question. Every man must be for the United States or against it. There can be no neutrals in this war only patriots and traitors. ', 68661, 0), (431414, 'War is not only a matter of equipment, artillery, group troops or air force; it is largely a matter of spirit, or morale.', 67633, 0), (431415, 'When I see the Confederate flag, I see the attempt to raise an empire in slavery. It really, really is that simple. I don''t understand how anybody with any sort of education on the Civil War can see anything else.', 1309, 0), (431416, 'For me, true beauty has nothing to do with wrinkles and everything to do with the fact that my maternal grandmother raised five children just after the war and remained a fighter throughout her life. True beauty is the slick of red lipstick my paternal grandmother would put on before going to church on Sunday.', 47394, 0), (431417, 'Morality binds people into groups. It gives us tribalism, it gives us genocide, war, and politics. But it also gives us heroism, altruism, and sainthood.', 2838, 0), (431418, 'Organize, agitate, educate, must be our war cry.', 2137, 0), (431419, 'So I would say God hates war, but God loves every soldier.', 710, 0), (431420, 'In war, events of importance are the result of trivial causes.', 62623, 0), (431421, 'We have but one flag, one country; let us stand together. We may differ in color, but not in sentiment. Many things have been said about me which are wrong, and which white and black persons here, who stood by me through the war, can contradict.', 15993, 0), (431422, 'Life on Earth is at the ever-increasing risk of being wiped out by a disaster, such as sudden global nuclear war, a genetically engineered virus or other dangers we have not yet thought of.', 1222, 0), (431423, 'The art of war is of vital importance to the state. It is a matter of life and death, a road either to safety or to ruin. Hence it is a subject of inquiry which can on no account be neglected.', 1026, 0), (431424, 'The negative effects of combat were nightmares, and I''d get jumpy around certain noises and stuff, but you''d have that after a car accident or a bad divorce. Life''s filled with trauma. You don''t need to go to war to find it; it''s going to find you. We all deal with it, and the effects go away after awhile. At least they did for me.', 14639, 0), (431425, 'In war, whichever side may call itself the victor, there are no winners, but all are losers.', 68662, 0), (431426, 'From the neck up is where you win or lose the battle. It''s the art of war. You have to lock yourself in and strategise your mindset. That''s why boxers go to training camps: to shut down the noise and really zone in.', 68663, 0), (431427, 'When the tyrant has disposed of foreign enemies by conquest or treaty, and there is nothing more to fear from them, then he is always stirring up some war or other, in order that the people may require a leader.', 51, 0), (431428, 'Anyone who has ever looked into the glazed eyes of a soldier dying on the battlefield will think hard before starting a war.', 4746, 0), (431429, 'Like Nemesis of Greek tragedy, the central problem of America after the Civil War, as before, was the black man: those four million souls whom the nation had used and degraded, and on whom the South had built an oligarchy similar to the colonial imperialism of today, erected on cheap colored labor and raising raw material for manufacture.', 3227, 0), (431430, 'I hate war as only a soldier who has lived it can, only as one who has seen its brutality, its futility, its stupidity.', 2119, 0), (431431, 'The time to take counsel of your fears is before you make an important battle decision. That''s the time to listen to every fear you can imagine! When you have collected all the facts and fears and made your decision, turn off all your fears and go ahead!', 57896, 0), (431432, 'People never lie so much as after a hunt, during a war or before an election.', 4746, 0), (431433, 'To hold a pen is to be at war.', 808, 0), (431434, 'Establishing lasting peace is the work of education all politics can do is keep us out of war. ', 11408, 0), (431435, 'Do not try to do too much with your own hands. Better the Arabs do it tolerably than you do it perfectly. It is their war, and you are to help them, not to win it for them.', 16259, 0), (431436, 'On the last morning of Virginia''s bloodiest year since the Civil War, I built a fire and sat facing a window of darkness where at sunrise I knew I would find the sea.', 1698, 0), (431437, 'It is an unfortunate fact that we can secure peace only by preparing for war.', 1680, 0), (431438, 'In peace, sons bury their fathers. In war, fathers bury their sons.', 1863, 0), (431439, 'This was not an act of terrorism, but it was an act of war.', 2358, 0), (431440, 'Peace is not a relationship of nations. It is a condition of mind brought about by a serenity of soul. Peace is not merely the absence of war. It is also a state of mind. Lasting peace can come only to peaceful people.', 8325, 0), (431441, 'I find capitalism repugnant. It is filthy, it is gross, it is alienating... because it causes war, hypocrisy and competition.', 3470, 0), (431442, 'The world knows that America will never start a war. This generation of Americans has had enough of war and hate... we want to build a world of peace where the weak are secure and the strong are just.', 1680, 0), (431443, 'The most important thing in our war preparations is to teach all our people to hate U.S. imperialism. Otherwise, we will not be able to defeat the U.S. imperialists who boast of their technological superiority.', 68664, 0), (431444, 'I thought the Vietnam war was an utter, unmitigated disaster, so it was very hard for me to say anything good about it.', 68665, 0), (431445, 'The philosophy of protectionism is a philosophy of war.', 9998, 0), (431446, 'We must eliminate all nuclear weapons in order to eliminate the grave risk they pose to our world. This will require persistent efforts by all countries and peoples. A nuclear war would affect everyone, and all have a stake in preventing this nightmare.', 21719, 0), (431447, 'The Vietnam War was a great tragedy for our country. And it is now far enough away so that one can study without using the slogans to see what''s really happened.', 2393, 0), (431448, 'God is day and night, winter and summer, war and peace, surfeit and hunger.', 1083, 0), (431449, 'War may sometimes be a necessary evil. But no matter how necessary, it is always an evil, never a good. We will not learn how to live together in peace by killing each other''s children.', 1229, 0), (431450, 'You cannot simultaneously prevent and prepare for war.', 104, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (431451, 'More than an end to war, we want an end to the beginning of all wars - yes, an end to this brutal, inhuman and thoroughly impractical method of settling the differences between governments.', 2261, 0), (431452, 'War - An act of violence whose object is to constrain the enemy, to accomplish our will.', 3161, 0), (431453, 'War is the greatest plague that can afflict humanity, it destroys religion, it destroys states, it destroys families. Any scourge is preferable to it.', 1746, 0), (431454, 'In many parts of the world, especially Pakistan and Afghanistan, terrorism, war and conflict stop children to go to their schools. We are really tired of these wars. Women and children are suffering.', 1851, 0), (431455, 'War is the continuation of politics by other means.', 2677, 0), (431456, 'Germany was beaten after World War I, but it didn''t take long for it to rise again as a much more malignant threat. The end of World War II was not to be a compromise; it was to come about from the total annihilation of the enemies'' ability and will to make war.', 68666, 0), (431457, 'I had seen people who had lost everything and everyone they loved to war, famine, and natural disasters.', 10320, 0), (431458, 'The war on drugs is a war against the communities.', 40169, 0), (431459, 'An Atheist believes that a hospital should be built instead of a church. An atheist believes that deed must be done instead of prayer said. An atheist strives for involvement in life and not escape into death. He wants disease conquered, poverty vanished, war eliminated.', 10467, 0), (431460, 'The sailor''s life is at the best a life of danger. He pursues honor on the mountain wave and finds it in the battle and in the storm, and never did more distinguished chivalry display itself than in the conduct of our seamen during the late war.', 68667, 0), (431461, 'There has never been a protracted war from which a country has benefited.', 1026, 0), (431462, 'No matter what you think about the Iraq war, there is one thing we can all agree on for the next days - we have to salute the courage and bravery of those who are risking their lives to vote and those brave Iraqi and American soldiers fighting to protect their right to vote.', 66567, 0), (431463, 'I have never advocated war except as a means of peace.', 9689, 0), (431464, 'I will not play tug o'' war. I''d rather play hug o'' war. Where everyone hugs instead of tugs, Where everyone giggles and rolls on the rug, Where everyone kisses, and everyone grins, and everyone cuddles, and everyone wins.', 79, 0), (431465, 'Secret operations are essential in war upon them the army relies to make its every move. ', 1026, 0), (431466, 'Make no mistake, adolescence is a war. No one gets out unscathed.', 439, 0), (431467, 'Even philosophers will praise war as ennobling mankind, forgetting the Greek who said: ''War is bad in that it begets more evil than it kills.''', 1275, 0), (431468, 'Humanity should question itself, once more, about the absurd and always unfair phenomenon of war, on whose stage of death and pain only remain standing the negotiating table that could and should have prevented it.', 66871, 0), (431469, 'We find that the Romans owed the conquest of the world to no other cause than continual military training, exact observance of discipline in their camps, and unwearied cultivation of the other arts of war.', 68668, 0), (431470, 'Going to war without France is like going hunting without an accordion.', 4137, 0), (431471, 'Black Lives Matter is the ultimate divisive movement. They aren''t shy about what they don''t like, which is western civilization, capitalism, and the rule of law. They really dislike the police, and certainly get the credit for the war between black men and police.', 8420, 0), (431472, 'I know that war and mayhem run in our blood. I refuse to believe that they must dominate our lives. We humans are animals, too, but animals with amazing powers of rationality, morality, society. We can use our strength and courage not to savage each other, but to defend our highest purposes.', 68669, 0), (431473, 'It is good that war is so horrible, or we might grow to like it.', 1924, 0), (431474, 'It just seems to me that the world''s kind of a mess, and the more messy it gets, the more interested I am in escapist fare. Having a good time is something that isn''t about the war in Iraq or the Asian flu or the Kyoto protocol - things that are horribly depressing to consider in our real lives. I''m eager to get away from them.', 68670, 0), (431475, 'World War II ended the Great Depression with one of the great public-private industrial collaborations in the history of man.', 19516, 0), (431476, 'In time of war the laws are silent.', 1306, 0), (431477, 'In 1968, America was a wounded nation. The wounds were moral ones; the Vietnam War and three summers of inner-city riots had inflicted them on the national soul, challenging Americans'' belief that they were a uniquely noble and honorable people.', 51919, 0), (431478, 'World War II, the atomic bomb, the Cold War, made it hard for Americans to continue their optimism.', 16382, 0), (431479, 'Ever since World War I, superior force is no longer measured in terms of men or horses, but in the means to wreak destruction.', 68671, 0), (431480, 'A pint of sweat, saves a gallon of blood.', 57896, 0), (431481, 'If we are to teach real peace in this world, and if we are to carry on a real war against war, we shall have to begin with the children.', 32, 0), (431482, 'I think Islam has been hijacked by the idea that all Muslims are terrorists; that Islam is about hate, about war, about jihad - I think that hijacks the spirituality and beauty that exists within Islam. I believe in allowing Islam to be seen in context and in its entirety and being judged on what it really is, not what you think it is.', 68672, 0), (431483, 'We''ve persevered because of a belief we share with the Iraqi people - a belief that out of the ashes of war, a new beginning could be born in this cradle of civilization. Through this remarkable chapter in the history of the United States and Iraq, we have met our responsibility. Now, it''s time to turn the page.', 1693, 0), (431484, 'No one ever said that fighting the war against terrorism and defending our homeland would be easy. So let''s support our troops, law enforcement workers, and our mission to keep our nation and our children safe in the days and years to come.', 68673, 0), (431485, 'After two world wars, the collapse of fascism, nazism, communism and colonialism and the end of the cold war, humanity has entered a new phase of its history.', 10607, 0), (431486, 'The critical importance of honest journalism and a free flowing, respectful national conversation needs to be had in our country. But it is being buried as collateral damage in a war whose battles include political correctness and ideological orthodoxy.', 68674, 0), (431487, 'The Founders who crafted our Constitution and Bill of Rights were careful to draft a Constitution of limited powers - one that would protect Americans'' liberty at all times - both in war, and in peace.', 11414, 0), (431488, 'Only the dead have seen the end of the war.', 2683, 0), (431489, 'War is an ugly thing, but not the ugliest of things. The decayed and degraded state of moral and patriotic feeling which thinks that nothing is worth war is much worse.', 1880, 0), (431490, 'One of the good things about the way the Gulf War ended in 1991 is, you''d see the Vietnam veterans marching with the Gulf War veterans.', 27772, 0), (431491, 'There is so much that must be done in a civilized barbarism like war.', 1646, 0), (431492, 'The best weapon against an enemy is another enemy.', 11, 0), (431493, 'Ours is a world of nuclear giants and ethical infants. We know more about war that we know about peace, more about killing that we know about living.', 49153, 0), (431494, 'Peace has its victories no less than war, but it doesn''t have as many monuments to unveil.', 14120, 0), (431495, 'With the end of the cold war, all the ''isms'' of the 20th century - Fascism, Nazism, Communism and the evil of apartheid-ism - have failed. Except one. Only democracy has shown itself true the help of all mankind.', 66144, 0), (431496, 'In 1953, after the armistice ending the Korean War, South Korea lay in ruins. President Eisenhower was eager to put an end to hostilities that had left his predecessor deeply unpopular, and the war ended in an uneasy stalemate.', 68675, 0), (431497, 'The government has a history of not treating people fairly, from the internment of Japanese Americans in World War II to African-Americans in the Civil Rights era.', 67555, 0), (431498, 'The first and most imperative necessity in war is money, for money means everything else - men, guns, ammunition.', 65659, 0), (431499, 'Fortune, which has a great deal of power in other matters but especially in war, can bring about great changes in a situation through very slight forces.', 62623, 0), (431500, 'It is not enough to say we must not wage war. It is necessary to love peace and sacrifice for it.', 21767, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (431501, 'We were emerging from the period of war, of uniforms, of women-soldiers built like boxers. I drew women-flowers, soft shoulders, fine waists like liana and wide skirts like corolla.', 18060, 0), (431502, 'I worked night and day for twelve years to prevent the war, but I could not. The North was mad and blind, would not let us govern ourselves, and so the war came.', 16075, 0), (431503, 'Love has its place, as does hate. Peace has its place, as does war. Mercy has its place, as do cruelty and revenge.', 67417, 0), (431504, 'Nullification means insurrection and war and the other states have a right to put it down. ', 2245, 0), (431505, 'When all the world is overcharged with inhabitants, then the last remedy of all is war, which provideth for every man, by victory or death.', 2593, 0), (431506, 'There''s something brave and touching about game girls of all ages keeping themselves smart in hard times - one thinks of those wonderful women during World War II drawing stocking seams in eyebrow pencil up the back of legs stained with gravy browning because nylons were so hard to get hold of.', 28504, 0), (431507, 'The first time I saw nitroglycerine was in the beginning of the Crimean War. Professor Zinin in St. Petersburg exhibited some to my father and me, and struck some on an anvil to show that only the part touched by the hammer exploded without spreading.', 31009, 0), (431508, 'I was hooked on aviation, made model airplanes, and never thought I would be able to fly myself. It cost too much. But then World War II came along and changed all that.', 14739, 0), (431509, 'The first World War in so many ways shaped the 20th century and really remade our world for the worse.', 19809, 0), (431510, 'Peace for us means the destruction of Israel. We are preparing for an all-out war, a war which will last for generations.', 68676, 0), (431511, 'The Cold War is over but Cold War thinking survives.', 49481, 0), (431512, 'If you want to fight a war on drugs, sit down at your own kitchen table and talk to your own children.', 68677, 0), (431513, 'One of the lessons learned during the Vietnam War was that the depiction of wounded soldiers, of coffins stacked higher than their living guards, had a negative effect on the viewing public. The military in Iraq specifically banned the photographing of wounded soldiers and coffins, thus sanitizing this terrible and bloody conflict.', 11749, 0), (431514, 'No one has the right to ignite a war and lead an occupation and armies to conquer people, invading them and make them suffer all kinds of torture, murder, expulsion, displacement, bombing and terrorism by different lethal prohibited weapons and then come and speak as the savior of the people or a defender of their rights.', 68678, 0), (431515, 'In time of war, truth is always replaced by propaganda.', 37323, 0), (431516, 'It is important to emphasize that guerrilla warfare is a war of the masses, a war of the people. The guerrilla band is an armed nucleus, the fighting vanguard of the people. It draws its great force from the mass of the people themselves.', 68679, 0), (431517, 'I am not only a pacifist but a militant pacifist. I am willing to fight for peace. Nothing will end war unless the people themselves refuse to go to war.', 104, 0), (431518, 'The first panacea for a mismanaged nation is inflation of the currency the second is war. Both bring a temporary prosperity both bring a permanent ruin. But both are the refuge of political and economic opportunists. ', 110, 0), (431519, 'Let us ever remember that our interest is in concord, not in conflict; and that our real eminence rests in the victories of peace, not those of war.', 10515, 0), (431520, 'In war the heroes always outnumber the soldiers ten to one.', 411, 0), (431521, 'I would make this war as severe as possible, and show no symptoms of tiring till the South begs for mercy.', 65193, 0), (431522, 'We lived in a tall, narrow Victorian house, which my parents had bought very cheaply during the war, when everyone thought London was going to be bombed flat. In fact, a V-2 rocket landed a few houses away from ours. I was away with my mother and sister at the time, but my father was in the house.', 1222, 0), (431523, 'One cannot wage war under present conditions without the support of public opinion, which is tremendously molded by the press and other forms of propaganda.', 2273, 0), (431524, 'The president led us into the Iraq war on the basis of unproven assertions without evidence he embraced a radical doctrine of pre-emptive war unprecedented in our history and he failed to build a true international coalition. ', 50900, 0), (431525, 'It is far easier to make war than peace.', 4926, 0), (431526, 'However much we may sympathize with a small nation confronted by a big and powerful neighbours, we cannot in all circumstances undertake to involve the whole British Empire in a war simply on her account.', 68662, 0), (431527, 'If nations could only depend upon fair and impartial judgments in a world court of law, they would abandon the senseless, savage practice of war.', 68680, 0), (431528, 'The only way human beings can win a war is to prevent it.', 68681, 0), (431529, 'Yesterday, December seventh, 1941, a date which will live in infamy, the United States of America was suddenly and deliberately attacked by naval and air forces of the Empire of Japan. We will gain the inevitable triumph, so help us God.', 2261, 0), (431530, 'My child, you are going to be a great king; do not imitate me in the taste I have had for building, or in that I have had for war; try, on the contrary, to be at peace with your neighbors.', 65275, 0), (431531, 'You know, the period of World War I and the Roaring Twenties were really just about the same as today. You worked, and you made a living if you could, and you tired to make the best of things. For an actor or a dancer, it was no different then than today. It was a struggle.', 15826, 0), (431532, 'Preemption is the right of any nation in order to preserve its National Security; however, preemptive war is a tactic, not a strategy. When used as a strategy preemption dilutes diplomacy, creates an atmosphere of distrust, and promotes regional instability.', 68682, 0), (431533, 'An empire founded by war has to maintain itself by war.', 48659, 0), (431534, 'It is my conviction that killing under the cloak of war is nothing but an act of murder.', 104, 0), (431535, 'In modern war... you will die like a dog for no good reason.', 110, 0), (431536, 'In war, you win or lose, live or die - and the difference is just an eyelash.', 2273, 0), (431537, 'War against a foreign country only happens when the moneyed classes think they are going to profit from it.', 521, 0), (431538, 'War is a defeat for humanity.', 66871, 0), (431539, 'All warfare is based on deception.', 1471, 0), (431540, 'The very essence of literature is the war between emotion and intellect, between life and death. When literature becomes too intellectual - when it begins to ignore the passions, the emotions - it becomes sterile, silly, and actually without substance.', 1467, 0), (431541, 'Let us wage a moral and political war against the billionaires and corporate leaders, on Wall Street and elsewhere, whose policies and greed are destroying the middle class of America.', 40174, 0), (431542, 'The war on drugs is wrong, both tactically and morally. It assumes that people are too stupid, too reckless, and too irresponsible to decide whether and under what conditions to consume drugs. The war on drugs is morally bankrupt.', 55271, 0), (431543, 'Classical tragedy was the war between good and evil. We wanted evil to be defeated and good to be victorious. But the battle in modern tragedy is between good and good. And no matter which side wins, we''ll still be heartbroken.', 67520, 0), (431544, 'War should never be entered upon until every agency of peace has failed.', 10515, 0), (431545, 'America has fought five wars since 1945 and has gained its objectives in only one of them, the Gulf War.', 2393, 0), (431546, 'Diplomats are just as essential to starting a war as soldiers are for finishing it... You take diplomacy out of war, and the thing would fall flat in a week.', 1122, 0), (431547, 'A hospital alone shows what war is.', 2811, 0), (431548, 'Thus they have an idol that they petition for victory in war; another for success in their labors; and so for everything in which they seek or desire prosperity, they have their idols, which they honor and serve.', 68683, 0), (431549, 'I shall proceed from the simple to the complex. But in war more than in any other subject we must begin by looking at the nature of the whole for here more than elsewhere the part and the whole must always be thought of together. ', 2677, 0), (431550, 'We used to wonder where war lived, what it was that made it so vile. And now we realize that we know where it lives... inside ourselves.', 532, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (431551, 'The idea that a war can be won by standing on the defensive and waiting for the enemy to attack is a dangerous fallacy, which owes its inception to the desire to evade the price of victory.', 68684, 0), (431552, 'The War on Drugs employs millions - politicians, bureaucrats, policemen, and now the military - that probably couldn''t find a place for their dubious talents in a free market, unless they were to sell pencils from a tin cup on street corners.', 68685, 0), (431553, 'The threat today is not that of the 1930s. It''s not big powers going to war with each other. The ravages which fundamentalist political ideology inflicted on the 20th century are memories. The Cold war is over. Europe is at peace, if not always diplomatically.', 17822, 0), (431554, 'My father wanted to be a hero. He went to the Air Force Academy, was valedictorian, and then he found himself strafing villagers in Vietnam in a war he didn''t want to be in and didn''t understand. He was extremely conflicted about the line where he went from being the good guy to possibly being the bad guy.', 68686, 0), (431555, 'In most communities it is illegal to cry ''fire'' in a crowded assembly. Should it not be considered serious international misconduct to manufacture a general war scare in an effort to achieve local political aims?', 2119, 0), (431556, 'War is so unjust and ugly that all who wage it must try to stifle the voice of conscience within themselves.', 93, 0), (431557, 'War is to man what maternity is to a woman. From a philosophical and doctrinal viewpoint, I do not believe in perpetual peace.', 2005, 0), (431558, 'Be polite write diplomatically even in a declaration of war one observes the rules of politeness. ', 4746, 0), (431559, 'To all those who walk the path of human cooperation war must appear loathsome and inhuman.', 29457, 0), (431560, 'The sinews of war are infinite money.', 1306, 0), (431561, 'If there is no sufficient reason for war, the war party will make war on one pretext, then invent another... after the war is on.', 68687, 0), (431562, 'How is it they live in such harmony the billions of stars - when most men can barely go a minute without declaring war in their minds about someone they know.', 1539, 0), (431563, 'People always make war when they say they love peace.', 178, 0), (431564, 'Killing Japanese didn''t bother me very much at that time... I suppose if I had lost the war, I would have been tried as a war criminal.', 68688, 0), (431565, 'Although our war on drugs must be fortified with the best laws, enforcement efforts and resources, we would not be successful without your individual commitment to this cause.', 68689, 0), (431566, 'May the same Almighty Goodness banish the accursed monster, war, from all lands, with her hated associates, rapine and insatiable ambition!', 14584, 0), (431567, 'In this first testing ground of the atomic bomb I have seen the most terrible and frightening desolation in four years of war. It makes a blitzed Pacific island seem like an Eden. The damage is far greater than photographs can show.', 68690, 0), (431568, 'War is failure of diplomacy.', 68691, 0), (431569, 'President Johnson did not want the Vietnam War to broaden. He wanted the North Vietnamese to leave their brothers in the South alone.', 68692, 0), (431570, 'Weapons are an important factor in war, but not the decisive one; it is man and not materials that counts.', 15795, 0), (431571, 'The grim fact is that we prepare for war like precocious giants, and for peace like retarded pygmies.', 17580, 0), (431572, 'In the practical art of war, the best thing of all is to take the enemy''s country whole and intact; to shatter and destroy it is not so good.', 1026, 0), (431573, 'And we love to dance, especially that new one called the Civil War Twist. The Northern part of you stands still while the Southern part tries to secede.', 39403, 0), (431574, 'Today we know that World War II began not in 1939 or 1941 but in the 1920''s and 1930''s when those who should have known better persuaded themselves that they were not their brother''s keeper.', 15498, 0), (431575, 'I''m finding myself really angry over spending and the deficit. I''m finding myself really angry over what''s happening in the Middle East, the decision to stay in Afghanistan indefinitely. I''m angry about cap and trade. And I''ve been on record for a long time on the failed war on drugs.', 68241, 0), (431576, 'I grew up on what everybody called a plantation - but believe me, it wasn''t a plantation. It was just an old farm. I grew up with a lot of black people working in the fields, and it was during the Depression between 1930 and the war, so we were all poor - black and white.', 68693, 0), (431577, 'I''ve always been at war with myself, for right or wrong.', 2614, 0), (431578, 'War is hell. Hollywood fantasizes about it and makes it look good... war sucks.', 2455, 0), (431579, 'I''m trying to raise the awareness of the troops that, when they deploy and go to war, it''s not just them at war - it''s also their family. Their family is having to go through all the hardships and the stresses.', 2455, 0), (431580, 'When the peace treaty is signed, the war isn''t over for the veterans, or the family. It''s just starting.', 8210, 0), (431581, 'One of the greatest casualties of the war in Vietnam is the Great Society... shot down on the battlefield of Vietnam.', 21767, 0), (431582, 'War is God''s way of teaching Americans geography.', 224, 0), (431583, 'Americans play to win at all times. I wouldn''t give a hoot and hell for a man who lost and laughed. That''s why Americans have never lost nor ever lose a war.', 57896, 0), (431584, 'The U.S. army confirmed that it gave a lucrative fire fighting contract in Iraq to the firm once run by the Vice President Dick Cheney without any competitive bidding. When asked if this could be conceived as Cheney''s friends profiting from the war, the spokesman said ''Yes.''', 1326, 0), (431585, 'As history since Hiroshima shows, the best, perhaps the only, way to curb war is to deter it with such overwhelming force as to turn it from a struggle into suicide.', 57621, 0), (431586, 'My home policy: I wage war my foreign policy: I wage war. All the time I wage war. ', 4926, 0), (431587, 'I always found the extraordinary loss of life in the First World War very moving. I remember learning about it as a very young child, as an eight- or nine-year-old, asking my teachers what poppies were for. Every year the teachers would suddenly wear these red paper flowers in their lapels, and I would say ''What does that mean?''', 1101, 0), (431588, 'Wanton killing of innocent civilians is terrorism, not a war against terrorism.', 1955, 0), (431589, 'War is a racket. It always has been... A few profit - and the many pay. But there is a way to stop it. You can''t end it by disarmament conferences. You can''t eliminate it by peace parleys at Geneva. Well-meaning but impractical groups can''t wipe it out by resolutions. It can be smashed effectively only by taking the profit out of war.', 66579, 0), (431590, '''But,'' say the puling, pusillanimous cowards, ''we shall be subject to a long and bloody war if we declare independence.'' On the contrary, I affirm it the only step that can bring the contest to a speedy and happy issue.', 16829, 0), (431591, 'A nation''s ability to fight a modern war is as good as its technological ability.', 68694, 0), (431592, 'The peasant must always be helped technically, economically, morally and culturally. The guerrilla fighter will be a sort of guiding angel who has fallen into the zone, helping the poor always and bothering the rich as little as possible in the first phases of the war.', 68679, 0), (431593, 'Study and work and work and study will keep in active exercise both the physical and mental. These two, rightly conducted, will not war against each other.', 4150, 0), (431594, 'Serious sport is war minus the shooting.', 521, 0), (431595, 'War is wrong. Conscription for war is inconsistent with freedom of conscience, which is not merely the right to believe but to act on the degree of truth that one receives, to follow a vocation which is God-inspired and God-directed.', 51917, 0), (431596, 'The lesson of the Cuban Missile Crisis is plain: Strength prevents war weakness invites it. We need a commander-in-chief who understands that - and who won''t leave us facing a foe who thinks he doesn''t. ', 68695, 0), (431597, 'In wartime, truth is so precious that she should always be attended by a bodyguard of lies.', 3621, 0), (431598, 'When the women''s liberation movement began, when people began protesting against the Vietnam War, civil rights movement, at the beginning of those movements, the majority of the country was not with them, did not believe in the basic principles of any of those philosophies.', 17499, 0), (431599, 'In the first six to twelve months of a war with the United States and Great Britain I will run wild and win victory upon victory. But then, if the war continues after that, I have no expectation of success.', 68696, 0), (431600, 'Our life is half natural and half technological. Half-and-half is good. You cannot deny that high-tech is progress. We need it for jobs. Yet if you make only high-tech, you make war. So we must have a strong human element to keep modesty and natural life.', 68697, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (431601, 'Wars are not paid for in wartime, the bill comes later.', 1077, 0), (431602, 'Those who are at war with others are not at peace with themselves.', 8948, 0), (431603, 'During the Cold War, America undertook serious military cuts only once: after the election of Richard Nixon, during the Vietnam War. The result: Vietnam fell to the Communists, the Russians moved into Afghanistan, and American influence around the globe waned dramatically.', 17797, 0), (431604, 'The mother''s battle for her child with sickness, with poverty, with war, with all the forces of exploitation and callousness that cheapen human life needs to become a common human battle, waged in love and in the passion for survival.', 809, 0), (431605, 'Speaking as a writer, it would be difficult to find an event in American history more dramatic and riveting than the Civil War.', 68698, 0), (431606, 'During World War II, law-abiding Japanese-American citizens were herded into remote internment camps, losing their jobs, businesses and social standing, while an all-Japanese-American division fought heroically in Europe.', 11429, 0), (431607, 'Don''t settle; don''t compromise. Freeze your eggs, get your sociology doctorate, worry more about war and pestilence and the incredible inequality of geographical birth than finding your soulmate.', 13031, 0), (431608, 'The sacrifices in the war against terrorism reflect complete and strong determination of Pakistan against terrorism.', 67079, 0), (431609, 'In some states militant nationalism has gone to the lengths of dictatorship, the cult of the absolute or totalitarian state and the glorification of war.', 68699, 0), (431610, 'Today continuing poverty and distress are a deeper and more important cause of international tensions, of the conditions that can produce war, than previously.', 17580, 0), (431611, 'I have known war as few men now living know it. It''s very destructiveness on both friend and foe has rendered it useless as a means of settling international disputes.', 2273, 0), (431612, 'The United States is not, and never will be, at war with Islam.', 1693, 0), (431613, 'My husband was in the war of the Crimea. It is terrible the hardships he went through, to be two months without going into a house, under the snow in trenches. And no food to get, maybe a biscuit in the day. And there was enough food there, he said, to feed all Ireland; but bad management, they could not get it.', 21592, 0), (431614, 'Anyone who experienced World War I close-hand was grossed out by it forever. It just was so awful.', 45206, 0), (431615, 'If... many influential people have failed to understand, or have just forgotten, what we were up against in the Cold War and how we overcame it, they are not going to be capable of securing, let alone enlarging, the gains that liberty has made.', 1945, 0), (431616, 'There was never a good war, or a bad peace.', 1077, 0), (431617, 'My subject is War, and the pity of War. The Poetry is in the pity.', 6003, 0), (431618, 'My mom, Irmelin, taught me the value of life. Her own life was saved by my grandmother during World War II.', 68700, 0), (431619, 'A state of war only serves as an excuse for domestic tyranny.', 2564, 0), (431620, 'Patriots always talk of dying for their country and never of killing for their country.', 95, 0), (431621, 'Sometime they''ll give a war and nobody will come.', 1301, 0), (431622, 'All wars are civil wars, because all men are brothers.', 15972, 0), (431623, 'The way to win an atomic war is to make certain it never starts.', 49153, 0), (431624, 'Wars can be prevented just as surely as they can be provoked, and we who fail to prevent them, must share the guilt for the dead.', 49153, 0), (431625, 'It is not patriotic to commit young Americans to war unless our national security clearly requires it.', 68665, 0), (431626, 'To walk through the ruined cities of Germany is to feel an actual doubt about the continuity of civilization.', 521, 0), (431627, 'When the rich wage war, it''s the poor who die.', 592, 0), (431628, 'War will exist until that distant day when the conscientious objector enjoys the same reputation and prestige that the warrior does today.', 1680, 0), (431629, 'War remains the decisive human failure.', 4940, 0), (431630, 'We must concentrate not merely on the negative expulsion of war but the postive affirmation of peace.', 21767, 0), (431631, 'An army marches on its stomach.', 1702, 0), (431632, 'It is well that war is so terrible, otherwise we should grow too fond of it.', 1924, 0), (431633, 'The war... was an unnecessary condition of affairs, and might have been avoided if forebearance and wisdom had been practiced on both sides.', 1924, 0), (431634, 'Wars have never hurt anybody except the people who die.', 1803, 0), (431635, 'There will one day spring from the brain of science a machine or force so fearful in its potentialities, so absolutely terrifying, that even man, the fighter, who will dare torture and death in order to inflict torture and death, will be appalled, and so abandon war forever.', 1673, 0), (431636, 'The most successful war seldom pays for its losses.', 1207, 0), (431637, 'It is forbidden to kill therefore all murderers are punished unless they kill in large numbers and to the sound of trumpets. ', 808, 0), (431638, 'A lasting order cannot be established by bayonets.', 9998, 0), (431639, 'Love is like war: easy to begin but very hard to stop.', 411, 0), (431640, 'We should seek by all means in our power to avoid war, by analysing possible causes, by trying to remove them, by discussion in a spirit of collaboration and good will.', 68662, 0), (431641, 'I do not believe that civilization will be wiped out in a war fought with the atomic bomb. Perhaps two-thirds of the people of the earth will be killed.', 104, 0), (431642, 'When antibiotics became industrially produced following World War II, our quality of life and our longevity improved enormously. No one thought bacteria were going to become resistant.', 68701, 0), (431643, 'The real and lasting victories are those of peace, and not of war.', 760, 0), (431644, 'People were already beginning to forget, what horrible suffering the war had brought them. I did not want to cause fear and panic, but to let people know how dreadful war is and so to stimulate people''s powers of resistance.', 68186, 0), (431645, 'I was one of those children forced into fighting at the age of 13, in my country Sierra Leone, a war that claimed the lives of my mother, father and two brothers. I know too well the emotional, psychological and physical burden that comes with being exposed to violence as a child or at any age for that matter.', 7857, 0), (431646, 'It is the function of the Navy to carry the war to the enemy so that it is not fought on U.S. soil.', 60612, 0), (431647, 'From infancy, I had been accustomed to hear pro and con discussions of slavery and the American Civil War. Although the British government finally decided not to recognise the Confederacy, public opinion in England was sharply divided on the questions both of slavery and of secession.', 16347, 0), (431648, 'When I was a young boy, during the aftermath of World War II, Germany was broken and in ruins. Many people were hungry, sick, and dying. I remember well the humanitarian shipments of food and clothing that came from the Church in Salt Lake City.', 1842, 0), (431649, 'Peace is not an absence of war, it is a virtue, a state of mind, a disposition for benevolence, confidence, justice.', 2478, 0), (431650, 'We prefer world law in the age of self-determination to world war in the age of mass extermination.', 1680, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (431651, 'If men make war in slavish obedience to rules, they will fail.', 9689, 0), (431652, 'The war against terrorism is terrorism.', 68702, 0), (431653, 'War makes strange giant creatures out of us little routine men who inhabit the earth.', 9247, 0), (431654, 'War alone brings up to their highest tension all human energies and imposes the stamp of nobility upon the peoples who have the courage to make it.', 2005, 0), (431655, 'The quickest way of ending a war is to lose it.', 521, 0), (431656, 'Ronald Reagan will be remembered for leading the United States during a time of tremendous international transition - the demise of the Soviet Union, the Berlin Wall coming down, and the end of the Cold War.', 68703, 0), (431657, 'Peace is the virtue of civilization. War is its crime.', 98, 0), (431658, 'In remembering the appalling suffering of war on both sides, we recognise how precious is the peace we have built in Europe since 1945.', 65677, 0), (431659, 'War is too serious a matter to leave to soldiers.', 65193, 0), (431660, 'I may not lead the most dramatic life, but in my brain it''s ''War and Peace'' everyday.', 8055, 0), (431661, 'The Patriot Act is essential to our continued success in the war on terror here at home.', 66593, 0), (431662, 'In every war zone that I''ve been in, there has been a reality and then there has been the public perception of why the war was being fought. In every crisis, the issues have been far more complex than the public has been allowed to know.', 5956, 0), (431663, 'I extend my deepest gratitude to our Armed Forces and first responders serving both at home and abroad in the war against terrorism.', 68704, 0), (431664, 'When we analyze this war in a materialistic way and ask when is it going to end and who will be the winner and the loser, it means that we do not see the endgame.', 68705, 0), (431665, 'Yes, politics IS war without bloodshed; and war is an extension of those politics.', 68706, 0), (431666, 'Developments in information technology and globalised media mean that the most powerful military in the history of the world can lose a war, not on the battlefield of dust and blood, but on the battlefield of world opinion.', 47447, 0), (431667, 'It''s an interesting combination: Having a great fear of being alone, and having a desperate need for solitude and the solitary experience. That''s always been a tug of war for me.', 63992, 0), (431668, 'War is a blessing compared with national degradation.', 2245, 0), (431669, 'We''ve used up a lot of bullets. And we talk about stimulus. But the truth is, we''re running a federal deficit that''s 9 percent of GDP. That is stimulative as all get out. It''s more stimulative than any policy we''ve followed since World War II.', 6410, 0), (431670, 'When I was a youngster growing up in South Dakota, we never referred to the national debt, it was always referred to as the war debt because it stemmed from World War I.', 68665, 0), (431671, 'Past records of inter-Korean relations show that confrontation between fellow countrymen leads to nothing but war.', 67852, 0), (431672, 'When I was a young man, I was poor. In a war with other nations, I was in eighty-seven fights. There I received my name and was made Chief of my nation. But now I am old and am for peace.', 68707, 0), (431673, 'Almost everything about American society is affected by World War II: our feelings about race; our feelings about gender and the empowerment of women, moving women into the workplace; our feelings about our role in the world. All of that comes in a very direct way out of World War II.', 68708, 0), (431674, 'The earth is bountiful, and where her bounty fails, nitrogen drawn from the air will refertilize her womb. I developed a process for this purpose in 1900. It was perfected fourteen years later under the stress of war by German chemists.', 1908, 0), (431675, 'I have a graduate degree from Penn State. I studied at Penn State under a noted Hemingway scholar, Philip Young. I had an interest in thrillers, and it occurred to me that Hemingway wrote many action scenes: the war scenes in ''A Farewell to Arms'' and ''For Whom the Bell Tolls'' come to mind. But the scenes don''t feel pulpy.', 9823, 0), (431676, 'As a Korean War veteran, I know firsthand and understand the sacrifices made by our men and women in uniform.', 41313, 0), (431677, 'It''s my belief that, since the end of the Second World War, psychology has moved too far away from its original roots, which were to make the lives of all people more fulfilling and productive, and too much toward the important, but not all-important, area of curing mental illness.', 67434, 0), (431678, 'The Korean War, which China entered on the side of North Korea, fixed Mao''s image in the United States as another unappeasable Communist.', 29696, 0), (431679, 'When we contend, let us contend for all our rights - the doubtful and the certain, the unimportant and essential. It is as easy to contend, or even more so, for the whole as for a part. At the termination of the contest, secure all that our wisdom and valour and the fortune of war will permit.', 63147, 0), (431680, 'The only thing that kept the Cold War cold was the mutual deterrence afforded by nuclear weapons.', 68656, 0), (431681, 'Syria is attracting a lot more Westerners than the Iraq War ever did because it''s the perfect Sunni jihad.', 68253, 0), (431682, 'The most important accomplishment, I believe, was my voting against the First World War.', 16068, 0), (431683, 'We believe in peace in the settlement of all disputes through peaceful means, in the abolition of war, and, more particularly, nuclear war.', 67654, 0), (431684, 'World War II was the last government program that really worked.', 29034, 0), (431685, 'I''ve been to war, and it''s not easy to kill. It''s bloody and messy and totally horrifying, and the consequences are serious.', 40728, 0), (431686, 'A prisoner of war is a man who tries to kill you and fails, and then asks you not to kill him.', 3621, 0), (431687, 'I used to think that the Civil War was our country''s greatest tragedy, but I do remember that there were some redeeming features in the Civil War in that there was some spirit of sacrifice and heroism displayed on both sides. I see no redeeming features in Watergate.', 68709, 0), (431688, 'Our strategy is one of preventing war by making it self-evident to our enemies that they''re going to get their clocks cleaned if they start one.', 68710, 0), (431689, 'The Vietnam War required us to emphasize the national interest rather than abstract principles. What President Nixon and I tried to do was unnatural. And that is why we didn''t make it.', 2393, 0), (431690, 'We have always said that in our war with the Arabs we had a secret weapon - no alternative.', 12971, 0), (431691, 'War is an instrument entirely inefficient toward redressing wrong; and multiplies, instead of indemnifying losses.', 1207, 0), (431692, 'Lots of people who complained about us receiving the MBE received theirs for heroism in the war - for killing people. We received ours for entertaining other people. I''d say we deserve ours more.', 46, 0), (431693, 'I took a speed-reading course and read War and Peace in twenty minutes. It involves Russia.', 281, 0), (431694, 'A time will come when a politician who has willfully made war and promoted international dissension will be as sure of the dock and much surer of the noose than a private homicide. It is not reasonable that those who gamble with men''s lives should not stake their own.', 3173, 0), (431695, 'It is fatal to enter any war without the will to win it.', 2273, 0), (431696, 'In war there is no substitute for victory.', 2273, 0), (431697, 'Peace is the happy natural state of man war is corruption and disgrace. ', 63383, 0), (431698, 'Mankind will never win lasting peace so long as men use their full resources only in tasks of war. While we are yet at peace, let us mobilize the potentialities, particularly the moral and spiritual potentialities, which we usually reserve for war.', 62963, 0), (431699, 'Many intelligence reports in war are contradictory; even more are false, and most are uncertain.', 2677, 0), (431700, 'War should be the only study of a prince. He should consider peace only as a breathing-time, which gives him leisure to contrive, and furnishes as ability to execute, military plans.', 947, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (431701, 'Television brought the brutality of war into the comfort of the living room. Vietnam was lost in the living rooms of America - not on the battlefields of Vietnam.', 2728, 0), (431702, 'If we lose the war in the air we lose the war and we lose it quickly.', 68711, 0), (431703, 'If you want to go anywhere in modern war, in the air, on the sea, on the land, you must have command of the air.', 68712, 0), (431704, 'In time of peace prepare for war.', 68668, 0), (431705, 'One can go to war alone, but you can''t build peace alone.', 68659, 0), (431706, 'All oppression creates a state of war.', 477, 0), (431707, 'All the gods are dead except the god of war.', 63025, 0), (431708, 'As for charity, it is a matter in which the immediate effect on the persons directly concerned, and the ultimate consequence to the general good, are apt to be at complete war with one another.', 1880, 0), (431709, 'Only the most deluded of us could doubt the necessity of this war.', 9128, 0), (431710, 'Running for President is physically, emotionally, mentally and spiritually the most demanding single undertaking I can envisage unless it''s World War III.', 68713, 0), (431711, 'The first lesson is that you can''t lose a war if you have command of the air, and you can''t win a war if you haven''t.', 68714, 0), (431712, 'We live in the time where we have fictitious election results that elects a fictitious president. We live in a time where we have a man sending us to war for fictitious reasons.', 17499, 0), (431713, 'No war is inevitable until it breaks out.', 20910, 0), (431714, 'Our modern states are preparing for war without even knowing the future enemy.', 29457, 0), (431715, 'It is part of the general pattern of misguided policy that our country is now geared to an arms economy which was bred in an artificially induced psychosis of war hysteria and nurtured upon an incessant propaganda of fear.', 2273, 0), (431716, 'When people speak to you about a preventive war, you tell them to go and fight it. After my experience, I have come to hate war.', 2119, 0), (431717, 'The essential act of war is destruction, not necessarily of human lives, but of the products of human labor.', 521, 0), (431718, 'War is not an independent phenomenon, but the continuation of politics by different means.', 2677, 0), (431719, 'It is the youth who must inherit the tribulation, the sorrow... that are the aftermath of war.', 7777, 0), (431720, 'If our most highly qualified General Staff officers had been told to work out the most nonsensical high level organization for war which they could think of, they could not have produced anything more stupid that that which we have at present.', 68715, 0), (431721, 'Sometimes I think war is God''s way of teaching us geography.', 65733, 0), (431722, 'War is the remedy that our enemies have chosen, and I say let us give them all they want.', 65193, 0), (431723, 'You cannot qualify war in harsher terms than I will.', 65193, 0), (431724, 'So, this war is against the Islam that the West does not control.', 51994, 0), (431725, 'In a world of inhumanity, war and terrorism, American citizenship is a very precious possession.', 16939, 0), (431726, 'When was the last time you saw a musical about people at war with each other?', 68716, 0), (431727, 'You can say battle or war or whatever, but in the end, it''s music. It''s not really violent in intent at all, it''s really just about expression and celebrating that in itself.', 68618, 0), (431728, 'Every soldier thinks something of the moral aspects of what he is doing. But all war is immoral and if you let that bother you, you''re not a good soldier.', 68688, 0), (431729, 'As soon as I read that, it clicked: that''s my theater of war. It was exciting to think that I could write about World War Two from a totally new place.', 1100, 0), (431730, 'It''s a war of attrition. If you have patience and a modicum of faith in yourself your chances are not too bad.', 68717, 0), (431731, 'If something is said about the Raiders, I''m ready to go to war.', 68718, 0), (431732, 'No one will deny that the excessive use of alcohol and alcoholic beverages would do more than any other single factor to make impossible a total war effort.', 62778, 0), (431733, 'Nevertheless, China was unfortunately unable to understand Japan''s real position, and it is greatly to be regretted that the Sino-Japanese War became one of long duration.', 67656, 0), (431734, 'As a result of the World War, this old Germany collapsed. It collapsed in its constitution, in its social order, in its economic structure. Its thinking and feeling changed.', 67585, 0), (431735, 'If the Founding Fathers and other patriots who fought during the Revolutionary War could see the United States today, I believe they would be proud of the path that the thirteen colonies, now fifty strong states, have taken since then.', 67592, 0), (431736, 'In a war, you must hate somebody or love somebody; you must have a position or you cannot stand what goes on.', 67370, 0), (431737, 'Look at what President Kennedy managed to achieve during the Cuban missile crisis. If Bush had been president in 1962, do you think he would have avoided a nuclear war?', 68719, 0), (431738, 'If there ever was a religious war full of terror, it was the crusades. But you can''t blame Christianity because a few adventurers did this. That''s my message.', 68720, 0), (431739, 'People always seem to assume that we have a full, back-up support team - make-up, costume and a driver - but usually, in a war zone, there''s only me and the cameraman.', 68721, 0), (431740, 'War is not the answer, because only love can conquer hate.', 1332, 0), (431741, 'It''s the first war we''ve ever fought on the television screen and the first war that our country ever fought where the media had full reign.', 68692, 0), (431742, 'Bush''s war in Iraq has done untold damage to the United States. It has impaired our military power and undermined the morale of our armed forces. Our troops were trained to project overwhelming power. They were not trained for occupation duties.', 2935, 0), (431743, 'Where the stakes are the highest, in the war on terror, we cannot possibly succeed without extraordinary international cooperation. Effective international police actions require the highest degree of intelligence sharing, planning and collaborative enforcement.', 1693, 0), (431744, 'There have been only 268 of the past 3,421 years free of war.', 1167, 0), (431745, 'Everything in war is very simple. But the simplest thing is difficult.', 2677, 0), (431746, 'There are two things which a democratic people will always find very difficult - to begin a war and to end it.', 4021, 0), (431747, 'If few can stand a long war without deterioration of soul, none can stand a long peace.', 20909, 0), (431748, 'Happiness is a byproduct of function, purpose, and conflict; those who seek happiness for itself seek victory without war.', 320, 0), (431749, 'Be convinced that to be happy means to be free and that to be free means to be brave. Therefore do not take lightly the perils of war.', 2096, 0), (431750, 'I can not believe that war is the best solution. No one won the last war, and no one will win the next war.', 141, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (431751, 'War is the trade of Kings.', 8695, 0), (431752, 'Monarchs ought to put to death the authors and instigators of war, as their sworn enemies and as dangers to their states.', 1401, 0), (431753, 'Here''s how I think of my money - as soldiers - I send them out to war everyday. I want them to take prisoners and come home, so there''s more of them.', 66628, 0), (431754, 'My father was an immigrant who literally walked across Europe to get out of Russia. He fought in World War I. He was wounded in action. My father was a great success even though he never had money. He was a very determined man, a great role model.', 68028, 0), (431755, 'I''m old enough to remember the end of World War II. On Aug. 14, 1946, a year after the Japanese were defeated, most newspapers and magazines had single articles commemorating the end of the war.', 45221, 0), (431756, 'Unfortunately, in war, there are casualties, including among the civilian population.', 68722, 0), (431757, 'The United States established itself as a trustworthy new nation in its first two decades after the Revolutionary War by paying its debts, even when many in the country believed it had no obligation to do so. Alexander Hamilton, the founder of this newspaper, insisted on it.', 68723, 0), (431758, 'I absolutely don''t think a sentient artificial intelligence is going to wage war against the human species.', 15991, 0), (431759, '''Matterhorn'' is my metaphor of the Vietnam War - we built it, we abandoned it, we assaulted it, we lost, and then we abandoned it again.', 8210, 0), (431760, '''Jihad'' can mean holy war to extremists, but it means struggle to the average Muslim.', 68724, 0), (431761, 'There is nothing glamorous or romantic about war. It''s mostly about random pointless death and misery.', 117, 0), (431762, 'In the business of war, the role of women is really to maintain normalcy and ensure that there is cultural continuity.', 68725, 0), (431763, 'In the name of the rule of law, democracy and human rights, we cannot accept that the rights of individuals (Arab or Muslim) be trampled upon, or that populations are targeted and discriminated against in the name of the war against terrorism.', 4710, 0), (431764, 'I preferred the weapons of dialectic to all the other teachings of philosophy, and armed with these, I chose the conflicts of disputation rather than the trophies of war.', 11585, 0), (431765, 'With one terrible exception, the Civil War, law and the Constitution have kept America whole and free.', 68726, 0), (431766, 'In Iraq, many of my female friends were architects and professionals with a lot of power during the 1980s while all the men were at war in Iran.', 68727, 0), (431767, 'War is just a racket. A racket is best described, I believe, as something that is not what it seems to the majority of people. Only a small inside group knows what it is about. It is conducted for the benefit of the very few at the expense of the masses.', 66579, 0), (431768, 'War is a form of really bad manners, in a strange way. Invading a country I think is just the worst possible manners. ''You''re not invited!'' Gate crashing on a large scale!', 17483, 0), (431769, 'The European wars of religion were more deadly than the First World War, proportionally speaking, and in the range of the Second World War in Europe. The Inquisition, the persecution of heretics and infidels and witches, they racked up pretty high death tolls.', 3432, 0), (431770, 'I believe that democracies do not go to war; that''s the lesson of history, and I think that a democratic Pakistan is the world community''s best guarantee of stability in Asia.', 16721, 0), (431771, 'We all want a world without war, without conflict, without human suffering.', 68728, 0), (431772, 'One culture I find fascinating to juxtapose against American culture is the culture of Germany. They''ve gone through a long process through their art, poetry, public discourse, their politics, of owning the fact of their complicity in what happened in World War II. It''s still a topic of everyday conversation in Germany.', 67234, 0), (431773, 'Laws are the terms by which independent and isolated men united to form a society, once they tired of living in a perpetual state of war where the enjoyment of liberty was rendered useless by the uncertainty of its preservation. They sacrificed a portion of this liberty so that they could enjoy the remainder in security and peace.', 3016, 0), (431774, 'The Iraq War was the biggest issue for people of my generation in the West. It was also the clearest case, in my living memory, of media manipulation and the creation of a war through ignorance.', 25705, 0), (431775, 'The Vietnam War totally turned my life around. Some people''s lives were eliminated or destroyed by the experience. I was one of the fortunate few who came out better off.', 68729, 0), (431776, 'The world will never have lasting peace so long as men reserve for war the finest human qualities. Peace, no less than war, requires idealism and self-sacrifice and a righteous and dynamic faith.', 62963, 0), (431777, 'War has become a luxury that only small nations can afford.', 2694, 0), (431778, 'Those who can win a war well can rarely make a good peace and those who could make a good peace would never have won the war.', 3621, 0), (431779, 'There have been two popular subjects for poetry in the last few decades: the Vietnam War and AIDS, about both of which almost all of us have felt deeply.', 8916, 0), (431780, 'The real war is not between the West and the East. The real war is between intelligent and stupid people.', 2030, 0), (431781, 'If there is not the war, you don''t get the great general; if there is not a great occasion, you don''t get a great statesman; if Lincoln had lived in a time of peace, no one would have known his name.', 1674, 0), (431782, 'My dear Excellency! I have not gone to war to collect cheese and eggs, but for another purpose.', 68730, 0), (431783, 'Morality is contraband in war.', 32, 0), (431784, 'We should declare war on North Vietnam. We could pave the whole country and put parking strips on it, and still be home by Christmas.', 1727, 0), (431785, 'Sectional football games have the glory and the despair of war, and when a Texas team takes the field against a foreign state, it is an army with banners.', 1070, 0), (431786, 'We know more about war than we know about peace, more about killing than we know about living.', 49153, 0), (431787, 'As to war, I am and always was a great enemy, at the same time a warrior the greater part of my life and were I young again, should still be a warrior while ever this country should be invaded and I lived.', 67471, 0), (431788, 'War is organized murder and torture against our brothers.', 29457, 0), (431789, 'Democracies are indeed slow to make war, but once embarked upon a martial venture are equally slow to make peace and reluctant to make a tolerable, rather than a vindictive, peace.', 1779, 0), (431790, 'Geopolitical drama lessened but did not die after the Cold War; in 2008, the specter of thousands of seeming automatons banging drums at the opening of the Beijing Games frightened and enthralled the world, reminding us that China was a nation on the rise, a competitor for global dominance.', 17797, 0), (431791, 'The scenes on this field would have cured anybody of war.', 65193, 0), (431792, 'We must fight for peace bravely as we fought in war.', 67654, 0), (431793, 'If we don''t end war, war will end us.', 3173, 0), (431794, 'Ants are so much like human beings as to be an embarrassment. They farm fungi, raise aphids as livestock, launch armies into war, use chemical sprays to alarm and confuse enemies, capture slaves, engage in child labour, exchange information ceaselessly. They do everything but watch television.', 3484, 0), (431795, 'Construction of the first gas pipeline system was started during the 1960s, at the height of the Cold War, and for all those years, from the 1960s until this day, Russia has been fulfilling its contract obligations in a very consistent and reliable way, regardless of the political situation.', 50689, 0), (431796, 'In Britain and Europe, no event is less forgotten than World War I, or ''The Great War,'' as it was called until 1939.', 14083, 0), (431797, 'In nuclear war all men are cremated equal.', 68129, 0), (431798, 'The leaders of the world face no greater task than that of avoiding nuclear war. While preserving the cause of freedom, we must seek abolition of war through programs of general and complete disarmament. The Test-Ban Treaty of 1963 represents a significant beginning in this immense undertaking.', 60667, 0), (431799, 'Haiti and the Dominican Republic don''t just share an island, Hispaniola, but a history, one that includes all the signal events that went into creating the modern world: Columbus, conquest, genocide, slavery, imperial war, revolution, and U.S. counterinsurgencies and military occupations.', 10950, 0), (431800, 'Those who remember Washington''s cold war culture in the 1980s will recall the shocked reactions to Reagan''s intervention. People interested in foreign policy were astonished when in 1985 he met alone at Geneva - alone, not a single strategic thinker at his elbow! - with the Soviet Communist master Gorbachev.', 9597, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (431801, 'Once brave politicians and others explain the war on drugs'' true cost, the American people will scream for a cease-fire. Bring the troops home, people will urge. Treat drugs as a health problem, not as a matter for the criminal justice system.', 55271, 0), (431802, 'War consisteth not in battle only, or the act of fighting; but in a tract of time, wherein the will to contend by battle is sufficiently known.', 2593, 0), (431803, 'I''m not going to say I was opposed to the Vietnam War. I''m going to say I''m opposed to war. But I''m also opposed to protests that deny other people their rights.', 1721, 0), (431804, 'If the people raise a great howl against my barbarity and cruelty, I will answer that war is war, and not popularity seeking.', 65193, 0), (431805, 'Circumstances cause us to act the way we do. We should always bear this in mind before judging the actions of others. I realized this from the start during World War II.', 35520, 0), (431806, 'Capitalism is war socialism is peace. ', 68731, 0), (431807, 'To secure peace is to prepare for war.', 2677, 0), (431808, 'What shall I say further? Shall I not stop short and leave to your imaginations to portray the tragic deeds of war? Is it not enough that I here leave it even to unexperience to fancy the hardships, the anxieties, the dangers, even of the best life of a soldier?', 67827, 0), (431809, 'We know we must win the war on terror to protect innocent people and the freedoms that define our way of life.', 68655, 0), (431810, 'Who do you call a civilian in a guerilla war? I mean, it might be a farmer by day or a merchant, a housewife, and by night the housewife may be helping to make landmines and booby traps and who knows.', 3159, 0), (431811, 'Obviously, the greater the length of a war the higher is likely to be the number of casualties in it on either side.', 68684, 0), (431812, 'I know that military alliances and armament have been the reliance for peace for centuries, but they do not produce peace; and when war comes, as it inevitably does under such conditions, these armaments and alliances but intensify and broaden the conflict.', 68732, 0), (431813, 'By the end of World War II, we were the most powerful and least damaged of the great nations. We also had most of the money. America''s hegemony lasted exactly five years.', 2074, 0), (431814, 'There is nothing worth having that can be obtained by nuclear war - nothing material or ideological - no tradition that it can defend. It is utterly self-defeating.', 68733, 0), (431815, 'A Failure in this Duty did once involve our Nation in all the Horrors of Rebellion and Civil War.', 68734, 0), (431816, 'As polarized as we have been, we Americans are locked in a cultural war for the soul of our country.', 54786, 0), (431817, 'There''s a War Crimes Act in the United States passed by a Republican Congress in 1996, which says that grave breaches of the Geneva Convention are subject to the death penalty. And that doesn''t mean the soldier that committed them - that means the commanders.', 1955, 0), (431818, 'The forest restoration campaign is a war to ameliorate nature.', 67852, 0), (431819, 'The primary, the fundamental, the essential purpose of the United Nations is to keep peace. Everything it does which helps prevent World War III is good. Everything which does not further that goal, either directly or indirectly, is at best superfluous.', 65173, 0), (431820, 'I was the guy who was constantly speaking out against the Vietnam War. I have no regrets about that.', 68665, 0), (431821, 'The surrealists, and the modern movement in painting as a whole, seemed to offer a key to the strange postwar world with its threat of nuclear war. The dislocations and ambiguities, in cubism and abstract art as well as the surrealists, reminded me of my childhood in Shanghai.', 2312, 0), (431822, 'No matter what political reasons are given for war, the underlying reason is always economic.', 20910, 0), (431823, 'Cyber war takes place largely in secret, unknown to the general public on both sides.', 68675, 0), (431824, 'I think the Cold War works as a great analogy or simile for different kinds of conflict. It''s funny, when you look back at it, it''s one of the last times that the boundaries were clear. Now, as we see on ''Homeland,'' there are no clear boundaries and enemies.', 68735, 0), (431825, 'I come from - I came from Wales, and it''s a strong, butch society. We were in the war and all that. People didn''t waste time feeling sorry for themselves. You had to get on with it. So my credo is get on with it. I don''t waste time being soft. I''m not cold, but I don''t like being, wasting my time with - life''s too short.', 48587, 0), (431826, 'This war differs from other wars, in this particular. We are not fighting armies but a hostile people, and must make old and young, rich and poor, feel the hard hand of war.', 65193, 0), (431827, 'If you support the war on drugs in its present form, then you''re only paying lip-service to the defense of freedom, and you don''t really grasp the concept of the sovereign individual human being.', 68736, 0), (431828, 'Once we have a war there is only one thing to do. It must be won. For defeat brings worse things than any that can ever happen in war.', 110, 0), (431829, 'War: a massacre of people who don''t know each other for the profit of people who know each other but don''t massacre each other.', 3087, 0), (431830, 'This nation has always struggled with how it was going to deal with poor people and people of color. Every few years you will see some great change in the way that they approach this. We''ve had the war on poverty that never really got into waging a real war on poverty.', 68737, 0), (431831, 'There is many a boy here today who looks on war as all glory, but, boys, it is all hell.', 65193, 0), (431832, 'In all history there is no war which was not hatched by the governments, the governments alone, independent of the interests of the people, to whom war is always pernicious even when successful.', 93, 0), (431833, 'Sometimes people ask me why I began perestroika. Were the causes basically domestic or foreign? The domestic reasons were undoubtedly the main ones, but the danger of nuclear war was so serious that it was a no less significant factor.', 41880, 0), (431834, 'Migration is the story of my life: my parents and grandparents journeyed across four continents to flee war and find jobs, eventually finding their way to the U.S.', 67070, 0), (431835, 'Preparation for war is a constant stimulus to suspicion and ill will.', 68738, 0), (431836, 'I could have ended the war in a month. I could have made North Vietnam look like a mud puddle.', 64083, 0), (431837, 'In the World War nothing was more dreadful to witness than a chain of men starting with a battalion commander and ending with an army commander sitting in telephone boxes, improvised or actual, talking, talking, talking, in place of leading, leading, leading.', 21541, 0), (431838, 'Every time we walk along a beach some ancient urge disturbs us so that we find ourselves shedding shoes and garments or scavenging among seaweed and whitened timbers like the homesick refugees of a long war.', 1812, 0), (431839, 'If we are to assume that North Korea becomes a nuclear-power state, of course the danger of having an all-out nuclear war, that possibility is very slim.', 50249, 0), (431840, 'This gulf war syndrome thing is truly unfortunate, and I''ve met some of the vets who have this. These are my guys, and I feel terrible about it.', 4137, 0), (431841, 'It''s kind of a terrible irony, in a way, that the solution to America''s problems was World War II.', 68739, 0), (431842, 'As a child growing up during the Korean War, I knew poverty. I studied by candlelight.', 21719, 0), (431843, 'There are grave misgivings that the discussion on ecology may be designed to distract attention from the problems of war and poverty.', 2002, 0), (431844, 'It was post war. It was very gray, very dreary. Everything was still rationed when I first saw the United States in 1951. I went over to visit my sister who was a war bride.', 68740, 0), (431845, 'When it comes to war, we focus more on the mainstream coverage of the event, rather than the event itself. People dying is never funny. Protest puppets are always funny.', 54876, 0), (431846, 'You ask me if I will not be glad when the last battle is fought, so far as the country is concerned I, of course, must wish for peace, and will be glad when the war is ended, but if I answer for myself alone, I must say that I shall regret to see the war end.', 16117, 0), (431847, 'But to the fighting soldier that phase of the war is behind. It was left behind after his first battle. His blood is up. He is fighting for his life, and killing now for him is as much a profession as writing is for me.', 9247, 0), (431848, 'Oceania was at war with Eurasia therefore Oceania had always been at war with Eurasia. ', 521, 0), (431849, 'We are muddled into war.', 55270, 0), (431850, 'The Berlin Wall wasn''t the only barrier to fall after the collapse of the Soviet Union and the end of the Cold War. Traditional barriers to the flow of money, trade, people and ideas also fell.', 11721, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (431851, 'I was a surf bum wannabe. I left home at age 17 and moved to Southern California to try to take up surfing as a vocation, but this was in 1964, and there was this nasty little thing called the Vietnam War. As a result, I got drafted.', 68729, 0), (431852, 'Politics are very much like war. We may even have to use poison gas at times.', 3621, 0), (431853, 'But let there be no misunderstanding. The war against terror is every bit as important as our fight against fascism in World War II. Or our struggle against the spread of Communism during the Cold War.', 68741, 0), (431854, 'Wars are caused by undefended wealth.', 110, 0), (431855, 'If it were a fact, it wouldn''t be called intelligence.', 10833, 0), (431856, 'In times of peace, the war party insists on making preparation for war. As soon as prepared for, it insists on making war.', 68687, 0), (431857, 'What creates freedom? A revolution in the streets? Mass protest? Civil war? A change of government? The ousting of the old guard and its replacement by the new? History, more often than not, shows that hopes raised by such events are often dashed, sooner rather than later.', 4059, 0), (431858, 'For a war to be just three conditions are necessary - public authority, just cause, right motive.', 110, 0), (431859, 'Total war is no longer war waged by all members of one national community against all those of another. It is total... because it may well involve the whole world.', 592, 0), (431860, 'I knew that the Hague Convention prohibited the use of poison in war. I didn''t know the details of the terms of the Convention, but I did know of that prohibition.', 41953, 0), (431861, 'I believe that political correctness can be a form of linguistic fascism, and it sends shivers down the spine of my generation who went to war against fascism.', 5869, 0), (431862, 'I was never convinced that war was the best system to bring democracy to the country.', 68742, 0), (431863, 'I saw Kuwait many times before the war. I remember it as a beautiful place, full of very nice people, and it''s a tragedy to see that somebody could set out to deliberately destroy a country the way the Iraqis have.', 4137, 0), (431864, 'The war on drugs is not being won, and it continues to threaten stability and democracy not only in the Andes but throughout the Caribbean as well, where tiny police and military forces are outclassed by the sophisticated equipment in the hands of traffickers passing through the region on the way to their market in this country.', 67439, 0), (431865, 'If you walk into the front hallway of the CIA, you will see, on your left, a statue of William ''Wild Bill'' Donovan. Bill Donovan was the person who created the OSS, the Office of Strategic Services, which was America''s spy agency during World War II and then kind of morphed into what''s now the CIA.', 60069, 0), (431866, 'I think that this is the first war in history that on the morrow the victors sued for peace and the vanquished called for unconditional surrender.', 43480, 0), (431867, 'War on the other hand is such a terrible thing, that no man, especially a Christian man, has the right to assume the responsibility of starting it.', 93, 0), (431868, 'War can only be abolished through war, and in order to get rid of the gun it is necessary to take up the gun.', 15795, 0), (431869, 'I am at war... with the principal personage of traditional philosophy, that abstract subject who masquerades as everyone and anyone, but is really a male subject in disguise.', 68743, 0), (431870, 'The high point of civilization is that you can hate me and I can hate you but we develop an etiquette that allows us to deal with each other because if we acted solely upon our impulse we''d probably go to war.', 68744, 0), (431871, 'I am passionately interested in understanding how my country works. And if you want to know about this thing called the United States of America you have to know about the Civil War.', 10198, 0), (431872, 'When you go to war, both sides lose totally.', 1121, 0), (431873, 'I think what the Nobel committee is doing is going beyond war and looking at what humanity can do to prevent war. Sustainable management of our natural resources will promote peace.', 17733, 0), (431874, 'One of the things that ultimately led me to leave mathematics and go into political science was thinking I could prevent nuclear war.', 68745, 0), (431875, 'One big, glaring difference I can think of between Iraq and Vietnam is the news coverage. During the Vietnam War era, you had TV coverage of the war saturating the airwaves every night, and that coverage wasn''t put through a military filter at all.', 68746, 0), (431876, 'I think that you can honour the sacrifices of a common soldier without glorifying war.', 10676, 0), (431877, 'There was a belief after World War I that painting could be an act of civil revolt. I want this exhibition, ''New Museum,'' to be an act of civil disobedience. It''s not so much about the New Museum on the Bowery, but the idea of challenging museums as projections of cultural authority. It''s painting as insurgency.', 68747, 0), (431878, 'As history has repeatedly proven, one trade tariff begets another, then another - until you''ve got a full-blown trade war. No one ever wins, and consumers always get screwed.', 67775, 0), (431879, 'In our Country... one class of men makes war and leaves another to fight it out.', 65193, 0), (431880, 'I wanted to fight in the Iraq war because I felt like I had an obligation as a human being to help free people from oppression.', 25121, 0), (431881, 'I don''t know why you use a fancy French word like detente when there''s a good English phrase for it - cold war.', 12971, 0), (431882, 'The great leaders of the second world war alliance, Franklin Roosevelt and Winston Churchill, understood the twin sides of destruction and salvation. Their war aims were not only to defeat fascism, but to create a world of shared prosperity.', 68748, 0), (431883, 'Western civilization, Christianity, decency are struggling for their very lives. In this worldwide civil war, race prejudice is our most dangerous enemy, for it is a disease at the very root of our democratic life.', 68749, 0), (431884, 'While religious tolerance is surely better than religious war, tolerance is not without its liabilities. Our fear of provoking religious hatred has rendered us incapable of criticizing ideas that are now patently absurd and increasingly maladaptive.', 1816, 0), (431885, 'People have to realize that dieting is not a sprint, it''s a marathon. If you celebrate the small victories, you will eventually win the war.', 68750, 0), (431886, 'We can have a World War, I see absolutely no reason why we shouldn''t have a World Party.', 8314, 0), (431887, 'The most shocking fact about war is that its victims and its instruments are individual human beings, and that these individual beings are condemned by the monstrous conventions of politics to murder or be murdered in quarrels not their own.', 1032, 0), (431888, 'War is hell.', 65193, 0), (431889, 'War makes thieves and peace hangs them.', 3428, 0), (431890, 'It is not only the living who are killed in war.', 988, 0), (431891, 'The great object is that every man be armed.', 3269, 0), (431892, 'War never takes a wicked man by chance, the good man always.', 139, 0), (431893, 'Sweat saves blood.', 16072, 0), (431894, 'It has too often been too easy for rulers and governments to incite man to war.', 17580, 0), (431895, 'A boy doesn''t have to go to war to be a hero he can say he doesn''t like pie when he sees there isn''t enough to go around. ', 13154, 0), (431896, 'The terrorists and their supporters declared war on the United States - and war is what they got.', 2358, 0), (431897, 'Allow the president to invade a neighboring nation whenever he shall deem it necessary to repel an invasion,and you allow him to do so whenever he may choose to say he deems it necessary for such purpose - and you allow him to make war at pleasure.', 1012, 0), (431898, 'War is a racket. It is the only one international in scope. It is the only one in which the profits are reckoned in dollars and the losses in lives.', 66579, 0), (431899, 'The next war... may well bury Western civilization forever.', 2564, 0), (431900, 'The question is: how bad do things have to get before you will do something about it? Where is your line in the sand? If you don''t enforce the constitutional limitations on your government very soon, you are likely to find out what World War III will be like.', 68751, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (431901, 'When this sad war is over we will all return to our homes, and feel that we can ask no higher honor than the proud consciousness that we belonged to the Army of the Potomac.', 67727, 0), (431902, 'Meanwhile, our young men and women whose economic circumstances make military service a viable career choice are dying bravely in a war with no end in sight.', 41313, 0), (431903, 'War is a poor chisel to carve out tomorrow.', 21767, 0), (431904, 'Peace must be more than the absence of war.', 67891, 0), (431905, 'In most of the European countries - France stands out in its resistance to this particular form of American cultural imperialism - the national film industries were forced onto the defensive after the war by such binding agreements.', 47859, 0), (431906, 'The real trouble with war (modern war) is that it gives no one a chance to kill the right people.', 8630, 0), (431907, 'We want to keep the actual Civil War experience alive.', 68752, 0), (431908, 'If we justify war, it is because all peoples always justify the traits of which they find themselves possessed, not because war will bear an objective examination of its merits.', 9314, 0), (431909, 'The M-1 is the best tank in the world, if you can get it to the war in time, if you have a Saddam Hussein who''ll give you seven months to move your forces in.', 68753, 0), (431910, 'The guys who won World War II and that whole generation have disappeared, and now we have a bunch of teenage twits.', 2269, 0), (431911, 'South Korea first allowed women into the military in 1950 during the Korean War. Back then, female soldiers mainly held administrative and support positions. Women began to take on combat roles in the 1990s when the three military academies, exclusive to men, began accepting women.', 68754, 0), (431912, 'What ''War and Peace'' is to the novel and ''Hamlet'' is to the theater, Swan Lake'' is to ballet - that is, the name which to many people stands for and sums up an art form.', 20280, 0), (431913, 'I am the daughter of Nigerian immigrants. My mother is a survivor of both polio and of the Igbo genocide during her country''s civil war in the late 1960s.', 68755, 0), (431914, 'The ancient Jewish people gave the world the vision of eternal peace, of universal disarmament, of abolishing the teaching and learning of war.', 68756, 0), (431915, 'The story of FDR as U.S. Commander in Chief is a heroic war story of a president who had already overcome great adversity in facing polio but who went on to take the reins of our armed forces in the greatest conflagration in human history - on our behalf.', 68757, 0), (431916, 'Science fiction has always been a means for political comment. H.G. Wells'' ''The War of the Worlds'' wasn''t about a Martian invasion - it was a critique of British colonialism, and... ''The Time Machine'' is really an indictment of the British class system.', 13423, 0), (431917, 'I know war as few other men now living know it, and nothing to me is more revolting. I have long advocated its complete abolition, as its very destructiveness on both friend and foe has rendered it useless as a method of settling international disputes.', 110, 0), (431918, 'During war, the laws are silent.', 68758, 0), (431919, 'History teaches that war begins when governments believe the price of aggression is cheap.', 1727, 0), (431920, 'The most persistent sound which reverberates through man''s history is the beating of war drums.', 14934, 0), (431921, 'There is hardly such a thing as a war in which it makes no difference who wins. Nearly always one side stands more or less for progress, the other side more or less for reaction.', 521, 0), (431922, 'War is wretched beyond description, and only a fool or a fraud could sentimentalize its cruel reality.', 9128, 0), (431923, 'War settles nothing.', 2119, 0), (431924, 'A man who says that no patriot should attack the war until it is over... is saying no good son should warn his mother of a cliff until she has fallen.', 67663, 0), (431925, 'I have many times asked myself whether there can be more potent advocates of peace upon earth through the years to come than this massed multitude of silent witnesses to the desolation of war.', 68759, 0), (431926, 'The war is coming to the streets of America and if you are not keeping and bearing and practicing with your arms then you will be helpless and you will be the victim of evil.', 68760, 0), (431927, 'During the first six years of my life, Hungary was one of the most important components of the Habsburg dynasty''s vast Austro-Hungarian Empire, but after World War I it became an independent national entity.', 68761, 0), (431928, 'The magnificent army that fought in Desert Storm is a great army, and it still is a magnificent army today. But it was one we designed for the Cold War, and the Cold War has been over for ten years now.', 68762, 0), (431929, 'It required a strong heart to stand up against such talk, but I urged my people to be quiet and not to begin a war.', 4664, 0), (431930, 'Our enemies are Medes and Persians, men who for centuries have lived soft and luxurious lives; we of Macedon for generations past have been trained in the hard school of danger and war. Above all, we are free men, and they are slaves.', 23413, 0), (431931, 'Throughout this evolution from left to right, Beard always detested war. Hence his writings were slanted to show that the military side of history was insignificant or a mere reflection of economic forces.', 68763, 0), (431932, 'The Korean war has always been an unpopular war among the American people.', 3412, 0), (431933, 'The young patriots now returning from war in Iraq and Afghanistan and other deployments worldwide are joining the ranks of veterans to whom America owes an immense debt of gratitude.', 68764, 0), (431934, 'The definition of a modern approach to war is the acknowledgement of individual lives lost.', 58539, 0), (431935, 'We were succeeding. When you looked at specifics, this became a war of attrition. We were winning.', 68692, 0), (431936, 'I am not protesting against the conduct of the war, but against the political errors and insincerities for which the fighting men are being sacrificed.', 8904, 0), (431937, 'Yes, what has happened is we have moved from responding to these terrorist attacks as acts of civil disobedience to getting to the point after September 11 that we said, no, this is not just civil disobedience, this is an act of war.', 38698, 0), (431938, 'There are patriots who opposed the war in Iraq and there are patriots who supported the war in Iraq. We are one people, all of us pledging allegiance to the stars and stripes, all of us defending the United States of America.', 1693, 0), (431939, 'War, except in self-defense, is a failure of moral imagination.', 4793, 0), (431940, 'Guerrilla war is a kind of war waged by the few but dependent on the support of many.', 21078, 0), (431941, 'We can only move to a long-term resolution regarding terrorism and war by planting seeds of peace. We have to start with ourselves.', 48586, 0), (431942, 'War is not merely a political act but a real political instrument, a continuation of political intercourse, a carrying out of the same by other means.', 2677, 0), (431943, 'Looking back, there is nothing wrong with that peace, love and equality that the hippies espoused. In many ways, we have regressed because they were into organic food, back to nature, make love not war, be good to all men, share and share alike - which is what many are talking about now.', 66898, 0), (431944, 'There aren''t a lot of guys like me left. But I''m a war horse. I''ve been through it all. And you know something about war horses? Through the sleet, through the snow, they just keep going.', 68765, 0), (431945, 'America stood at the summit of power, emerging from the Cold War as an economic, cultural and military force without equal.', 68766, 0), (431946, 'It''s never acceptable to target civilians. It violates the Geneva Accords, it violates the international law of war and it violates all principles of morality.', 17810, 0), (431947, 'I am a Quaker. And as everyone knows, Quakers, for 300 years, have, on conscientious ground, been against participating in war. I was sentenced to three years in federal prison because I could not religiously and conscientiously accept killing my fellow man.', 51917, 0), (431948, 'Remember, God provides the best camouflage several hours out of every 24.', 68767, 0), (431949, 'I do not believe that the men who served in uniform in Vietnam have been given the credit they deserve. It was a difficult war against an unorthodox enemy.', 68692, 0), (431950, 'War is much too serious a thing to be left to military men.', 59960, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (431951, 'From a scientific perspective there is some indication that a nuclear war could deplete the earth''s ozone layer or, less likely, could bring on a new Ice Age - but there is no suggestion that either the created order or mankind would be destroyed in the process.', 62777, 0), (431952, 'Until the last great war, a general expectation of material improvement was an idea peculiar to Western man. Now war and its aftermath have made economic and social progress a political imperative in every quarter of the globe.', 17580, 0), (431953, 'You can easily die racing to cover a bank robbery as you can in a war zone.', 66975, 0), (431954, 'I also hear your president say that war is the means of last resort and I think he means that. I met him last autumn and he assured me that they wanted to come through and disarm Iraq by peaceful means, and that''s what we are trying to do as hard as we can.', 17604, 0), (431955, 'Ideas are the great warriors of the world, and a war that has no idea behind it, is simply a brutality.', 44653, 0), (431956, 'I tell people I won''t vote to go to war unless I''m ready to go or send my kids.', 67555, 0), (431957, 'World War II had a very important impact on the development of technology, as a whole.', 63450, 0), (431958, 'Since the Six-Day War, the whole world, which is the real arena of battle between us and the Palestinians, believes that Israel is right in regard to procedure, namely problems and disputes should be solved around the negotiating table.', 60701, 0), (431959, 'War, I thought, was the most negative aspect of male heterosexuality. If more men were homosexual, there would be no wars, because homosexual men would never kill other men, whereas heterosexual men love killing other men.', 1259, 0), (431960, 'I''ve been influenced by some of the greatest designers. Charles Eames. And Bruno Munari in the ''50s in Italy - when they had to retool the industry of war into an industry to help society. In a way, I''m influenced by designers that were there at a radical time of change.', 68768, 0), (431961, 'War is the unfolding of miscalculations.', 16196, 0), (431962, 'Can anything be stupider than that a man has the right to kill me because he lives on the other side of a river and his ruler has a quarrel with mine, though I have not quarrelled with him?', 144, 0), (431963, 'Don''t forget what I discovered that over ninety percent of all national deficits from 1921 to 1939 were caused by payments for past, present, and future wars.', 2261, 0), (431964, 'It seems like such a terrible shame that innocent civilians have to get hurt in wars, otherwise combat would be such a wonderfully healthy way to rid the human race of unneeded trash.', 68769, 0), (431965, 'War is fear cloaked in courage.', 68692, 0), (431966, 'No country can act wisely simultaneously in every part of the globe at every moment of time.', 2393, 0), (431967, 'Everyone, when there''s war in the air, learns to live in a new element: falsehood.', 42142, 0), (431968, 'One may know how to gain a victory, and know not how to use it.', 84, 0), (431969, 'War, I have always said, forces men to change their standards, regardless of whether their country has won or lost.', 55576, 0), (431970, 'When the war of the giants is over the wars of the pygmies will begin.', 3621, 0), (431971, 'You can''t say civilization don''t advance... in every war they kill you in a new way.', 1122, 0), (431972, 'It was a requirement by the veterans to list the 57,000 names. We''re reaching a time that we''ll acknowledge the individual in a war on a national level.', 58539, 0), (431973, 'We have been travelling through a cloud. The sky has been dark ever since the war began.', 68770, 0), (431974, 'War is cruelty, and none can make it gentle.', 68771, 0), (431975, 'The Japanese scored an important victory at Pearl Harbor, but the attack pulled the United States into World War II, and four years later, Japan was in ruins, utterly defeated.', 68253, 0), (431976, 'Basketball is like war in that offensive weapons are developed first, and it always takes a while for the defense to catch up.', 47736, 0), (431977, 'Let the word go forth from this time and place, to friend and foe alike, that the torch has been passed to a new generation of Americans - born in this century, tempered by war, disciplined by a hard and bitter peace.', 1680, 0), (431978, 'The basic fact about human existence is not that it is a tragedy, but that it is a bore. It is not so much a war as an endless standing in line.', 411, 0), (431979, 'This administration here and now declares unconditional war on poverty.', 1763, 0), (431980, 'In war there is no prize for runner-up.', 65434, 0), (431981, 'In war, when a commander becomes so bereft of reason and perspective that he fails to understand the dependence of arms on Divine guidance, he no longer deserves victory.', 65434, 0), (431982, 'War is delightful to those who have had no experience of it.', 67390, 0), (431983, 'A war for a great principle ennobles a nation.', 2076, 0), (431984, 'Being over seventy is like being engaged in a war. All our friends are going or gone and we survive amongst the dead and the dying as on a battlefield.', 62829, 0), (431985, 'I am never going to have anything more to do with politics or politicians. When this war is over I shall confine myself entirely to writing and painting.', 3621, 0), (431986, 'War is like love it always finds a way. ', 1140, 0), (431987, 'There must be people who remember World War II and the Holocaust who can help us get out of this rut.', 21702, 0), (431988, 'Every action is seen to fall into one of three main categories, guarding, hitting, or moving. Here, then, are the elements of combat, whether in war or pugilism.', 21078, 0), (431989, 'We shall never be able to remove suspicion and fear as potential causes of war until communication is permitted to flow, free and open, across international boundaries.', 16121, 0), (431990, 'To establish any mode to abolish war, however advantageous it might be to Nations, would be to take from such Government the most lucrative of its branches.', 1131, 0), (431991, 'I''m tired. I''m tired of feeling rejected by the American people. I''m tired of waking up in the middle of the night worrying about the war.', 1763, 0), (431992, 'The Canadian government continues to say they will not help us if we go to war with Iraq. However, the prime minister of Canada said he''d like to help, but he''s pretty sure that last time he checked, Canada had no army.', 1326, 0), (431993, 'We''ve killed a million Iraqis since the start of the Gulf war - mostly by blocking humanitarian aid.', 68702, 0), (431994, 'There are no absolute rules of conduct, either in peace or war. Everything depends on circumstances.', 1626, 0), (431995, 'War is not the continuation of politics with different means, it is the greatest mass-crime perpetrated on the community of man.', 29457, 0), (431996, 'The time not to become a father is eighteen years before a war.', 994, 0), (431997, 'I just want you to know that, when we talk about war, we''re really talking about peace.', 2358, 0), (431998, 'One certain effect of war is to diminish freedom of expression.', 7161, 0), (431999, 'Unconditional war can no longer lead to unconditional victory. It can no longer serve to settle disputes... can no longer be of concern to great powers alone.', 1680, 0), (432000, 'What is more immoral than war?', 2459, 0);
